title: peanut butter cups
directions: Melt butter and peanut butter together.
Add other ingredients.
Melt chocolate chips.
Fill 1/3 small muffin tin; cover with melted chocolate.

title: chicken pasta bake
directions: Saute first 5 ingredients in butter until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Stir into basil, salt and crushed red pepper; set aside.
Cook pasta according to package directions; drain.
Combine pasta vegetable mixture and chicken in large bowl.
Spoon mixture into a 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Combine whipping cream and cheeses in a medium saucepan.
Cook over low heat until cheese melts, stirring frequently.
Pour sauce over pasta mixture.
To store, cover and refrigerate up to 24 hours.
To serve, bake covered at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until thoroughly heated. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Can be frozen and sliced.

title: black raspberry custard pie
directions: In large bowl, beat eggs, sugar, flour and milk.
Spread raspberries in pie shell.
Pour sugar mixture over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until set.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Drop by spoonfuls on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cranberry-jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water (use the amount of water on package of Jell-O).
Add other ingredients and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Um-um.

title: lime pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers
1/4-inch
thick
and
cover
with lime water. Soak 24
hours.
Stir
often
with wooden spoon. Rinse well and cover with	fresh water for 3 hours.
Drain and cover with solution of next 7 ingredients, then let stand overnight. In a.m., place over heat and boil gently for 30 or 40 minutes, then can.

title: banana chocolate chip muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients together (flour, sugar, salt, baking powder and chocolate chips).
Mix remaining ingredients together with fork.
Gently mix dry and wet ingredients together just until moist.

title: lime jello punch
directions: Mix hot water, Jell-O and sugar in medium pan until the Jell-O and sugar are completely dissolved.
Add cold water, pineapple juice and lemon juice.
Pour into a plastic container if you want to freeze this mixture.
If not, store in the refrigerator.
Add ginger ale and ice before serving.
Makes 1 gallon.
Serves 40 to 50 people.

title: colorful cauliflower salad
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Lightly grease a large baking sheet.
In a large bowl, stir together the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
In a small bowl, stir eggs and buttermilk; set aside.
Using a pastry blender, cut the butter into the dry ingredients until the mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in the raisins and walnuts. Make a well in the center and pour in egg/buttermilk mixture.
Stir until just combined.
Flour a counter or work surface; add the dough and knead a few strokes to evenly distribute the ingredients (it will be sticky).
Flour the surface of the dough and pat out into a rectangle.
Using a cleaver or knife, cut the scones into 3-inch squares and place on baking sheet.
The scones should not touch, but they can be close (1-inch apart).
They will expand when baked, but are easily separated.
Bake for 15 to 18 minutes until lightly browned.
Remove from pan and place on a cooling rack. They may be eaten hot or cold with butter or preserves.
They are just as good the next day; reheat and enjoy.

title: tuna casserole supreme
directions: Prepare macaroni dinner as directed.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in a 1-quart casserole for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: doug's sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix above ingredients and spread over top of sweet potato mixture.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Combine with soup, tuna, peas, onions and milk.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: favorite macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute pepper and onion in margarine. Reduce heat to low.
Add Velveeta cheese and milk.
Stir until cheese spread is melted.
Stir in macaroni.
Spoon into a 2-quart greased casserole dish.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add oil, sugar, vanilla and zucchini. Mix lightly but well.
Add flour, cinnamon, salt, soda, baking powder and nuts.
Pour into well-greased loaf pan.
Cook for 45 to 60 minutes, or until toothpick comes out clean, at 350°.
(Can frost if desired.)

title: cheese ball
directions: Beat softened cream cheese with electric mixer on medium speed.
Add Cheddar cheese, if desired.
Add lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, olives, onions and garlic.
Mix on slow speed until well blended.
Put in airtight container overnight. Refrigerate.
Mold into ball, roll in chopped nuts.

title: fudge
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in a 6-quart saucepan and cook to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add last 4 ingredients.
Beat until thick.
Spread in buttered dish and let cool and then cut into squares.

title: easy taco pizza
directions: Prepare ground beef and onion following directions on taco seasoning.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Prepare pizza crust mix and arrange in rectangle on large greased cookie sheet.
Spread hamburg mixture on crust.
Sprinkle tomatoes and peppers on the hamburg. Top with shredded cheese.
Bake for 16 to 20 minutes, or until crust is brown.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown beef in large, heavy kettle; drain and add onions.
Cook until onions are tender.
Add remaining ingredients except cheese; simmer for 15 minutes (minimum).
Ladle into bowls; top with the grated cheese and tortilla chips.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: grits fiesta
directions: Cook grits done in water.
Saute bell pepper, onion and celery.
Add to grits along with milk, Cheez Whiz, eggs, pimento, garlic and cream cheese.
Stir thoroughly and pour into casserole sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: corn and rice especiale
directions: Cook rice according to package direction.
Cook green pepper and onion in butter until tender but not brown; stir into rice with corn, eggs, milk and salt.
Turn into 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake covered at 375° until knife inserted in center comes out clean, 40 to 45 minutes.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs and paprika around edge.
Bake uncovered about 5 minutes longer.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: marvelous meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Mix well with hands.
Turn mixture into 8 x 4 x 3 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Let stand 10 minutes before slicing.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: You will also need a trifle bowl or glass bowl.

title: hot mushroom dip
directions: Saute mushrooms.
Thin cream cheese with clam juice and combine with all ingredients.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Serve hot with crackers or corn chips.

title: german fruit cookies
directions: Grind fruits and nuts together.
Combine sugar, butter, coffee and molasses in a 3-quart saucepan.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Cool. Blend in flour and fruit mixture.
Chill at least 4 hours (overnight is fine).
Shape into 1-inch balls with well floured hands.
Place on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Dip warm cookies in warm glaze.

title: sweet corn muffins
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix rest of ingredients in another bowl.
Stir milk mixture into corn meal mixture just until moistened.
Spoon batter into greased muffin pans.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from pans to cool.

title: spiced apple cider
directions: Simmer cider with spices and brown sugar for 10 minutes. Strain.
Serve hot or cold.
If serving cold, you may add lemon and orange juices before serving.

title: early morning casserole
directions: Scramble and cook until brown the sausage.
Drain on paper towel and put in ovenproof baking dish. Melt in skillet the butter.
Scramble until slightly soft the eggs.
Pour over sausage and add soup and chilies.
Cover top with grated cheese.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for approximately 15 minutes, or until heated through and through.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sue's famous apple pie
directions: Crust: sift flour, baking powder and salt together. Cut in shortening to size of small pieces. Add water a little at a time until dough is moist enough to hold together. Chill. Roll dough for bottom and top crust.

title: pumpkin oxtail soup
directions: Dice pumpkin and boil with oxtails 2 hours over medium heat. When broken down, add onion, garlic, diced carrots, diced potatoes, garlic, salt and pepper.
Cook on low two more hours. Soup should have a consistency of a thick sauce.

title: spinach dip
directions: Squeeze spinach dry.
Add remaining ingredients and blend well.
Cover and refrigerate at least two hours.

title: ham biscuits
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Place margarine in a 2-quart baking dish.
Microwave at High setting for 30 seconds or until margarine melts.
Add green pepper and next 5 ingredients, stirring well.
Stir in potatoes.
Cover tightly with heavy-duty plastic wrap.
Fold back a corner to allow steam to escape.
Microwave at High setting for 12 to 14 minutes or until tender, uncovering and stirring every 5 minutes. Sprinkle with paprika.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: german cheese ball
directions: Drain sauerkraut and squeeze dry.
Mix all ingredients (except cream cheese).
Shape into loaf or ball.
Chill overnight.

title: chocolate lover's delight
directions: Make cake mix per directions on box.
Bake.
Let cool for 10 minutes.
Use end of wooden spoon and poke holes in cake.
Add sweetened milk and caramel topping.
Put in fridge.
When ready to eat, top with Cool Whip and crushed candy bar.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer ingredients in dish.
Mix mayonnaise and sugar together and spread mixture over layered ingredients.
Sprinkle cheese and bacon bits on top.
Refrigerate 8 to 12 hours.

title: chocolate eclair cake #1
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with whole graham crackers.
Mix the pudding with 3 cups milk; beat for 2 minutes.
Add Cool Whip; mix well.
Spread 1/2 mixture over crackers.
Place another layer of crackers over pudding.
Spread remaining pudding over crackers; add another layer of crackers.

title: yellow cake layers
directions: Cream butter and sugar, add eggs one at time.
Sift flour, salt and soda, add to creamed mixture alternately with milk ending with flour and vanilla.
Grease and flour 3 or 4 cake pans.
Bake at 350 for 20-25 mins. or until tooth pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans 10 mins. then turn out on racks to cool. Frost with favorite frosting.

title: two gallons barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all items together.
Cook until it boils.
Put in quart jars and seal.

title: jay's cheese puffs
directions: Add beaten egg yolks and Worcestershire sauce to cheese. Combine with beaten egg whites and fold in crushed potato chips. Place small amount of mixture on whole potato chips and bake in 400° oven until puffed and brown, 5 to 6 minutes.
Serve at once.

title: really easy healthy pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place Boboli on pizza pan.
Saute in nonstick pan the onion, pepper and mushrooms.
Put spaghetti sauce on boboli.
Spoon veggies on evenly.
Bake in oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and add cheese on top.
Bake for 5 more minutes.
Slice and enjoy!

title: chicken and sour cream enchiladas
directions: Mix 1 cup sour cream, chicken, 1 cup cheese, 1/4 cup salsa, cilantro and cumin.
Spoon about 1/4 cup of chicken mixture onto each tortilla.
Roll up tortillas.
Place tortillas in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Top with remaining 3/4 cup salsa.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining 1 cup cheese; continue baking until cheese is melted.
Top with lettuce and tomatoes.
Serve with remaining 1 cup sour cream.
Makes 10 servings.
Preparation time:
20 minutes.
Cooking time:
35 minutes.

title: sauce for barbecued spareribs
directions: Mix all ingredients and brush over ribs as they cook.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix together the sugar, flour and salt, then add milk and egg yolks to this mixture.
Constantly stir over medium heat until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat and add margarine, vanilla and coconut; mix well.
Pour into baked pie crust or graham cracker crust.

title: chicken and corn chowder
directions: Simmer chicken, onion, carrot, herbs and water in 6-quart pot until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken.
Strain broth and return to pot.
Dice chicken (bite-size) and return to broth.
With broth boiling, add the potatoes; reduce heat until potatoes are cooked. Add the corn and cook for another 7 minutes.
Garnish bowls with parsley.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: dried-chipped beef dip
directions: Melt butter.
Add pecans and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: radish dip
directions: Mix sour cream, cream cheese, Worcestershire, mustard, celery salt, salt and hot sauce.
Add in radishes, cucumbers, bell pepper and onion.
Mix well and serve with assorted crackers.

title: red beans and sausage
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Rinse well.
Cut sausage to desired lengths.
Put all ingredients in pot and cover with water, about 1 1/2 inches from layer of beans.
Cook until beans are tender.

title: lemony broccoli with garlic
directions: In a large skillet, over medium-high heat, heat the oil.
Add garlic.
Cook 1 to 2 minutes. Add broccoli. Cook 3 minutes, turning frequently to coat with oil. Add chicken broth and lemon peel.
Reduce heat to medium.
Simmer, covered, 5 to 7 minutes until broccoli is tender but still crisp. Sprinkle with lemon juice, salt and pepper to taste.
Makes 12 servings.

title: "temple" punch
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large punch bowl. Serve in cups with strawberry or lemon slice on handle.
Serves 35 to 50.

title: fish casserole
directions: Layer dressing in 9 x 9 inch baking dish.
Cover with fish. Mix soup and milk and pour over fish.
Sprinkle with Swiss cheese. Bake, covered, at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.

title: highland hot cakes
directions: Mix oats and milk; let stand 5 minutes.
Add eggs, melted shortening, then sifted dry ingredients.
Cook on a hot griddle.

title: baked gouda
directions: Using finger, smooth out perforated marks on dough to form solid rectangle.
Remove casing from Gouda; place cheese in center of dough.
Bring up all corners of dough to totally encase cheese, making sure all openings are sealed.
Brush top with egg white; sprinkle with sesame seed.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet; bake at 375° for 30 minutes, or until golden.
Allow to set for a few minutes before cutting into wedges.

title: chunky peanut butter cookies
directions: In a small bowl, mix flour and baking powder.
In large bowl, with mixer at medium speed, beat margarine, peanut butter, sugar and Sweet 'N Low until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla. Stir in flour mixture and peanuts.

title: baked potato  casserole
directions: Peel and dice potatoes.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: hot nectar
directions: Mix ingredients in a large saucepan, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Store in recycled apple juice bottles, etc., and heat desired amount as needed.
I usually pour desired amount into bottom of coffeepot.
Put the cloves and cinnamon stick in basket and perk!
This nectar is wonderful for sore throats and colds in the winter time!

title: dump-it cake
directions: Pour pineapple into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Spoon pie filling over pineapple. Sprinkle with coconut and nuts.
Slice butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Add sugar to oil, then eggs, pumpkin, spices sifted with flour, water and raisins.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Makes one loaf.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Add flour, 1/3 at a time, and stir.
Refrigerate overnight.
Cut into size you want.
Cook at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix instant pudding with milk; let thicken, then add Cool Whip and sour cream. Mix well with hand mixer. Layer the bottom of 8 x 11-inch pan with vanilla wafers, then cut up bananas and stir into pudding mixture. Pour pudding mixture over layered vanilla wafers. Crumble a few vanilla wafers over top and chill.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni until tender.
Drain.
Mix in oil to keep noodles separated.
Cool.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Top with bacon bits or grated cheese, if desired.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Scrape and slice carrots and boil in salted water until tender.
Drain well.
Combine all ingredients in a gallon Ziploc bag.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: lasagna(good)
directions: Put ground beef, chili powder, rosemary, garlic salt, parsley, salt, pepper, oregano, sweet basil, sugar and dried onions together and cook for 30 minutes.
Drain.
While hamburger is cooking, cook lasagna noodles (1/2 pound).
Add 1 large jar Ragu spaghetti sauce to hamburger mixture.
Spread some sauce in bottom of oblong pan, then noodles, sauce, cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven and let set about 15 minutes before eating.
Serve with salad and bread stick.

title: trent's casserole
directions: Brown ground
beef
and onion.	Drain well. Add drained corn, mushroom soup and milk.
Heat until hot.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix pumpkin, sugar, spices and flour first.
Add beaten eggs, then milk. Pour into unbaked crust. Bake at 400° for 45 to 55 minutes. Makes one pie.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Combine condensed milk and pecans and spread over warm cake. Broil for 10 minutes.
Remove and cool.
Beat butter & cocoa with mixer and add milk and vanilla and spread over cake.

title: rebecca's brisket
directions: Marinate beef brisket overnight in all ingredients except barbecue sauce.
Put brisket into cooking bag.
Remove air from bag.
Bake 1 hour per pound at 300° in a covered dish.

title: stuffed celery
directions: Blend cream cheese, Worcestershire sauce and lemon juice until smooth in a small bowl.
Stir in nuts.
Spread about 1 tablespoon into hollow in each piece of celery.
Garnish with slivered nuts, if desired.

title: green relish
directions: Place chopped vegetables in a large bowl. Sprinkle with pickling salt, stir well. Cover and chill overnight. Rinse well in colander under running water.

title: jello pudding
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and bring to boil.
Boil until thickens or longer.
Cool until jells.
Add Cool Whip and oranges to jellied mixture.
Mix and chill.

title: lobster stew
directions: Mix all ingredients except the cooked rice.
Simmer 1/2 hour, until hot.
Add cooked rice.
Simmer 5 minutes longer.
Serve.

title: chicken broccoli divan
directions: Grease a casserole dish with butter.
Arrange broccoli mixture and top with chicken.

Combine soup and milk; pour over chicken. (It depends on the size of your casserole dish as to whether you have to make another layer of broccoli mixture and chicken.) Sprinkle with cheese; pour Italian crispums over top and bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until hot.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: angel pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased pie pan. Cook for 1 hour at 300° until done.
Sprinkle nuts on top.

title: stuffed sole
directions: Lay sole flat; scatter shrimp evenly over each fillet.
Roll and secure with toothpicks.
Place fillets on a greased shallow baking dish and season with salt and pepper.
Stir together lemon juice, wine, onion and garlic.
Pour over fillets.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: fried okra
directions: Slice okra thin; coat with cornmeal.
Fry in oil over low heat until golden brown.

title: squash relish
directions: Mix together squash, peppers and onions; add salt.
Let set while you boil vinegar mixture (vinegar, sugar, pickling spice and turmeric tied in white bag).
Slowly stir in squash, onions and peppers.
Cook until mixture begins to change color.
Pack in sterilized canning jars and seal.

title: tia maria trifle
directions: Mix pudding mix, milk and liquor together and cook until bubbly.
Cool.
In serving bowl, add small amount of pudding, Cool Whip and cake, layering until the top ending with Cool Whip. Sprinkle with chocolate sprinkles or cherries.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: souper gravy
directions: *Condensed vegetable, celery or chicken soup can be used.

title: amish bread
directions: Mix the ingredients together and this will provide 3 Starters.
Count this as Day 1.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Put peaches on bottom of greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Mix together shortening, sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and milk.
Spread this over the peaches.
Mix sugar and juice.
Pour over dough. Pour melted butter over the mixture.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: fritters
directions: Dissolve sugar and yeast in lukewarm water.
Add yeast mixture to rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Cover with towel; let rise for 40 minutes.
Stir down and add 1 cup of any fruit or vegetable. Stir down again.
Drop by spoonful in deep melted shortening. Fry, turning once until golden.
(Bananas are especially good this way.)

title: poppy chicken
directions: Cook and cube chicken.
Put in casserole.
Make 1 cup chicken gravy with 2 tablespoons butter, flour and broth.
Mix with sour cream and pour over chicken.
Crush Ritz crackers and put on top. Melt 1 stick butter and drizzle over crackers.
Cover with poppy seed.
Cook for 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Bring sugar, milk and margarine to a boil for 2 minutes; remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop quickly on wax paper with a teaspoon.
Cool.

title: monkey bread
directions: Roll quartered biscuits in sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Place in well-greased Bundt pan.
In between each layer of biscuits, sprinkle raisins and walnuts.
In saucepan, bring leftover sugar-cinnamon mixture, vanilla and margarine to a slow boil. Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately.

title: tangy cocktail sauce
directions: In small bowl, combine all ingredients.
Cover; chill.
Serve with fish or seafood.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes about 1 cup.

title: shrimp, scallop and chicken provencal
directions: In large skillet, heat oil over medium-high heat.
Saute shrimp just until pink and scallops just until firm.
Remove with slotted spoon; set aside.
Add chicken to skillet; saute just until cooked.
Remove with slotted spoon; set aside.

title: braunschweiger dip
directions: Blend sour cream and soup mix.
Add rest of ingredients. Blend on medium-high until mixed; chill.
Makes 1 3/4 cups.

title: grandma smith's banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour loaf pan.
Mix flour, salt, nutmeg and baking powder; set aside.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add flour mixture alternately with mashed bananas.
Add nuts.
Pour in prepared pan. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Steam broccoli (not fork-tender).
Mix everything together. Pour into a 3-quart greased casserole dish.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: prune cake
directions: Sift flour once.
Add baking soda and spices then sift 3 times.
Cream butter thoroughly, add sugar gradually and cream together until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and prunes.
Then add flour alternately with milk, a small amount at a time.
Beat well after each addition.
Bake in two layer pans at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Spread caramel frosting between layers and on top and sides.
May also be served unfrosted.
(Recipe about 60 years old.)

title: best ever and easiest ever roasted turkey
directions: You will need a piece of old sheet or cheesecloth large enough to completely cover and tuck under turkey.

title: frozen strawberry squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix first 4 ingredients in shallow baking pan.
Bake for 20 minutes, stirring and breaking up as you stir.
Sprinkle 2/3 crumb mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Save the rest for topping.
Combine egg whites, sugar and strawberries in a bowl; add lemon juice.
Beat on high for 10 minutes or until you have stiff peaks.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spoon over crumb mixture.
Freeze for 6 hours.
Cut into squares and serve. Excellent!!
Yields 12 servings.

title: peach fluff salad
directions: Open crushed pineapple and juice to pour into boiler.
Add both boxes of jello and bring to a boil. Cool it.
Fold in buttermilk and Cool Whip. Place in refrigerator.
Chill and serve.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs; add oil, sugar and zucchini.
Add dry ingredients, then vanilla and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Mix together and press into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cafe cappuccino(dry mix)
directions: Combine instant coffee, sugar, dry milk, dried orange peel, and baking soda.
Mix well.
Store in an air tight container.
Makes about 2 cups of dry mix (about 32 - 1 cup servings).

title: mary jane puffs
directions: Heat water and butter to boiling point.
Stir in flour.
Stir constantly until mixture leaves the pan and form into a ball (about 1 minute).
Beat in eggs, 1 at a time, until smooth and velvety.
Drop from spoon onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 50 minutes, until dry.
Let cool.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Cut rhubarb into pieces.
Mix sugar, flour and salt.
Add well beaten eggs and rhubarb.
Pour into a 9-inch pie crust.
Cover with crumbs or crust.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: onion-cheese supper bread
directions: Cook onion in small amount of fat until tender but not brown. Combine egg and milk, add to biscuit mix, stir only until mix is just moistened.
Add onion, 1/2 the cheese and parsley.
Spread into a greased 8 x 1 1/2-inch round cake pan.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese, drizzle melted butter over top.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: green beans with mushrooms
directions: Wash beans, trim ends and remove strings.
Snap if desired or leave whole.
Arrange beans in a steaming rack above boiling water.
Cover and cook 10 to 12 minutes.
Meanwhile, melt margarine and add garlic and mushrooms.
Cook until mushrooms are tender, stirring constantly.
Add beans and remaining ingredients to mushrooms.
Cook 3 minutes more.

title: chuck's peanut butter fudge
directions: Butter 8 x 8-inch glass dish, set aside.
Mix sugar, milk and salt together.
Cook over medium heat to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add vanilla, butter and peanut butter.
Beat fudge until it stiffens and loses its glaze.
Quickly pour into glass dish.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: milky way bar crumble bars
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Remove from heat and stir in flour, oats, sugar, salt, soda and vanilla.
Blend until crumbly.
Press 2/3 of the mixture into a greased 8-inch pan.
Arrange bar slices in pan, about 1/4 inch from the rim.
Finely crumble the remaining mixture over the sliced bars.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until edges are golden brown.
Cool in pan.
Cut into bars.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cook peppers for 3 minutes, then stuff.
Cook meat, onions and garlic.
Add seasoning and soup; simmer for 10 minutes.
Add cheese and rice.
Bake for about 30 minutes.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Cover and chill overnight.
To reduce calories, use Sweet 'N Low.

title: "ceviche-acapulquito style"
directions: Place the fish in a shallow container.
Pour the lime juice over the fish; cover and refrigerate the mixture for about 2 hours, stirring occasionally until the fish is opaque.
Just before serving the ceviche, stir in the vegetables and the cilantro.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
With a slotted spoon heap the ceviche onto the crisp tortillas and serve.

title: cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage and onion in food processor.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until well blended.
Add more mayonnaise if needed.

title: fruit pizza(make up the night before.)
directions: Cut cookies in 1/8-inch slices and place in 14-inch lightly greased pizza pan.
Bake at 375° until done, but not crisp.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Spread over crust after the crust has cooled.
Place listed fruits on top (or any other combination of fruit).

title: kisses
directions: Beat egg whites until frothy.
Add sugar and beat until stiff. Add corn flakes, coconut and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonful on well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: sweet and sour green beans
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; remove from pan and crumble.
Add sugar and vinegar to the drippings.
Drain the beans; slice and separate onions in rings in a Crisco-greased casserole.
Place a layer of beans, almonds, bacon and onion rings; continue layering until all are used.
Pour prepared dripping mixture over all.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mash potato casserole
directions: Bake the potatoes until tender. Remove pulp and reserve in bowl.
Saute in 1 stick butter the leek and Prosciutto or ham. Cook 5 minutes. Add the spinach and Parmesan cheese.
Mash potatoes with the 1/2 stick butter, sour cream and hot milk.
Add leeks mixture, salt and pepper.
Bake in buttered casserole, covered, for 30 minutes and uncovered for 30 minutes. Top with the Jarlsburg cheese before baking at 350°.

title: carrot bars
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs.
Beat.
Sift dry ingredients and add to first mixture.
Add carrots.
(Mixture will be very runny.) Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a 12 x 16-inch jelly roll pan.

title: egg and sausage casserole(night before breakfast)
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Layer bread cubes, sausage and cheese.
Pour mixture of egg, milk, salt and dry mustard over all. Put in refrigerator until morning.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, covered, with foil.
Slit foil several times on top.
Serves approximately 15.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions.
While macaroni is cooking, combine all other ingredients and mix well.
Drain macaroni and pour into flour mixture.
Then pour into casserole dish and top with grated cheese.
Bake at 450° until done.

title: easy oven omelet
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs.
Add milk.
Add bacon, ham or mushrooms.
Stir in cheese and onion.
Pour into greased or sprayed 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch dish or 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, for 40 to 45 minutes or until omelet is set and top is golden brown.
Makes 4 servings.

title: old fashioned applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Then add eggs.
Add apples and flour mixed with soda, cinnamon and cloves.
Reserve a little flour to mix with nuts and raisins and add last.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: italian pasta sauce
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add onion and pepper.
Saute until tender.
Add all other ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer, adding water if necessary, for 3 hours. Serve with crusty bread and salad.

title: anise slices(biscotti)
directions: Into large bowl, measure 1 1/2 cups flour and remaining ingredients.
With a mixer at low speed, beat ingredients until just mixed.
Increase speed to medium and beat 3 minutes, occasionally scraping bowl.
With spoon, stir in remaining 1 cup flour.
Wrap dough in plastic wrap and refrigerate until firm. Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a large cookie sheet.
Divide dough in half.
On floured surface, shape each half into 10 x 3-inch loaf.
Place loaves 2-inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake 20 minutes.
Remove cookie sheet from oven.
With sharp knife, immediately slice each loaf into 1/2 to 3/4-inch slices.
Turn down slices on same cookie sheet making sure they don't touch. Return to oven and bake 5 minutes longer or until lightly golden. Cool on wire rack.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen biscotti.

title: potato salad
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix potatoes and 3 tablespoons of vinaigrette in large baking dish.
Roast for 20 minutes.
Reduce to 375° and roast until tender, stirring occasionally, about 50 minutes total.
Transfer to a large bowl and cool slightly.
Mix in 3 tablespoons vinaigrette and 1/3 cup Blue cheese.
Season to taste.
Cook green beans in boiling salted water until crisp-tender.
Drain.
Rinse under cold water.
Drain well.
Mix with 3 tablespoons of cheese, 2 tablespoons vinaigrette and walnuts.
Combine with potatoes.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Serves 4.

title: sis's "lots of beans"
directions: In a large pan, add beans; do not drain juices.
Add remaining ingredients to beans.
Bake at 325°, uncovered, for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: aunt stinky's cheesecake
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients until creamy and smooth.
Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Pour into a graham cracker crust in a spring-form pan.
(Use recipe on graham cracker crumb box; use 1 1/2 recipes.) Bake at 500° for 10 minutes, then reduce to 250° and bake for 1 hour.
Turn off heat. Open door; cool in oven for 3 hours.
Do not move or touch.
When completely cooled, remove from oven, remove side from pan and leave on bottom to serve.
May be topped with glaze.

title: mom's cheesecake
directions: Beat sugar and cream cheese together.
Whip whipping cream in separate bowl.
Add whipped cream to sugar and cheese mixture. Pour and fold in jello.
Pour in graham cracker crust in 9 x 9-inch pan.
Chill and serve.

title: creamy chicken tetrazzini
directions: Saute green pepper, mushrooms and onion in butter in a Dutch oven until tender.
Add flour and next 4 ingredients; stir until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually stir in half and half, cook until thickened, stirring gently.
Add 1/4 cup Cheddar cheese, stirring until cheese melts.
Add shredded chicken, mushroom soup, 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese, sherry and pimiento; stir well.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put chicken in a 2-quart baking dish (greased).
Cover with vegetables.
Combine soup, broth and pepper.
Pour over chicken. Combine flour, milk and butter and pour over mixture.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: date and nut bread
directions: Cover dates with boiling water; add the butter and let cool. Add brown sugar.
Stir together flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Combine egg, date mixture and flour.
Mix vanilla and walnuts into mixture.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Mix above ingredients and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
This is a very moist, easy-to-make cake. It generally tastes better the day after it's made.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Layer
in
casserole
dish in order:
chicken (chopped) and soup.
Mix milk, onion and egg together; pour over chopped chicken.
Add
Pepperidge
Farm
dressing mix. Pour broth over casserole.
Bake
at 350° for 1 hour or until firm and lightly brown.

title: zucchini jam
directions: Cook zucchini for 12 to 15 minutes until clear; stirring constantly. Add sugar, pineapple, and lemon juice. Boil 6 minutes more. Take off of stove and add Jello. Pour into jelly jars and seal. You do not have to process.

title: easy french onion soup
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender.
Add chicken broth and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer 1 hour.
Spoon into soup bowls.
Top each bowl with croutons and cheese.
Serve immediately.
Serves 6.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Put one layer of each of the ingredients.
Top with ripe olives, tomatoes, green onions and Cheddar cheese.

title: apple pie filling
directions: Mix cornstarch, nutmeg, cinnamon, sugar and salt with water and cook until thick. Add lemon juice. Peel and slice apples and pack into jars. Do not pack tight. Cook in hot water bath. Cook quarts for 20 minutes and pints for 15 minutes. Makes 7 quarts.

title: granny's strawberry pie
directions: Bake
a
9-inch pie shell until brown.	Let cool.
Wash and slice
strawberries.
Place in cool pie shell.
In saucepan,
mix water, sugar and cornstarch.
Cook over medium heat while stirring.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low and cook until mixture
is
clear.
Then add strawberry gelatin.
Pour over strawberries
in
pie
shell.
Chill.
Add	whipped cream when ready to serve.
Makes 1 pie.

title: hamburger cabbage
directions: Brown hamburger meat.
While browning, put onion and garlic in and let them get tender.
Steam the cabbage.
Drain meat and cabbage.
Mix together.
Put a tablespoon of water, salt, pepper and salt to taste.
(Cornbread is good with it.)

title: guacamole
directions: Peel avocado and remove pit.
Blend all but last four ingredients in blender or food processor until smooth.
Spread on plate and chill.
Just before serving, top with diced tomatoes, diced onions, diced olives and grated Mozzarella cheese.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 325°
for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Cool and add Buttermilk Sauce.

title: lazy cake
directions: Mix first ingredients.
Heat baking dish with the 1/2 stick oleo.
Pour batter in melted oleo.
Add fruit pie filling on top. We especially like the cherry pie filling.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° (do not overbake).

title: drop sand tarts
directions: Mix well.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° until edges start to turn brown.
May sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar and put a nut on top, if desired.

title: easy fruit icebox pie
directions: Slice 2 bananas in each pie crust.
Mix cream cheese and sugar.
Beat with mixer until smooth.
Add 2 cups Cool Whip. Divide in half and pour over bananas.
Open pie filling and put 1/2 can on each pie.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Chill 2 hours and serve.

title: pumpkin dip
directions: In a small bowl beat cream cheese and sugar until well blended.
Add pumpkin, syrup and cinnamon; beat until smooth. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Serve as a dip with animal crackers and assorted cut up fruit.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake at 325° or 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until brown.

title: salvation army donuts - world war 1
directions: Beat eggs lightly. Add sugar and melted butter.
Add the sifted dry ingredients with milk.
Knead and shape. Cut with donut cutter. Drop into hot shortening and fry until brown. Drain on brown paper bags.

title: fresh pack kosher dill pickles
directions: Wash pickles well, especially around blossom end.
Soak overnight in enough brine to cover.
Next day, drain and pack pickles into quart jars, putting in 2 tablespoons of mustard seed, 2 cloves of garlic, 3 heads of dill or 1 tablespoon of dill seed per quart.
Mix 1 1/2 quarts vinegar, 3/4 cup salt, 1/4 cup sugar, 2 1/4 quarts water and 2 tablespoons mixed pickling spice in cloth bag.
Bring to boil and pour over pickles in jars.
Seal and process in boiling hot water for 20 minutes.
Have water boiling and start timing when you put jars in.

title: oreo cookie ice cream cake
directions: Combine and spread on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan; freeze 20 minutes.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Toss together coconut, chocolate chips and pecans.
Place in pie shell.
Mix sugars, salt and margarine. Beat in corn syrup and vanilla.
Gently fold eggs into sugar mixture.
Pour evenly over ingredients in pie shell.
Bake 55 to 65 minutes or until deep golden brown on top and nearly set in the center.
Cool at room temperature.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add to rest of ingredients.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 325° in 2 greased and floured loaf pans.

title: peanut butter muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease twelve 2 1/2 x 1 1/4-inch muffin pan cups.
In medium bowl, with spoon, mix milk, peanut butter and egg until smooth.
Add baking mix and sugar, with spoon beat vigorously 30 seconds.
Fill each muffin pan cup two-thirds full. Bake 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Immediately remove muffins from pan.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Bake at 350° covered for 30 minutes.
Remove cover and cook another 30 minutes.

title: peach cake
directions: Mix all together and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.
This is very rich.
Don't need icing unless you prefer it.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Dust chicken pieces with flour, paprika and salt and pepper. Put single layer, skin side down, in baking dish.
Dribble melted butter over chicken.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 minutes; turn chicken and bake 20 minutes longer.
Stir 3 cans Campbell's cream of mushroom soup with water until smooth.
Pour over chicken and bake 20 minutes longer or until tender.
Serves 10 generously.

title: piper's no-crust pumpkin pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, butter, milk, pumpkin, biscuit mix and cinnamon in blender.
Cover and blend at low speed for 3 minutes. Pour into a greased 9-inch pie plate or quiche pan.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Bake on a cookie sheet for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle top with granola and continue to bake for another 20 minutes or until center feels firm.
Cool on wire rack.
Serve with vanilla ice cream.

title: marinated carrot pennies
directions: Boil carrots until tender.
Combine soup, sugar, oil, vinegar, mustard, and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer sauce uncovered for 20 minutes.
In medium-size casserole layer the following:
carrots, onions, pepper, and sauce.
Repeat layers once more, ending with the sauce.
Refrigerate overnight.
May reheat to serve or may be served chilled.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Prepare broccoli per package directions; drain.
Mix in remaining ingredients except Rice Krispies. Pour in buttered casserole.
Add 2 cups crushed Rice Krispies, mixed with 1 tablespoon melted butter.
Add to top of broccoli dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sauerkraut, pork and dumplings
directions: Place
sauerkraut,
pork
and
water in large saucepan. Bake in 300° oven 6 to 8 hours.	As pork and sauerkraut brown, turn over and add water, if necessary, several times.
Remove pork
and keep
warm
while	dumplings
cook.
Place pan with sauerkraut on stove.
Add 3/4 cup water and bring to boil.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Mix together peanut butter, butter and brown sugar.
Then add the vanilla and powdered sugar.
Press into a cookie sheet. Sprinkle chocolate chips over top.
Then bake at 350° for 5 minutes.
Immediately take out of oven.
Take a knife and spread melted chocolate chips over top as icing.
Chill.

title: nacho chili dip
directions: Heat chili and Velveeta in slow cooker.
Keep hot to serve. Dip nachos in chili.
Enjoy!

title: italian-style swiss steak
directions: Preheat broiler.
Broil beef on rack 4-inches from heat 2 minutes on each side. Set aside.
In a large nonstick skillet, heat oil. Add mushrooms, onion, carrots and celery.
Cook over medium heat until onion is translucent, about 2 minutes. Stir in tomato sauce, wine, oregano, garlic powder, pepper, salt and 1 cup water.
Return meat to skillet. Cover and simmer over low heat 1 hour. Add green pepper and potatoes.
Simmer until meat is tender, about 35 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni al dente according to package directions.
Mix mayonnaise, mustard, salt, pepper, marjoram and thyme together in a small bowl.
In large bowl, combine macaroni, celery, onion, peas, cheese and dressing. Mix thoroughly and chill in refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours.

title: july cooler
directions: Dissolve sugar in water; cool.
Stir in lemonade, crushed bananas, orange juice and pineapple juice.
Now freeze.
Spoon mixture into glasses until half full, then fill the glass to top with uncola.
Serves 50.

title: party nibblers
directions: Mix pretzels, nuts and cereal in large (12 x 8-inch) baking dish.
Melt butter on High (maximum power) 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir in seasonings and Worcestershire.
Drizzle over cereal; mix thoroughly.
Cook on High (maximum power) 5 to 6 minutes, stirring after 3 minutes or until evenly toasted.
Cool and store in airtight container.
(Total cooking time:
6 1/2 to 7 1/2 minutes.)
Makes 2 1/2 quarts.

title: swedish potato salad
directions: Place potatoes in a bowl.
Blend vinegar, oil, salt and pepper in a small bowl and pour over potatoes.
Chill several hours. Spoon potatoes into a salad bowl and sprinkle onion and parsley in the center of the potatoes.
Spoon beets in a ring around the onions and parsley.
Toss just before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: lettuce and cauliflower layered salad
directions: Layer lettuce, cauliflower, bacon and onion, then sprinkle cheese on top.
Mix Miracle Whip with the sugar and dollop on top. Set overnight or several hours in refrigerator.
Garnish with tomatoes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Tear cauliflower into tiny pieces.
Dice celery, carrots and green pepper.
Stir the mayonnaise, sour cream, dip and cheese. Mix together.
Pour over vegetables and mix.
Chill and serve.

title: hawaiian salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: frosted coconut pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour in unbaked shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Mix only one pie at a time.

title: pimiento dip
directions: Dice vegetables and process.
Process the two cheeses until fluffy.
Add juice and Worcestershire sauce to cheese.
Pulse in pimiento (drained), pepper and onion.
Serve in a red or green pepper with raw vegetables and crackers.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Combine first five ingredients.
Pour into baked pie shell. Top with whipped topping.
Refrigerate.

title: company casserole
directions: Melt butter or margarine, stir in flour and cook over low heat until bubbly.
Add broth and milk.
Bring to boil.
Cook for one minute, stirring constantly.
Add sherry, green onion dip mix, salt and pepper.
Place noodles in 2-quart buttered casserole. Add chicken and mushrooms.
Pour sauce over the top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes, covered.
Remove cover, sprinkle with cheese and dot with remaining butter or margarine.
Bake 10 more minutes to melt cheese.

title: one pan noodle stroganoff
directions: Cook beef, onion and garlic until meat is browned.
Drain off fat.
Drain mushrooms, reserving liquid.
Add liquid, broth, lemon juice, salt and pepper to skillet.
Stir in uncooked noodles. Cover and simmer 12-15 minutes or until noodles are tender.
Stir in sour cream and mushrooms.
Cook and stir until heated through but do not boil.
Top with snipped parsley.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Line the bottom of a loaf pan with wax paper and butter it. Sift flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
In a large bowl, cream the butter, sugar and orange rind.
Beat in egg until blended.
Add flour mixture in 3 additions, alternating with orange juice, mixing each time.
Fold in cranberries and walnuts. Turn into loaf pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° until cake tester comes out clean, about 55 minutes.
Cool on wire rack. Wrap and store for flavors to blend.

title: chuck wagon beans
directions: Brown the meat and onion in a skillet; drain off fat.
Place meat in a crock-pot and add beans, sugar, vinegar, catsup and salt. Cook on low for 4 to 5 hours, stirring occasionally.
Add bacon to top of dish before it is served.

title: loose cabbage rolls
directions: Saute first 4 ingredients until meat is brown.
Remove from heat.
Add rice.
Salt and pepper heavily.
Layer sliced cabbage and meat mixture in a 2-quart casserole.
Pour V-8 juice over top. Cover and cook in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: dr. bird cake
directions: Sift together first 4 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix until well blended.
Pour into an 8 inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cake will crack slightly on top.

title: scalloped cabbage
directions: Cook the pieces of cabbage in boiling salt water for 5 to 7 minutes.
Drain the water from cabbage.
In buttered baking dish, layer cabbage and white sauce.
Put bread crumbs on top and dot with butter.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 400° until crumbs are brown.
Serves 6.

title: dana's fruit punch
directions: Mix juices according to directions, adding the amount of water called for; use more or less sugar, according to taste.

title: chinese cole slaw
directions: Break Ramen noodles apart, being careful not to grind them. Brown them in butter until crisp.
Set aside.
Brown onions, sunflower seeds and almonds in skillet with butter.
Set aside.

title: grandma iris' waffles
directions: Mix all ingredients together with mixer.
Makes approximately 4 large waffles.

title: hot mexican spinach dip
directions: Cook spinach.
Reserve 1/2 cup liquid, then drain spinach. Add to spinach the oleo, flour and onion; stir.
Add remaining ingredients.
Serve hot with corn chips or crackers.

title: apple-zucchini bread
directions: Mix eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla.
Add zucchini, apples, flour, seasonings and nuts.
Bake in two greased pans at 375° for 1 hour.

title: sourdough starter
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and store at room temperature 3 days.
Stir 2 times daily.
Ready when thick, white and bubbly.

title: stretch chicken
directions: Make Stove Top stuffing.
Pour into baking dish.
Add spices. Cover with chicken or mix together.
Pour can of soup, plus can of water, over all.
Poke holes in dressing.
Heat through in microwave or oven at 350°, until hot.

title: marshmallow treats
directions: Insert toothpicks in marshmallows and freeze.
Melt caramels, condensed milk and margarine in pan.
Dip marshmallows in caramel and roll in Rice Krispies.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Sugar Cookie Crust:
Bake and cool on a cookie pan.

title: louisiana caper butter
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender or food processor. Process until well blended.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Arrange apple slices evenly in pastry shell.
Combine cinnamon and 1/2 cup sugar.
Stir well, and sprinkle mixture over apples. Combine flour and remaining sugar, stir well.
Cut margarine into flour mixture with a pastry blender (I use my fingers, works well) until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Yields one 9-inch pie.

title: spiced whole wheat muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.

Spray muffin pan with vegetable spray. Mix all-purpose flour, whole wheat flour, cinnamon, ginger, allspice, baking powder, salt, raisins and pecans in large bowl. Beat eggs, molasses, milk and butter together in separate bowl. Mix liquids into dry ingredients just until blended with a few swift strokes.
Dough will be slightly lumpy, do not overmix.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full and bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mexican macaroni salad
directions: Cook
macaroni using package directions; drain.
Place Velveeta cheese in glass dish.
Microwave on Medium until melted. Add cheese, olives, undrained beans and green onions to macaroni in large bowl; mix well.
Chill for 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts for 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Then break breast pieces into bowl. Add cream of chicken and sour cream. Pour into casserole dish. Break crackers over top. Put a little butter over crackers. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients; place in 13x9 glass casserole. Refrigerate overnight or 8 hours. Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
This can be frozen.

title: country style barbecued ribs
directions: Place ribs in a large saucepan or Dutch oven. Cook ribs, covered in water,
until ribs are tender, 45 to 60 minutes. Drain well.
Set aside.

title: mexican grits
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients until thick; remove from heat and add cheese, then add remaining ingredients.
Mix well; pour into greased 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine flours, oats and baking soda.
Set aside.
In large bowl, beat butter with an electric mixer (medium speed) for 30 seconds.
Add sugar;
beat until fluffy.
Add eggs, milk, vanilla and lemon juice.
Beat well.
Stir in zucchini.
Add flour mixture gradually while beating on low speed until combined.
Stir in walnuts.
Spread in greased ring mold or 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan. Bake in 350° oven, 55 to 60 minutes or until a wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cover with foil the last 10 minutes of baking.
Cool completely for easy slicing.
Makes approximately 12 servings.

title: roasted pecan clusters
directions: Melt butter in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jellyroll pan.
Spread pecans evenly in the pan.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.
Melt bark squares in top of a double boiler or the microwave.
Remove from heat and stir until smooth.
Cool 2 minutes.
Add pecans and stir until well coated.
Drop by rounded teaspoons onto waxed paper.
Cool completely.
Yields 3 1/2 dozen.

title: granny's white icing
directions: Cook flour and milk until thick, stirring constantly.
Set aside to cool, covered.
When flour and milk mixture is cool, put all ingredients in mixer.
Beat to consistency of whipped cream. Enough for a 2 layer cake or a tube cake.

title: pickle relish
directions: To each quart of sliced cucumbers, add 1 onion and salt; let stand 3 hours.
Add the remaining ingredients, except turmeric; heat through.
Add the turmeric.
Pack into pint jars.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix soups and broth.
Add chicken, vegetables and potatoes. Pour into 2 crusted deep dish pie pans.
Cover with biscuits or top crust.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pineapple cake delight
directions: Bake cake in 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Cool.
Make the vanilla instant pudding.
Spread pudding on top of cooled cake.
Pour can of pineapple (drained) over top of pudding.
Spread Cool Whip over layer of pineapple.
Sprinkle top with crushed walnuts.

title: chicken kirkpatrick
directions: Saute onion, pepper and celery in oil.
Add gravy mixture. Add mushrooms, tomatoes, cheese and chicken.
Layer mixture with spaghetti in an 8 x 8-inch Pyrex dish sprayed with Pam.
Bake, covered, at 400° for 25 minutes or until bubbly.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco; add eggs and beat well.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture gradually.
Add fruit cocktail and nuts, mixing well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with coconut and brown sugar.
Bake at 300° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: fudge
directions: At low heat, melt chocolate chips and combine with milk, salt and vanilla.
Remove from heat and mix in peanut butter chips. Spread evenly in pan lined with foil.
Refrigerate for 2 hours. Remove foil and cut.

title: dill dip
directions: Blend and chill at least 1 hour.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place the pan in oven to melt butter.
Stir together flour, milk and sugar in a mixing bowl.
Pour the batter into warm pan.
Spoon applesauce evenly over the batter and cover with apple slices.

title: caramel bars
directions: Mix cake mix, egg and butter or oleo together.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour on top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes, when cold, cut in bars.

title: hash brown bake
directions: Mix all ingredients except bread crumbs and melted butter. Place in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with bread crumbs and melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cream pie
directions: Boil milk in saucepan.
Combine sugar, flour, salt and egg yolks; add to milk and stir until thickened.
Remove from heat. Add vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: gingerbread house construction
directions: Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until frothy.
Add confectioners sugar slowly.
Beat until it forms stiff peaks and will hold a sharp line when a knife is drawn through it.
Keep bowl covered with a damp cloth or towel.
Be certain that your bowl and beaters are free of oils!

title: french prime rib
directions: Place rib roast in a large bowl.
Combine olive oil and Worcestershire sauce; rub this mixture thoroughly into roast.
Mix all herbs and spices together; place on a large piece of waxed paper.
Roll the roast in the seasonings until covered.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours, or until meat thermometer reaches 160° for medium.
Remove from oven, cover with foil and let stand for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with Parmesan Potatoes.

title: old timey tea cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients; roll out cookies and bake at 400° until brown.

title: imperial chicken
directions: Note:
You can use seasoned bread crumbs and 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese and eliminate other spices.

title: yummy crunchies
directions: Melt butter; add sugar and heat to boiling.
Cook for exactly 3 minutes.
Pour over single layer of saltines in a large shallow greased baking pan.
Bake for 15 minutes in preheated oven.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with semi-sweet morsels.
Wait 5 minutes or until morsels have melted; spread melted chocolate evenly.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: cranberry layer salad
directions: Mix cranberry sauce with 1 cup hot water until smooth consistency.
Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup hot water (stirring until well mixed).
Add Jell-O and 1 cup chopped nuts to cranberry sauce.
Pour 1/2 of this mixture in a square baking dish and place in freezer until firm set.
Spread sour cream over chilled portion.
Top with second half of cranberry sauce mixture (spoon on).
Refrigerate.
(You may make this a day ahead of need.)

title: cheese and sesame chicken
directions: Soak the chicken in milk.
Roll in cracker crumbs and place in a baking dish.
Sprinkle with sesame seed.
Sprinkle with paprika and garlic powder to taste.
Drizzle with margarine.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, until tender and the juices run clear.
Uncover for the last 5 to 10 minutes to give a crusty topping.

title: buttermilk pie *
directions: Beat ingredients just enough to mix.
Bake in unbaked pastry shell in 325° oven until golden brown and pie is set in center.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter, peanut butter, sugar, egg, and vanilla thoroughly. Sift together dry ingredients. Blend into creamed mixture. Shape into 1 inch balls, roll in granulated sugar. Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets. Criss cross with fork tines. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Cool slightly before removing from sheet. Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown onion and beef in drippings.
Add remaining ingredients. Cook slowly for 2 hours.
Serves 8.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Toast or caramelize almonds (cook almonds and sugar over low heat stirring constantly until sugar melts and coats almonds). Pour almonds onto waxed paper to cook, break into pieces before adding to salad.
You can use cashews instead of almonds and then you don't have to coat them with sugar.
Toss lettuce, spinach, celery, onions and parsley together; refrigerate.
Just before serving, add oranges and nuts.
Toss lightly with dressing. Serves 8.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender.
Drain and mash.
Add butter and cheese.
Add eggs, milk and crackers.
Mix well. Season to taste. Put in 2-quart casserole. Top with buttered cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook and then puree broccoli in a food processor.
Saute onion and celery in margarine until transparent. Blend in flour until smooth.
Add broth.
Cook, stirring until slightly thickened. Stir in broccoli, half and half, milk and salt.
Heat thoroughly. I usually double the recipe! I also mix cornstarch and water and add to soup at the end because I like it thicker!

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Drain pineapple well and reserve juice.
Soak raisins in juice (for best results, soak overnight).
Drain yams; mash yams until all lumps are removed.
Mix raisins, yams and pineapple thoroughly and put mixture into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover with marshmallows, standing on edge to form a complete covering so none of mixture is visible.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 20 to 30 minutes or until marshmallows are golden brown.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: coconut milk
directions: Blend until very smooth.
Strain well or use on cereal unstrained.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter. Gradually beat in sugar until light and fluffy, about 5 to 7 minutes. Add eggs, one at

a time, beating well after each addition. Combine flour, baking soda and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with the sour cream and vanilla. Beat on low just until blended. Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch fluted tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes or until cake tests done. Cool in pan for 15 minutes before removing to a wire rack to cool completely.

title: smothered chicken
directions: Brown chicken in oven.
After browning, pour on celery soup, mixed with 1/2 cup of water.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° until tender.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate easter nests
directions: Melt both chocolate bars in a double boiler.
When melted, stir in chocolate and corn flakes.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper and shape into nests.
Put a few tiny jelly beans in the center of each nest.
Makes about 20 nests.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Cook ground beef; drain.
Add taco seasoning as directed on package.
Crush chips and line bottom of baking dish.
Cover chips with ground beef.
In large bowl, mix Ro-Tel, corn (drained), chili beans and sour cream.
Pour mixture over ground beef.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted, about 20 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients until thick (medium heat).
Remove from stove and add jello and food coloring.
Let cool.
Fill cooled cooked crust with berries and pour mixture over. Refrigerate 3 hours. Top with Cool Whip.

title: juicy meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Turn into greased shallow baking pan.
With wet hands, shape into loaf.
Dot top with 1 tablespoon of shortening.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until brown. Serves 4.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Drain shrimp and add to all other diced ingredients with mayonnaise until a nice dip consistency forms.
Serve with crackers and small rye bread.
Double for a large recipe.

title: chicken pot pie #1
directions: Cook onion in margarine until tender, but not browned.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk, water and bouillon cube. Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in chicken and vegetables.
Heat until bubbly.
Pour into two 4 x 4-inch individual casserole dishes.

title: yogurt pancakes
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Beat milk and eggs together.
Stir into dry ingredients.
Stir in yogurt.
Pour into hot skillet until set.
Top with fruit and syrups of choice.

title: cracked cookies
directions: Cream shortening and white sugar.
Add brown sugar.
Add one egg and beat until mixture is fluffy.
Add dry ingredients and vanilla.
Chill.
Roll balls of dough the size of small walnuts. Dip in sugar and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: classic green bean casserole
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, combine soup, milk, soy sauce and pepper.
Stir in beans and 1/2 can of onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Stir.
Top with remaining onions.
Bake 5 more minutes.

title: quick meal for two
directions: Spray a large frying pan with oil and about 2 tablespoons butter.
Sprinkle on bottom of pan salt, pepper and thyme. Sprinkle lightly each of the following layers of:
leftover meat, onion, potato and 1 or more kinds of vegetables.
Pour over can of V-8 or tomato sauce.
Bring to a boil; lower the flame.
Cover with lid and cook for about 10 minutes.
A salad goes well with the meal.

title: meal in a skillet
directions: Cook beef in skillet until it changes colors (almost done). Drain beef.
Add onions, celery and garlic clove.
Stir well while cooking for 15 minutes.
Add English peas, Spanish rice, salt and pepper to meat.
Cook 10 more minutes.
Dip up into serving plates and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese on top while meat is hot.

title: english pea salad
directions: You will need an oblong glass dish.

title: cream cheese icing
directions: Mix well and spoon onto the cake.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix in order given and pack in greased baking dish.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: chocolate chip pizza
directions: Mix sugar, brown sugar, butter, peanut butter, vanilla flavoring, egg, flour and marshmallows together until not lumpy. Flatten out like pizza crust.
Place chocolate chips and pecans on top.
Place in stove at about 350°.
When the crust looks burnt, take out.
Make sure the chocolate chips are melted. Let cool and put coconut on top if desired.

title: easy baked chicken
directions: Clean and wash chicken. Pat dry with paper towels.
Spray entire chicken with Pam cooking spray. Sprinkle on generous amount of Lawry's seasoning to entire chicken.
Place a baking rack in a shallow pan and put chicken on, breast side down. Bake at 400° for 1
1/2 hours.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before slicing.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Make a brine with 1 cup vinegar, 2 teaspoons salt, 2 cups sugar and 1 tablespoon celery seed.
Do not heat.
When sugar is dissolved, add celery seed and salt and pour over sliced cucumbers and onions.
Store in refrigerator in covered container.
Let stand 24 hours before using.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: In a casserole place first 5 ingredients.
Add onion rings on top.
Bake at 305° for 2 hours.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions.
Bake in a greased 15 x 11-inch jelly roll pan for 15 minutes at 350°.
Combine pudding mix with cold milk.
Beat in cream cheese.
Fold in by hand the defrosted frozen topping.
Spread this pudding mixture onto the cake.
Drain the pineapple and sprinkle it over the pudding.
Top with cherries, coconut and nuts.
Keep in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: spiced tea
directions: Combine all ingredients and store in tightly covered container.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown onion, garlic and meat in oil.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, sugar, salt and oregano; simmer for 1 hour.

title: city chicken
directions: Divide veal cubes and place on 6 skewers.
Combine crumbs and seasonings.
Dip veal into beaten egg which has been combined with milk.
Roll in crumb mixture.
Heat oil in skillet and brown veal slowly in hot fat.
Dissolve bouillon cube in hot water; pour over meat in skillet.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Complete cooking by baking for 1 hour, covered, in a 350° oven.
Serves 6.

title: pico de gallo
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate. Keeps for several days.

title: hamburger hash
directions: Brown ground chuck and onion.
Combine first 8 ingredients in a 3-quart casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Sprinkle noodles over top of casserole and bake 10 to 15 more minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: kung pao wings
directions: Cut chicken wings into 3 sections. Discard wing tip section. Set the wings aside.

title: corn pudding
directions: To corn, add salt, pepper, sugar, melted margarine, and flour. Add beaten eggs and milk, stirring well.
Pour into greased 9-inch square baking dish and bake at 350° approximately 35 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: never fail rolls
directions: Mash potatoes.
Stir in shortening while potatoes are still hot; beat well.
Add milk and salt, then beat in yeast and 1 cup of flour; let stand until foamy.
Add well beaten eggs and remaining flour; beat dough until elastic and easy to handle. Knead until smooth.
Let stand in warm place until double in bulk. Make into rolls; let rise until light.
Bake in moderate oven (375°).

title: spider cake
directions: Prepare cake mix and bake in two 8-inch pans, following package directions.
When cakes have been removed from pans, let stand on cooling racks at least 2 hours to firm up for easier frosting. Empty container of frosting into medium-sized bowl.
Beat with electric mixer until smooth.
Gradually beat in black food color, 1/4 teaspoon at a time, until icing is almost black (color darkens upon standing).
Place cake on serving plate.
Spread frosting between layers and on top and sides of cake, smoothing out the sharp edge and rounding top slightly.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Prepare cake per package directions; bake in 9 x 13-inch pan. When cool, cut cake in small squares.
Place half in bottom of punch bowl.
Prepare pudding per package.
Pour half of pudding over cake; layer half of pineapple next, then half of cherry pie filling and half of Cool Whip.
Repeat the layers one more time. Keep refrigerated.
Serves a large number of people.

title: cucumber soup
directions: Peel the cucumbers, cut them lengthwise into quarters, scrape out the seeds and cut cucumbers into cubes.
Trim the roots of the scallions and cut them into 1/4-inch thick slices, including about 1-inch of the green part.
Simmer the cucumbers and scallions in the chicken consomme until the vegetables are tender.
Add the A. 1. sauce and whirl in the blender.
Adjust seasonings.
Pour into the plates and sprinkle the chives on top.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix powdered sugar and peanut butter until crumbly.
Cook pudding until it bubbles.
Cool in refrigerator.
Sprinkle half of peanut butter mixture in pie shell.
Add layer of pudding (all). Add thick layer of Cool Whip.
Sprinkle remaining peanut butter mixture on top.

title: carrot cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease a loaf pan.
Combine all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Pour into loaf pan and bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix very well together all ingredients, except barbecue sauce and Cheddar cheese.
Make a loaf, put in oiled baking pan.
Pour about 1/2 cup barbecue sauce on top, sprinkle with shredded Cheddar cheese on top of sauce.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
They'll all want seconds.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown ground meat, green pepper and onion.
Add stewed tomatoes, sugar and rice.
Cook on low 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Bring to a boil soups, water and chicken. Add rice. Set off heat; add pepper to taste. Stir and let stand 15 minutes or until thick.

title: pineapple cheese mold
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add cream cheese, beaten with milk. Mix pineapple, mayonnaise, celery and nuts, pour in mold and chill.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Shred lettuce in oblong pan.
Layer remaining vegetables (celery, onions, etc.).
Spread carefully mayonnaise on top. Sprinkle 1 tablespoon sugar on top of mayo, then Romano cheese and Salad Supreme. Refrigerate 24 hours.
Toss before serving.

title: best oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat butter and sugar until fluffy. Beat in egg and vanilla.
Combine flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg and add to mixture; mix well.
Stir in oats.

title: hot shrimp toast
directions: Grind together to a paste with finest blade of meat grinder or blend in blender first three ingredients.
Add salt, sugar and beaten egg.
Spread mixture on thin sliced white bread.
Sprinkle lightly with fine dry bread crumbs.
Cut each slice in 4 triangles.
Heat 1-inch of oil in skillet; fry triangles, shrimp side down first, then brown other side.
Drain on paper towels. Freeze.
When ready to serve, defrost and reheat in 400° oven for 5 minutes.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Make up stuffing according to directions on box.
Spread each chicken breast with stuffing and roll up.
Secure with toothpick, if needed.
Using ice cream scoop, make stuffing balls of remaining stuffing.
Place in flat roasting pan (or Corning Ware large frypan).
Mix soup with milk.
Spoon over chicken and stuffing.
Bake in 350° oven until fork-tender, about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: seven layer salad
directions: 1st layer:
Tear up head of lettuce; place in large bowl.

title: fruit-biscuit breakfast
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease 6 1/2-cup ring mold or 12-cup fluted tube pan.
In large bowl, combine fruit.
Add 2 tablespoons orange juice and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Gently stir to coat; refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain artichokes and chop them in 1/8-inch pieces.
(I like to put the artichokes in the food processor and chop them up!)
Add 1 cup of mayo and 1 cup of cheese.
Mix together.
Pour into baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until bubbling. Sprinkle Parmesan over the top and cook 10 additional minutes. Serve with Wheat Thins.

title: spiced apple syrup
directions: In a small saucepan, combine juice, cloves, cinnamon stick and water.
Heat to boiling.
Simmer 5 minutes or until syrup measures 3/4 cup.
Makes 6 servings.

title: zucchini squash bake
directions: Cut zucchini in half and remove all seeds.
Fill with mixture. Put in pan and bake 1 hour at 400°.

title: easy fried chicken
directions: Skin chicken.
Sprinkle desired amount
of seasoning on each piece.
Dip in buttermilk; dredge in flour.
Put into hot oil (deep enough to cover
chicken
pieces.) Fry approximately 15 minutes on each side.
May also fry pork chops this way.

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Cream margarine well and add next 6 ingredients.
Mix well and add last 3 ingredients.
Mix all well and drop by teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with greased bottom of glass dipped in sugar.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Do not make this batter in advance.
Bake at once.
Light and crisp.

title: hamburger barbecue
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer together for 1 hour.

title: chili dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and put into crock-pot.
Cook on low setting for 3 hours.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and sift 3 times.
With large spoon, cream shortening and mix sugar evenly.
Add eggs and beat until airy; stir in applesauce lightly.
Add flour mixture in three stages, beating thoroughly each time.
Add raisins, being careful not to let them bunch at bottom.
Empty into greased square pan (about 8-inch square) and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cake attains best flavor if not eaten for a day or so.
Wax paper or tight bread box will keep it moist.

title: quick herbed zucchini
directions: Slice the zucchini in 1/4-inch slices.
In a heavy skillet, saute the zucchini in heated butter for 3 minutes, turning once. Remove from the pan and set aside.
In the same pan, saute the onions until soft, but not browned.
Combine the zucchini with the onions.
Add the salt and herbs.
Heat slowly over low heat.
Add the cream, if used.
Heat but do not boil.
Arrange on a serving platter, garnish with parsley.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chocolate pecan cluster
directions: Combine peanut butter and both chips in heavy saucepan.
Place over low heat; cook, stirring constantly, until melted. Stir in peanuts. Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Chill until firm. Store in a covered container in refrigerator.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Beat egg yolk, flour and sugar together well.
Add vinegar, water and butter.
Stir over medium heat until thick.
Flavor with lemon flavoring and pour into a baked pie crust.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix the 6 dry ingredients well.
Add pumpkin, stirring well. Add eggs and milk, stir well and fill 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes until custard and crust are well baked.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken and celery.
To mayonnaise, add the remaining ingredients and blend.
Pour mixture over chicken and chill.

title: chicken cheesy broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until slightly tender.
Drain well.
Add poultry seasoning to enough water to cook chicken.
Simmer, covered, until tender, about 25 minutes.
Drain well.

title: one bowl chocolate fudge
directions: Microwave chocolate and milk in 1 1/2-quart microwavable bowl on High for 1 minute.
Stir until chocolate is melted and smooth. Stir in vanilla, salt and walnuts.
Spread into greased 9 x 5-inch pan.
Refrigerate 30 minutes or until firm.
Cut into squares. Makes about 2 dozen squares.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook
cabbage
in
boiling
salted
water until tender. Drain and chop.
In buttered baking dish (9 x 13-inch), layer 1/2
of cabbage, 1/2 of soup and 6 slices of cheese.
Repeat, ending
with cheese.
Toss
cracker
crumbs
with
butter and spread
over the top.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Simmer all together for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve on toasted, buttered hamburger buns.

title: pecan pralines
directions: In large, heavy saucepan, combine the sugar, soda, buttermilk and salt.
Cook over high heat for 5 minutes or to 210° on candy thermometer, stirring frequently and scraping bottom of pan.
Add butter and pecan halves; continue cooking, stirring constantly, scraping bottom and sides of pan until candy reaches a soft ball stage (234°), about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and cool slightly.
Beat until thick.
Drop from tablespoon onto wax paper and let cool.

title: all-purpose marinade
directions: Marinate beef, pork, poultry, fish or vegetables.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Prepare pie crusts following package directions for 2-crust pie. Mix soup, mixed vegetables, chicken, milk, thyme and pepper. Pour into pastry-lined pie plate. Top with second crust. Fold top crust under bottom crust. Flute edge. Brush crust with egg if desired. Cut slits in top crust. Bake at 375 degrees for 40 minutes until golden brown. Cool 10 minutes.

title: lemon delight
directions: Grease pan lightly.
Mix pudding as per package directions. Cool.
Mix oleo, flour and 1/4 cup of nuts and press in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in oven 15 minutes or
until lightly browned at 350°.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
Cool and cut in small squares.
Mix Jell-O, sugar, cornstarch and water.
Cook on medium heat until mixture begins to thicken.
Remove from stove and add strawberries.
Cool.
Mix vanilla pudding by directions and stir in Cool Whip.

title: lee's chicken casserole
directions: Mix together and bake for 45 minutes.
May garnish with fried onions.

title: colorful pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta in boiling, salted water until just tender, following package directions; drain.
Mix yogurt, lemon juice, sugar and a pinch of salt together.
Whip cream until stiff and stir into yogurt mixture.
Combine cheese, walnuts, fruits, pasta and yogurt mixture in bowl.
Separate endive into leaves, then tear into pieces.
Arrange endive pieces on 4 salad plates.
Spoon pasta salad on top and serve.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix the first four ingredients well.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Form into balls and press flat with sugar-bottomed glass.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: mexican rice
directions: Fry rice in 1 tablespoon shortening until brown.
Remove and fry ground meat, onion, garlic, salt, chili powder and tomatoes. Combine meat, rice and water in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: polish paluszki
directions: Using first 4 ingredients, make dough as for pie crust.
Heat until lukewarm milk, dissolve 2 yeast cakes in lukewarm milk.
Add eggs to milk and yeast mixture.
Add dry ingredients to milk mixture and mix with hands only until it holds together.
Shape into roll, cover with waxed paper and chill 6 hours or overnight. Roll out on granulated sugar by pieces (thin).
