Cut in squares, spread apricot filling (solo) in middle and flip 2 corners over it.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 375° on cookie sheet.

title: sugar-free hot spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large jar to store.
Mix to taste with hot water in your favorite mug.
You can also add some sugar-free lemonade mix to the dry ingredients.

title: easy 7-layer dip
directions: Layer the ingredients on a serving dish.
Chill and serve with nachos.

title: hal's cheese cake
directions: Beat with electric mixer and pour into spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 25
to 40 minutes.
Cool.
Serve with sour cream and fresh fruit topping.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix the flour, butter and pecans and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, then cool.
Mix 1 cup Cool Whip, powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Spread over baked crust. Mix pudding and milk until thickened and spread over cream cheese layer.
Top with Cool Whip and chill for 2 to 3 hours.
Keep refrigerated.

title: chicken and mushroom casserole
directions: Mix together rice, water, celery, onions and mushrooms.
Add chicken.
Top with butter.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour and 15 minutes in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Cook, rinse and drain macaroni.
Add shrimp, eggs, onion, green pepper, salt, pepper and salad dressing.
Chill and serve on lettuce.

title: pecan rolls
directions: Combine first three ingredients.
Mix well with hands.
Shape mixture into 5 (4 x 1-inch) rolls.
Mixture will be very dry. Chill 2 or 3 hours.
Combine caramels and water in top of a double boiler; cook until melted.
Dip rolls in melted caramels and roll each in pecans; chill 1 hour.
Cut into slices to serve.
Yield: 5 rolls.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together.
Bring to a boil in medium saucepan, stirring occasionally.
Cook for 2 1/2 minutes. Remove from the heat.
Add oatmeal, nuts and flavoring; mix well. Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Let set until cool.

title: chocolate yeast cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening until fluffy.
Add 3 egg yolks and yeast which has been dissolved in water.
Sift flour, soda and salt 3 times.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Set aside.
Add flour, milk and vanilla alternately to creamed mixture.
Add raisins or nuts.
Fold in egg whites.
Cover with cloth or Saran Wrap and let stand 6 hours or overnight.
Bake in tube pan 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Can be frosted or dust 10x sugar.

title: chili con queso dip (with meat)
directions: Melt cheese in double boiler or microwave.
When melted add tomatoes and soup.
Saute onions, garlic, and bell pepper.
Add ground meat and sausage and brown.
Drain well.

title: salad dressing(for cabbage)
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1/2 cup water.
Bring to a boil vinegar, sugar and 1/4 cup water.
Add gelatin, salt, celery salt and pepper.
Cool and add 1 cup salad oil.
Store in refrigerator; shake dressing at times to keep mixed until set.
Keeps for months in refrigerator.

title: caramel chocolate gumbo bars
directions: Press 1/2 cake mixture in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 8 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle 6 to 8 ounces chocolate chips. Pour caramel over chocolate chips.
Drop remaining cake mixture by spoonfuls on top.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes.

title: hello dollies
directions: Layer the pan in order of the list.
Preheat oven to 350°. Cook for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: charmain chill shrimp dip
directions: Just mix all the ingredients, except shrimp, then add the shrimp.
The flavors develop more if done ahead of time.
Enjoy!

title: garlic chicken breast
directions: Combine oleo, chopped chives and garlic powder.
Spread, freeze and cut into strips and place inside chicken.
Coat with cereal after you put butter inside and secure with toothpicks. Bake in a 425° oven for 35 minutes uncovered.

title: moist chocolate cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together and set aside.
In saucepan bring oleo, oil and water to boil.
Remove from stove and add buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients to liquid part. Beat all ingredients well.
Pour into greased and floured pan (17 1/2 x 11 1/2 x 1-inch).
Bake in oven at 400° for 20 minutes. While cake is baking mix frosting.

title: turkey wild rice soup
directions: Rinse rice and drain.
In medium saucepan, combine rice, oil and water; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Meanwhile, in a large kettle, cook onion, celery and carrot in butter until vegetables are almost tender.
Blend in flour; cook and stir 2 minutes.
Add broth and undrained rice. Bring to a boil; cook and stir until slightly thickened.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 20 minutes.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine cornstarch and sugar.
Blend in peach puree, water and lemon juice.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil until thickened and clear.
Remove from heat and set aside to cool.
Beat together cream cheese and powdered sugar until smooth.
Spread cream cheese mixture evenly in bottom of pie shell.
Spoon peaches on top.
Pour cooled puree mix over all. Chill before serving.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown meat; add onions and cook until tender but not brown. Add peas, soups, sour cream, pimiento, salt and pepper.
Mix well. Cook and drain noodles.
Stir into mixture.
Pour into 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle crumbs over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes to 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: pizza casserole(serves 6 to 8 people)
directions: Cook noodles.
Brown meat, onion and mushrooms until meat is cooked.
Drain off fat.
Mix pizza sauce and seasonings with meat. Add noodles and mix well.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch greased baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
(Extremely easy to make and kids love it!)

title: christmas holly cookies
directions: Melt butter and marshmallows.
Add vanilla and color; mix well.
Add cornflakes; mix well until coated.
Drop by spoonful onto wax paper.
Work quickly!
Decorate with "red hot" candy pieces to look like holly.

title: geneva's cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in a well-greased iron skillet.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes, or until brown.

title: chocolate filled bonbons
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cream the Crisco, sugar, brown sugar, vanilla and egg in a large bowl on medium speed.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Press 2 level teaspoonfuls of dough around each chocolate Kiss, covering completely.
Place pecan half on top.
Place on ungreased baking sheet. Bake 6 to 7 minutes.
(Don't overbake; they will not brown.)
Gently press pecans into cookies.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: dump cake
directions: In large glass 9 x 13-inch cake pan, place the entire can of pineapple; spread evenly.
Spread cherry pie filling over pineapple.
Sprinkle cake mix evenly over pineapple and cherries. Dot with butter.
Sprinkle nuts over top.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Cool before serving.

title: apricot jello
directions: Dissolve jello with boiling water.
Add apricot baby food and mix well with Cool Whip.
Place in refrigerator until set and very cold.
Before serving, spread Cool Whip on top.
Can also be served by layering jello (after jello is set), fresh peaches and Cool Whip in a brandy snifter.

title: crisp waffles
directions: Heat waffle iron.
Beat eggs with hand beater until fluffy; beat in remaining ingredients just until smooth.
Pour about 1/2 cup of batter onto center of hot waffle iron.
Bake until steaming stops, about 5 minutes.
Remove waffle.
Serve with butter, jelly or syrup.

title: sancocho
directions: *Can be found in the tropical produce section of supermarkets.

title: cheesy pork chops and potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spoon cheese spread into 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Place in oven just until cheese melts, 5 minutes.

title: beer butt chicken
directions: For dry rub: Mix together the sugar, salt, pepper, cajun seasoning and black pepper.

title: stir crazy crunch
directions: Place popped popcorn into a large, buttered, heatproof bowl. In a 2-quart saucepan, combine sugars, syrup, water, vinegar, butter and salt.
Using candy thermometer, cook the syrup to 290° on medium heat, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat and add peanuts.
Pour over popcorn, tossing corn to coat well.
Spread mixture into buttered 9 x 13 x 2-inch dish.
When cool, break into pieces.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Pour uncooked rice in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour in chicken broth.
Arrange chicken on top of rice.
Mix soups, poppy seed, onion and sour cream; pour on top of chicken.

title: hot crab spread
directions: Blend sour cream with cream cheese.
Stir in melted butter, cornstarch, onion, salt and vermouth.
Gently fold in crab and Cheddar, reserving 1/4 cup Cheddar for topping.
Spread mixture in ungreased baking dish; top with remaining cheese and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.
Garnish with parsley.

title: monster cookies
directions: Combine sugars and butter.
Beat in eggs, syrup, vanilla and soda.
Add peanut butter, oats, chips and nuts.
Drop on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Allow to cool slightly on pan, then remove.
May have to add a few more oats if dough is not stiff enough.
This takes a very large pan to mix these in.
Makes around 200 cookies.

title: stuffed baked potatoes with horseradish cream
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Pierce potatoes several times with fork. Place on oven rack and bake until crisp outside and cooked inside, about 1 hour.
Transfer to baking sheet and cool for 5 minutes. Cut off top 1/3 of the potatoes.
Scoop potato from bottom 2/3 into large bowl, leaving 1/4-inch thick shell.
Scoop potatoes from top 1/3 and add to the same bowl.
Discard tops.
Mash potatoes with 6 tablespoons sour cream, butter and 2 tablespoons horseradish. Season with salt and pepper.
Spoon into potato shells, dividing equally.
Mix 1/2 cup sour cream, 2 tablespoons horseradish and dill in small bowl.
Cover and chill.

title: carrot-pineapple bread
directions: Cream together oil, sugar and eggs. Add crushed pineapple. Mix together flour, cinnamon, baking soda and salt. Add to pineapple mixture. Next add shredded carrots and nuts. Bake in 2 large or 4 small loaf pans in 325° oven for about 50 minutes.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: nut sponge cake(torte)
directions: Beat 7 yolks 10 minutes.
Add 1 1/2 cups sugar and beat 5 minutes.
Meanwhile, sift cake flour, baking powder and salt.
Add dry ingredients, alternately to egg yolks with water.
Add vanilla and chopped nuts.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into batter.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes in 2 (10-inch) round pans, greased and floured.
Cool cake in inverted pans.
When cool, slice each layer in half and spread with Sweet Butter Custard Frosting.

title: hot buttered rum
directions: Set ingredients out until soft and mix together.
Put 1 to 2 tablespoons in
a
cup with hot milk or water with a shot of rum. We like
it best with hot milk.
Keeps good frozen or will keep in a	refrigerator
for
a
long
time.
One	batch usually last us all winter.

title: hershey's kisses cookies
directions: Make in balls and roll in sugar.
Bake at 370° for 10 minutes. Put candy on top and bake for 3 more minutes.

title: apricot glazed meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients, except preserves.
Put in a loaf pan. Spread preserves on top only.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: vermicelli with asparagus
directions: Cook asparagus in boiling water for 2 minutes; drain, then refresh under running cold water.
Melt butter in large skillet. Add asparagus, garlic, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and pepper; saute while stirring for a minute or two.
Toss with hot, cooked spaghetti.
Serve with grated Parmesan.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Add broccoli, onions and bacon. Mix mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar together. Pour over vegetable mixture and refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.

title: fresh salsa
directions: Blend garlic with lemon and lime juice in a blender. Chop other veggies and mix. Store in glass jars in refrigerator. Mixture will keep up to two weeks, but I usually share with a friend.
Makes 2 1/2 quarts.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and top with the crumbs.
Bake in ovenproof dish at 350° until bubbly.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, milk, butter and cocoa in saucepan over high heat, stirring constantly.
Boil 3 minutes. Remove from heat. Add salt, vanilla, oats and peanut butter; stir well.

title: beef and tater bake
directions: Combine meat, bread crumbs, egg, onion, ketchup, salt and pepper. Pat into an 8-inch square baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and drain excess fat.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Brown meat and onion;
add salt, tomato sauce and olives.
Put layer of crumbled tortilla chips on bottom of greased 9 x 12-inch pan, then layer of meat mixture.

title: muffuletta(sandwich)
directions: Combine mixed vegetables and olives in a small bowl.
Heat oil in small saucepan over medium-low heat.
Add garlic and oregano; cook 2 minutes.
Do not brown.
Halve bread horizontally and pull out a little bread from each half.
Brush inside of bottom half with oil mixture.
Top with half of vegetables.
Add ham and turkey; top with remaining vegetables.
Cover with top half of bread.
Wrap with Saran Wrap and refrigerate for at least 2 hours or overnight.
Cut in wedges to serve.
Can be made a day ahead and tightly wrapped and refrigerated.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Follow directions for high altitude on cake mix.
In a large mixing bowl mix pina colada mix, 1/2 cup rum, oil and eggs.
Blend well.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Fold in coconut.
Pour into well-greased and floured 2 x 9 x 13-inch pan.
Shake out excess flour.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes in pan.
Then invert to cool on rack.
Soften sherbet.
Blend in 1/2 cup rum.
Fold in pineapple and freeze.
Serve atop cake slices.

title: shrimp bisque
directions: Place celery, potatoes, water, salt and pepper in multi-cooker.
Set heat control at 250° and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to 212°.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Blend milk and flour.
Stir in potato mixture.
Add shrimp, butter and zucchini.
Simmer, stirring, until thickened and bubbly.

title: chocolate covered cherry cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, stir together the flour, cocoa, baking powder, soda and salt; set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, beat margarine for 30 seconds.
Add sugar; beat on low speed until fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla; beat well on medium speed. Gradually add flour mixture to beaten mixture, beating on low speed until well blended.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls; place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press down center of each cookie with thumb.
Drain cherries; reserve juice.
Press a cherry into the center of each cookie.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.
Cool completely.
Add frosting.

title: fudge brownie muffins
directions: Place butter and cocoa in a 2-cup glass measuring cup. Microwave at High for 1 minute or until butter melts.
Set aside.

title: date and walnut delight
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Add sugar and cream together well.
Add nuts, dates and cracker crumbs, then add beaten egg whites.
Bake in slow oven 30 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve with whipped cream.

title: gingerbread cake
directions: In large bowl, blend soup and eggs.
Add gingerbread mix. Blend at low speed until moistened; beat 2 minutes on medium speed. Fold in raisins and walnuts.
Pour into well-greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until cake is done. Serve warm or cool.

title: grandma's old fashioned macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni until done (don't overcook) and drain.
Place half of macaroni in a buttered casserole dish (margarine is okay). Place Cheddar cheese slices all over top of macaroni.
Place remaining macaroni over cheese and also top that layer with cheese slices (approximately 1/8-inch slices or grated is okay but use plenty of cheese).
Beat egg with fork slightly; add about 1 cup milk and stir.
Pour mixture over macaroni and cheese.
Then pour more milk until it just covers all the macaroni and cheese.
The secret is to bake, uncovered, until all milk is absorbed.
It usually takes 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Cheese should be crispy on top.

title: barbecue spareribs
directions: Place ribs in baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over ribs.
Bake in 325° oven for 2 hours.

title: fruit salad
directions: Make a simple syrup from sugar and water by heating until it dissolves.
Let cool, then pour over mixture of fruit and nuts. Chill.

title: peach cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together first.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Stir
together good.
Pour in tube pan.
Bake at 350° for
hour and 20 minutes.
Cool awhile before removing from pan.
Good with a cream cheese icing.

title: split pea soup
directions: Put all ingredients in a large pot. Bring to boiling point slowly.
Stir often.
Then cover and simmer about 3 hours.

title: custard pie
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a good boil, scald and add vanilla.
Beat eggs; add milk mixture.
Pour into unbaked pie crust and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Pour instant pudding mix over Cool Whip and stir to blend. Add thawed strawberries and marshmallows.

title: pickled turnips
directions: Peel turnips; cut crosswise in thin slices not more than 1/4 inch thick.
Mix with salt and let stand 1 hour.
Drain and rinse thoroughly with water.
Bring remaining ingredients to a boil. Add turnips and simmer 2 minutes.
Cool well.
Makes 8 servings.

title: easy one dish ham bake
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix broccoli, soups, 1 cup milk, the ham and onion powder in ungreased rectangular baking dish, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Mix Bisquick and milk.
Pour evenly over soup mixture. Bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: karo sweet and sour pork
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve juice.
Heat corn oil over medium heat.
Add next 3 ingredients.
Stir-fry 2 minutes or until tender crisp; remove.
Stir-fry pork, 1/2 at a time, for 3 minutes. Return pork to skillet.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix together
all
dry
ingredients.
Then
blend
oil, eggs, water and
pumpkin.
Add to dry ingredients; blend well. Grease and flour 4 one-pound coffee cans or 2 large loaf pans. Fill 1/2 full.
Bake at
for 1 hour or until done.
Cool in pans slightly; take out and let cool.
Wrap in foil and put in refrigerator.
Will
keep
about
weeks.
Can
also
be frozen.

title: cheese muffins
directions: Mix together.
Grease muffin pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: In mixing bowl, combine sausage with cheese.
Mix until well blended. Add biscuit mix and blend thoroughly. Shape mixture into 1-inch balls.
Place 1-inch apart on baking sheet. Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes until nicely browned. Serve hot.

title: angel cake dessert(diabetic)
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup hot water.
Let set in refrigerator until it starts to thicken slightly.
Add strawberries which have been thawed and crushed.
Add the yogurt.
Place cake shell in a loaf pan; alternate strawberry mixture and cake.
End with cake. Cover and place in the refrigerator until set.
Slice and serve.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Cook bacon or sausage; drain.
Separate crescent rolls; place on ungreased 12-inch pizza pan.
Press over bottom and up sides to form a crust seal.
Spoon meat over crust.
Sprinkle hash browns on top.
Spread Cheddar over hash browns.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Sift together the next 5 ingredients and add to first mixture.
Add nuts and raisins. Grease and flour 2 loaf pans or 3 small pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spam bake
directions: Prepare dinner as directed. Add Spam and green pepper. Place in 10 x 6-inch baking dish. Combine milk and egg; pour over dinner mixture. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute celery, butter and onion.
Mix together and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix sugar, flour and pineapple juice.
Add cheese and pineapple.
Mix well.
Pour into 1-quart casserole dish, greased. Mix cracker crumbs and margarine; sprinkle over pineapple.
Bake at 300° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: strawberry preserves
directions: Boil strawberries.
Leave in water 2 minutes.
Put through colander and drain, not perfectly dry.
Add 4 cups sugar; boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add 2 cups sugar and boil for 5 minutes.
Pour in a shallow pan (bread pan works best) and let stand overnight, stirring occasionally.

title: favorite beef dish
directions: Mix all together.
Simmer until well blended.
It's easy and good.

title: pecan pie
directions: Prepare pastry and roll out to fit pie plate.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: In a large bowl, place sugar, flour, pumpkin, oil, eggs, salt, cinnamon, baking powder and soda; beat for 3 minutes.
Bake in greased and floured 13 x 9 inch pan for 45 minutes in a 325 degree oven.

title: chocolate pudding cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In ovensafe casserole dish, melt margarine.
In separate bowl, mix flour and 1 cup sugar.
Add milk and blend well.
Pour into melted margarine.
Do not stir.
Mix cocoa, 1 cup sugar and water in a small bowl.
Pour into batter. Do not stir.
Bake at 350° until done, approximately 35 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook hamburger meat, onion and bacon until almost done.
Add the drained tomatoes, brown sugar, dark corn syrup and the pork and beans.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for about 3 hours.

title: mom's vegetable casserole
directions: Mix the water chestnuts, cheese, soup and mayonnaise together well and add the cooked vegetables.
Put in baking dish.
Sprinkle crackers over casserole.
Drizzle melted butter over casserole. Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix the cake mix, 2 eggs and the softened butter well.
Spread into the bottom of a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: no-sugar filled cookies
directions: Blend cream cheese, sour cream and shortening.
Add flour and salt; mix well.
Set in refrigerator until firm (about 30 minutes).
Roll out half of the dough on cookie sheet; spread on filling evenly (recipe below).
Place other half of dough on top. Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes or until top is brown.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onions in boiling water, covered, 10 minutes or until tender.
Drain, mash and add butter, eggs, milk, seasoning and sugar.
Blend well.
Place in casserole dish; top with cheese and crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: eclair cake
directions: Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with whole crackers.
Mix pudding according to directions on box.
Blend Cool Whip into pudding mix.
Pour half of mixture over first layer of crackers, then add second layer of crackers.
Pour remaining pudding mixture over crackers, then add third layer of crackers and frost with chocolate frosting.
Best if made 1 day ahead.
Keep covered tightly and refrigerate.

title: low-fat chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken until tender in 3 quarts of water and put in refrigerator overnight.

title: four-hour bread
directions: Pour potato water, hot, over flour and sugar.
Add potatoes and cool.
Add yeast.
Make sponge.
Beat 5 minutes, then let rise and add lard and salt.
Stiffen up and knead at least 20 minutes. Let rise and knead down.
Let rise again.
Make into loaves or light cakes.
Let rise and bake.

title: easy pork fried rice
directions: Heat 1/2 tablespoon oil over medium heat in large skillet or wok.
Add eggs; cook without stirring until set.
Invert skillet over baking sheet to remove cooked eggs; cut into 1 1/2 x 1/2-inch strips and set aside.

title: browned rice
directions: Melt oleo in large iron skillet (that has a lid) over low heat.
Add rice.
Cook, stirring frequently until rice is yellow. Dissolve bouillon cubes and salt in boiling water.
Slowly add rice.
Simmer with cover for 25 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: chicken liver casserole
directions: Sprinkle livers with salt and pepper; shake in small amount of flour in paper bag.
Brown in margarine in hot skillet.
Saute onion and rice in remaining butter in skillet until lightly browned.
Add chicken broth; stir well and pour in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Place livers over top of rice.
Cover with tinfoil and bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.

title: gold oven cake
directions: Mix butter and Crisco.
Add sugar, one cup at a time.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift in flour.
Add milk; alternate with flour.
Put in flavor.
Pour into tube pan.
Place in cold oven; turn to 350°.
Do not open oven until after 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain beans real good.
Add ingredients together in glass casserole dish.
Save 1 1/2 cups of cheese and place it on top. Bake in 350° oven in an uncovered dish for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let it cool 5 to 10 minutes before eating.

title: hot chicken salad(microwave)
directions: Place cubed chicken in a 10-inch casserole. Combine celery, green pepper and onion in a 2-cup glass measure. Cover with plastic wrap. Microwave at HIGH 2 to 3 minutes or until tender-crisp. Drain, if necessary.

title: imperial crab
directions: Combine all ingredients, except 1 tablespoon beaten egg. Toss gently. Place in a 1-quart casserole that has been lightly lined with mayonnaise. Combine saved egg with 1 tablespoon of mayonnaise. Pour over mixture and sprinkle with paprika. Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes. Serves 4.

title: baked chicken
directions: Brush chicken with mayonnaise.
Shake on bread crumbs.
Bake on broiler pan rack at 425° for 40 to 45 minutes or until golden brown and tender.

title: easy pineapple zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla until thick.
Stir in remaining ingredients and blend well.
Pour into 2 greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple pie
directions: Peel apples and cut in small cubes.
In a deep pan, pour water and mix in tapioca, stirring over low-medium heat until it is completely dissolved.
Add brown sugar, apple pie spice and lemon juice; stir.
Then add apples and cook for 5 to 10 minutes.
The apples have to be still a little hard.

title: microwave divinity
directions: Mix all ingredients, except egg whites, in a large Pyrex glass bowl and microwave 20 minutes.
While syrup mixture is cooking beat egg whites.
When syrup is ready, pour slowly, while beating, over egg whites.
Beat until starting to set up.
Add vanilla. Drop by spoonfuls on tinfoil or waxed paper.

title: curried chicken salad
directions: Cover and chill up to 8 hours.

title: hawaiian banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar, oil, crushed pineapple, bananas, vanilla, soda, baking powder, flour and pecans.
Bake in two loaf pans for 55 to 60 minutes. Makes two loaves.

title: beef and bean chili
directions: Combine ground beef and onion in a Dutch oven.
Cook over medium heat, stirring to crumble until beef is browned and onion is translucent; drain.
Add tomatoes and next 3 ingredients; stir well.
Bring to a boil; cover and reduce heat.
Simmer 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add beans; simmer 10 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Remove from heat; ladle into serving bowls. Top with shredded Cheddar cheese; serve with crackers.

title: crab imperial
directions: Make sauce.
Save
out 3 tablespoons sauce mix, stir in 12 ounce can crab
meat.
Put	in 1 quart casserole.
Top with "saved out" sauce.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°. Serves 4 to 6.

title: green beans with bacon
directions: In a covered saucepan, cook beans in a small amount of water for 20 to 25 minutes or until tender.
Drain.
Meanwhile, in a skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon; reserve drippings. Crumble bacon and set aside.
Add beans to drippings; sprinkle with pepper and seasoned salt.
Heat through.
Add crumbled bacon and toss.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: banana salad
directions: Mix
salt,
mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Fold in pineapple, cherries
and
nuts.
Whip	cream
until thick and shiny. Fold in cheese and bananas, along with cream.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Line bottom of pie pan with 1 can crescent rolls.
Brown meat and drain excess fat.
Add soup and onions.
Pour into pie plate. Cover with cheese.
Top with 2nd can crescent rolls.
Brush with beaten egg.
Bake in oven at 400° for 20 minutes.
Cover with aluminum foil to prevent overbrowning and bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: 24 hour cole slaw
directions: Heat vinegar, sugar, oil, salt, celery seed and mustard to boiling.
Pour over cabbage and onion, mixing well.
Place in airtight container and store in refrigerator.
Best eaten the next day.

title: asparagus vegetable casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch casserole dish and layer in order as named. Dredge bread in melted butter and place on top.
Bake at 350° until bread is crisp, approximately 20 minutes.

title: chocolate heath bar cake
directions: Crack two heath bars in small pieces and place in cake batter. Follow instructions on cake mix. Warm the chocolate fudge sauce and mix with eagle brand milk. Set aside. Poke holes in cake and pour mixture over it. Crack 3 heath bars and mix with cool whip. Spread on cooled cake. Sprinkle remaining heath bars on top. Refrigerate over night before serving.

title: 100 year old black walnut cake
directions: Cut cold butter into pieces and quickly cream.
Add sugar and cream well with butter.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Sift flour and baking powder together.
Add alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Stir in flavoring and nuts.
Turn batter into tube pan that has been sprayed with a nonstick cooking spray or well buttered.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until cake tests done.

title: hurry tuna curry
directions: Cook onion, green pepper and garlic in 2 tablespoons butter until tender but not brown.
Stir in sour cream, curry powder, salt and pepper.
Break tuna into bite size pieces; add to mixture.
Heat slowly, stirring often.
Serve over rice.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Combine cornstarch, salt, brown sugar, vinegar and pineapple juice; cook until thick.
Add chicken, green pepper, pineapple chunks and onion.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Serve over hot rice.

title: cranberry pineapple delight
directions: Dissolve jello in water. Add pineapple, cranberries and nuts. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch container. Chill until firm.
Serves 10.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brush bottom and sides of crust evenly with egg yolk.
Bake on baking sheet until light brown, about 5 minutes.
Remove crust from oven.
Combine 3 egg yolks, pumpkin, sugar, salt and spices.
Gradually add evaporated milk.
Mix well. Pour into crust. Bake on baking sheet for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and continue baking for 45 minutes or until knife inserted near center of pie comes out clean. Cool before serving.
Garnish, if desired.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Place uncooked broccoli on bottom of casserole dish.
Mix mushroom soup, water, onion soup and rice; pour over broccoli. Lay chicken pieces over top.
Cover and bake at 325° for 2 hours or more.

title: easy punch
directions: Mix all
ingredients
as
is, except for ginger ale and sherbet.
Add ginger ale just before serving and float sherbet on top as needed.
May add ice.

title: beefy jalapeno cornbread
directions: Combine cornmeal, milk, eggs, salt, soda, bacon drippings and corn in a mixing bowl.
Blend well and set aside.
Saute ground beef until lightly browned, drain thoroughly and set aside.
Pour half of cornmeal batter into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle with cheese, crumble beef over cheese and sprinkle with onions and peppers.
Pour remaining cornmeal batter over top. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine sugar, eggs and oil; beat until light and fluffy. Stir in pumpkin.
Combine dry ingredients; stir into pumpkin mixture.
Add water, raisins and nuts; blend well.
Spoon batter into a well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 65 to 75 minutes.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: crunchy ice cream squares
directions: Remove ice cream from freezer to soften as you prepare the crunchy base for the dessert.
Combine the cereal, brown sugar, nuts, butter or margarine and coconut.
Mix and blend well.
Press half the crunchy mixture into the bottom of a 9-inch square cake pan.
Pat down firmly.
Spread ice cream evenly over the top. Sprinkle with remaining crunchy mixture to cover.
Cover airtight. Freeze until firm, about 1 hour.
When ready to serve, remove from freezer.
Cut into squares.
Top each square with a fresh strawberry, if desired.

title: beef stuffed shells
directions: Cook shells 12 minutes.
Drain and rinse.
Saute in oil, onions, garlic and mushrooms.
Mix in beef, egg, bread crumbs, cheeses, oregano, salt and pepper.
Stuff shells with meat mixture.
Arrange shells in large deep baking pan that has been covered with 3 to 4 cups of spaghetti or tomato sauce.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Baste with sauce and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese before serving.

title: venison meat loaf
directions: Use 1/2 can tomatoes and mix all ingredients together.
Form into a loaf.
Put in a cake pan or glass baking dish and cover with remaining 1/2 can of tomatoes.
Cover with tinfoil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Check halfway through to be sure meat is not burning.
Add some water to pan if getting too dry.

title: cherry sweet bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Sprinkle 1 cup over dates and cherries.
Cream sugar, butter and eggs; blend until light and fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients.
Add fruit and nuts last.
Bake in two buttered loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Put first 3 ingredients in large bowl and mix well.
Let stand overnight.
Drain and rinse in cold water; drain again.
Put in large kettle with remaining ingredients.
Cook, stirring occasionally, 30 minutes or until desired consistency.
Pour into 6 or 8 hot pint jars and seal.
Process 5 minutes.

title: cauliflower casserole
directions: Saute mushrooms, bell pepper and onion in butter.
Add flour and stir until smooth.
Gradually add milk.
Add cheese and bake at 350°.

title: low-fat pound cake
directions: Combine applesauce and sugar; beat until blended.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Mix milk, water and vanilla.
Alternately add flour mix and milk mix to applesauce and sugar mix.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour into lightly greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: codfish casserole
directions: Day before:
Soak salted cod in water for 24 hours.
Make sure to change water 3 or 4 times.

title: pulled mints
directions: Boil until hard ball forms in water.
Pour into greased platter.
Put 8 drops of peppermint on top.
Let stand until cool enough to pull.
Pull until stiff.
Make into rope and cut into small pieces.

title: madeline's coffee cake
directions: In a bowl, cream the butter and sugar.
Add the eggs, sour cream and vanilla, beating until well blended.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and soda together.
Add gradually to creamed mixture, beating after each addition.
Mix walnuts with sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Butter a 10-inch tube pan.
Turn 1/2 of the batter into pan.
Sprinkle walnut and sugar mixture on top.
Add rest of batter and cover the top with nut mixture. Bake in moderate oven for 45 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix grated Cheddar cheese and cream cheese together.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Make into balls.
Roll into parsley flakes and chopped pecans.
Makes 2 balls.

title: mulled citrus tea
directions: In medium saucepan, combine water, cinnamon sticks, cloves and allspice; heat until very hot.
Remove from heat.
Add tea bags; cover.
Steep tea for 5 minutes; remove tea bags, cinnamon sticks and cloves.
Add orange juice, lemon juice and honey; mix well. Heat tea thoroughly.
In small bowl, combine lemon peel and sugar; sprinkle on tea.
Makes six 1-cup servings.

title: old fashioned bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place bread in a buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Next, blend together cream, egg yolks, sugar, salt, vanilla, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add preserves and raisins. Beat well and pour over the bread.
Stir gently with a fork until the ingredients are well blended.
Place dish in a pan containing 1-inch of hot water and bake for 45 minutes or until almost set in the center.
Serve with Hard Sauce.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles until tender and drain.
Combine noodles, drained tuna, mayonnaise, vegetables and salt.
Blend soup and milk; heat thoroughly.
Add cheese; heat and stir until cheese is melted. Add to noodle mixture.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Bake in hot oven at 400° for 20 minutes.
Serve with tossed salad.

title: hillbilly cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand. Pour into a hot iron skillet. Bake at 450° for about 25 minutes.

title: gram's chocolate pie
directions: Put milk in saucepan.
Add other ingredients one at a time, ending with flour.
Cook over medium heat until thick.
When cooked, add butter and vanilla.
Pour into prepared pie crusts. Makes two pies.
Top with coconut or egg whites.

title: white chocolate cheesecake
directions: Melt chocolate squares as directed on package.
Prepare Jell-O cheesecake as directed on package, stirring white chocolate into filling mixture before spreading in crust.
Garnish with white chocolate shavings.

title: sweet and sour pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to directions on package.
Mix sugar, pepper, salt, garlic salt, vinegar and mustard together in small saucepan.
Cook over low heat until mixed and sugar is melted.
It is not necessary to boil this.

title: can opener enchiladas
directions: In
a
nonmetal
bowl, combine soup, corn, green onions and chili
powder.
Microwave,
uncovered,
on High for 4 minutes, stirring
once.
Stir
in
chicken, sour cream and milk. Slit package that holds tortillas.
Cook on High for 1 minute, until tortillas
are softened.
Spread about 1 1/4 cups of the chicken mixture in a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch nonmetal baking dish. Spread 1/4 cup
of the chicken mixture on each tortilla.
Top with about 1 tablespoon of the cheese and roll up.
Place seam side down,
in the
mixture in the baking dish.
Cook, uncovered, for
to
8 minutes,
until heated through.
Top with remaining cheese
and microwave
for
2 minutes more or until cheese melts.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Boil squash; drain and mash.
Add sugar, milk, cornstarch and egg yolks.
Cook over slow heat, stirring constantly until real thick.
Remove from heat; add flavorings and oleo.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Add meringue.
Bake at 375° until stiff.

title: peanut butter bread
directions: Sift together first 4 ingredients.
Cut in peanut butter.
Add egg and milk.
Stir only until moistened.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, or until toothpick comes out clean.
This makes 2 medium loaves.
Tip:
Crunchy peanut butter makes this especially good!

title: walnut glory cake($1,000 bake off)
directions: Sift flour with cinnamon and salt.
Beat egg whites (1 1/4 cups) in large mixing bowl until soft mounds form.
Gradually add 3/4 cup sugar and vanilla in small mixing bowl.
Beat until thick and lemon colored.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Fold batter gently but thoroughly into egg whites using a wire whip or rubber spatula.
Fold in walnuts.
Turn into ungreased 10-inch tube pan, not a bundt pan!
Bake at 350° 55 or 65 minutes.
Invert.
Cool before removing from pan.
Frost with a vanilla glaze.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar or serve with a dollop of whipped cream.

title: chicken and bacon wraps
directions: Wrap chicken with slices of bacon.
Combine soup and sour cream; pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 425°. Chicken will look pink, but it's only from the bacon.

title: savory broccoli
directions: Trim broccoli, pare stems and cut stems into 1/4-inch slices. Separate flowerets into bite-size portions.
Heat butter and broth to boiling in a large saucepan.
Add broccoli, onion, salt and pepper.
Return to boiling, lower heat, cover and simmer until broccoli is tender, about 10 minutes.

title: "fruit pizza"
directions: Spread cookie dough over entire pan.
Cook sugar cookie dough on pizza pan until half baked.
Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar until creamy.
Spread on cookie dough.
Add 4 to 5 kinds of fruit. Chill and slice like a pizza.
Add Cool Whip, if desired.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Heat together the corn and milk.
Gradually stir in the beaten egg.
Add 1 cup of the cracker crumbs (reserve 1/4 cup for the topping), onion, pimiento, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Pour mixture into a greased 8-inch round baking dish.
Combine the 1/4 cup cracker crumbs and the melted butter.
Sprinkle over corn. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: nacho layer dip
directions: Mix refried beans with taco seasoning and cover bottom of cake pan, then layer the rest of the ingredients in the order listed.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding with 3 cups milk.
Stir until almost thick.
Fold in Eagle Brand milk.
Then fold in Cool Whip.

title: lemon cheesecake dessert
directions: In a bowl combine the cracker crumbs, pecans and sugar, add butter, mix well (set aside 1/2 cup).
Press the remaining crumb mixture into greased 13 x 9 inch baking dish.
Bake at 325 degrees for 8 minutes.
Meanwhile, in a small bowl beat the cream cheese until smooth.
Add the milk, eggs and lemon juice, beat until smooth.
Spoon over crust.
Sprinkle with the reserved crumb mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes or until center is almost set.
Cool on a wire rack.
Store in refrigerator.
16 to 20 servings.

title: hershey syrup cake
directions: Cream sugar and softened butter.
Add other ingredients.
Bake at 350° in a greased and floured pan for 30 minutes.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Mix the salt and flours.
Add eggs and milk to make dough like biscuit dough.
Roll dough out to cut in pieces for dumplings, about 1/2 inch square.
Put a few at a time in pot with cooked chicken.
Do this until all dough is used; stir lightly.
Spoon cream on top of dumplings; stir lightly.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in fondue or crock-pot to heat.
Serve with small pieces of Italian bread.

title: tang pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into pie crusts and chill.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix pineapple chunks, orange slices and strawberries (cut strawberries into 4 pieces).
Add apples (cut up) and bananas just before serving.
Peel and slice kiwi and add to top of salad. Serve.

title: chinese vegetable casserolewestboro, missouri
directions: Cook vegetables as directed (not quite as done) and drain.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with sour cream.
Chill.
Roll and bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes, not too brown.

title: grandma stanton's homemade ice cream
directions: Put sugar, flour and cornstarch in bowl and mix well.
Beat egg yolks separately in bowl.
Beat egg whites separately until quite stiff.
Put milk in kettle and place in a dish of hot water. When hot, stir in the egg yolks which have been mixed well with the sugar.
Stir into hot mixture.
Add slow; might have to add a little more milk.
Stir constantly until nearly boiling.
When cooled, add vanilla and beaten egg whites.

title: hamburger "o"
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add everything but celery and noodles. Cook until onions are tender.
Add celery and noodles.
Cook until noodles are tender.

title: four layered dessert
directions: 1st Layer:
In a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish, crumble together 1 cup of chopped pecans, 1 cup flour and 1 stick of butter to form a bottom crust.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, until lightly brown. Cool, then add 2nd layer on top.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Combine all ingredients, except pie crust, in mixing bowl. Beat for 1 minute.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: cookie turnovers
directions: Mix 1 cup sugar, the shortening, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour, salt and baking soda.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Prepare filling.
Heat oven to 400°.
Roll dough 1/16-inch thick on lightly floured cloth-covered board.
Cut into 3-inch rounds or squares.
Spoon about 1 teaspoon filling onto half of each circle.
Fold dough over filling; pinch edges to seal.
Place about 1 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Brush with milk; sprinkle with sugar.
Bake until very light brown, 8 to 10 minutes.
Immediately remove from cookie sheet.
Makes about 4 1/2 dozen.

title: stir-fry
directions: Slice carrots, mushrooms, cauliflower and onions.
Shell and devein shrimp.
Halve shrimp lengthwise.
Blend cornstarch into chicken broth.
Add soy sauce and garlic powder.

title: party dogs
directions: Mix jelly and mustard in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until jelly and mustard are blended.
Add wieners, sliced in diagonal slices, to the ingredients.
Turn heat down to simmer.
Simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: tea concentrate #2
directions: Boil water and sugar for 10 minutes.
Add the tea leaves and bring to boil.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Add ReaLemon.
Pour into containers and freeze.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: From stem end of pepper, cut thin slice off, removing inner seeds; rinse.
Boil enough water in 6-quart saucepan that will cover peppers.
Once water boils, parboil peppers 3 to 5 minutes, drain.

title: grilled chicken breasts
directions: Place chicken in shallow bowl.
Add remaining ingredients to blender; process until smooth.
Pour over chicken, coating all pieces.
Cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours.
Let stand for 15 minutes at room temperature.
Drain chicken; discard marinade. Grill over hot coals for 5 minutes on each side or until juices run clear.

title: dutch sausage with gravy(sausage cakes)
directions: Mold sausage into flat cakes and fry in shortening until brown.
Remove to hot platter to keep warm.
Brown onion in the hot fat.
Add the flour and stir until smooth.
Add bouillon and cook until thick.
Pour over sausage cakes and serve.

title: easy butter cookies
directions: Let butter stand at room temperature until soft.
Add sugar, then flour and vanilla.
Form dough into 1-inch balls and place on greased cookie sheet.
Make a deep indentation in center of each ball with your finger.
Place cookies in 350° oven.
Bake about 7 minutes or until just before cookies are browned.

title: broccoli flowerets
directions: Combine broccoli, onion and bacon; set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients until well blended.
Pour over broccoli mixture and chill until serving time.
"Easy brunch dish."

title: chocolate peanut butter pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar, vanilla, and peanut butter.
Add chocolate Cool Whip to mixture.
Spread into pie crust.
Top with regular Cool Whip.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil chicken and shred.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Twenty-four hours before serving, mix together mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Next day, mix broccoli, raisins, pecans, onion, sunflower seeds and bacon bits.

title: carrot cake
directions: In a bowl combine warm water, yeast and honey.
Let stand until it bubbles, then add remaining ingredients, stirring in whole wheat flour last.
Pour into oiled cake pan.
Sprinkle coconut on top and let stand 10 to 15 minutes in a warm place.
Preheat oven to 350° and bake for 45 to 60 minutes.
A rich treat; good in small pieces. Makes delicious cupcakes baked in muffin tins.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix ingredients together and chill.

title: gingersnap cookies
directions: Heat to boiling point the first 4 ingredients. Add and mix well. Mix remaining ingredients and sift together.

Add sifted dry ingredients to first mixture. Shape into mound; wrap in waxed paper and chill thoroughly. Roll on board lightly "floured" with confectioners sugar until dough is about 1/4-inch thick. Dip cutter in confectioners sugar each time before cutting cookie, then place cookie on lightly greased baking sheet. Bake in moderate 375° oven for about 8 minutes.

title: peanut slaw
directions: Bring to a boil, sugar, vinegar, flour, eggs and salt.
Cool. Mix with whipped cream and add to rest of ingredients when ready to serve.

title: almost fresh salsa
directions: Put all ingredients in the blender.
Mix and refrigerate.

title: cherry pie
directions: You will also need 8 or 9-inch pie pan.

title: cold raw carrot relish
directions: Clean vegetables.
Chop or grind all vegetables and put in large bowl.
Add salt and mix well with vegetables.
Let stand for 1/2 hour.
Drain juice.
Do not save juice.
Place vegetables in large bowl and add sugar, vinegar, mustard and celery seed.
Mix well.
Chill and serve on hot dogs and hamburgers.
Keep refrigerated.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream sugar and oleo.
Add eggs, flour, buttermilk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: broccoli flower bouquet
directions: Wash cauliflower and broccoli and break into similar sized flowerets.
Cut the rind from lemon with vegetable peeler, try not to get any white on peel.
Add lemon peel, garlic, salt and bay leaf to a large pot of boiling water.
Boil 5 minutes to flavor water.
Add vegetable flowerets; boil 3 to 4 minutes, until broccoli is bright green and vegetables are crisp-tender.
Do not overcook.
Drain in colander and rinse with cold water to stop cooking.
Shake well.
Discard seasonings.
(May be done in advance to this point.)
Refrigerate vegetables in plastic bag.

title: brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Combine sugar, cocoa and flour in a medium bowl.
Add melted margarine and the 3 eggs.
Stir until well blended; add vanilla and bake for 27 to 30 minutes.

title: orange delight
directions: Mix orange
juice
with
cake
mix
until
smooth. Coat orange sections
lightly with flour; dip in cake batter.
Deep fry sections
in
hot oil (350°) until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel; cool.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and/or flaked coconut. Yield:
approximately 5 dozen pieces.

title: fudge
directions: Melt margarine. Stir in pudding and add 1/2 cup milk.
Heat until it boils (1 minute), stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Beat in sugar, then add vanilla.
Pour batter into a 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch pan. Chill.

title: salmon balls
directions: Drain salmon, reserving liquid.
Add baking powder to liquid and let stand for 2 to 3 minutes.
Beat in egg; add onion and salmon.
Stir in enough flour and meal to form mixture into balls the size of an egg.
Deep fat fry until golden brown.
Makes 10 to 14 balls.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients. Pour in crust. Chill until set.

title: strawberry pretzel dessert(8 servings)
directions: Combine pretzels, margarine and sugar.
Press mixture into a 9 x 12-inch pan; bake for 8 minutes at 350°.
Set aside to cool. Combine cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip; spread over cooled crust.

title: english pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add salad dressing to cover.

title: mushroom potatoes
directions: Pour soup mixture over potatoes and cook about 1 hour at 350°, covered.

title: gingersnap cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together. Beat in eggs, molasses and dry ingredients.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Dip in sugar. Place on baking sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) for 15 to 18 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Beat eggs, pumpkin, sugar and oil in large bowl, mixing oil until light and fluffy.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Add to pumpkin mixture a little at a time and mix thoroughly.
Spread in an ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Cool and frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: low-fat curry chicken salad
directions: Cut chicken breasts into bite size chunks and stir-fry in olive oil until done (only a few minutes).
Leftover chicken may also be used.
Chop celery, snow peas and any other vegetables.
Combine all ingredients in bowl.
Serve at once or chill.
Adjust amount of ingredients to suit number of guests.

title: chicken delight
directions: Cook and drain broccoli and lay in bottom of buttered casserole dish.
Lay chicken pieces on top and pour sauce (combine soup, mayonnaise, curry powder and lemon juice).
Sprinkle top with cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: boiled icing
directions: Reserve 2 tablespoons sugar.
Combine remaining sugar, water and corn syrup in a heavy pan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring to soft ball stage (240°).
Remove from heat.
Quickly beat egg whites and salt until soft peaks form, gradually add reserved sugar, beat until blended.
Continue to beat, slowly adding syrup mixture.
Add vanilla and beat until stiff peaks form and frosting is thick.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Boil rhubarb, sugar and pineapple together for 15 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in jello.
Pour into containers. Refrigerate or freeze.
Fresh jam in early spring.

title: raw hot dish
directions: Crumble hamburger in baking dish.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Bake 2 to 3 hours at 350°.

title: chocolate sandwich cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, cream and vanilla; blend well.
Combine dry ingredients, stir into creamed mixture.
Drop by spoonful onto lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until done.
Cool. Meanwhile, prepare filling.

title: quick quiche
directions: Blend in the blender; pour into a 9-inch ungreased pie pan. Add 1 cup of grated cheese or any leftover vegetable or meats. Mix a little to submerge the cheese or leftovers.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before cutting.

title: plum cake
directions: Beat together. Pour in a greased Bundt pan or 2 loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: You will need 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Combine and beat for 2 minutes.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from oven.
Take toothpick and poke holes into top of loaves.
Add Glaze.

title: onion potatoes
directions: Chop potatoes into small pieces.
Mix melted butter with one envelope onion soup mix.
Toss over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or microwave for 20 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump can of pineapple with juice on bottom of greased pan. Dump can of pie filling on top.
Sprinkle dry cake mix all over this.
Dribble melted butter over top.

title: hot golden punch
directions: Combine sugar, water and spices; gently boil for 30 minutes. Remove cloves and cinnamon.
Add remaining juices and heat when ready to serve.

title: strawberry square salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries; stir until thawed.
Add crushed pineapple and diced bananas.
Pour half of this mixture into 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Chill until firm. Spread evenly with sour cream.
Pour remaining gelatin over top and chill until firm.
Cut in squares.
Top with sour cream dollops.

title: tortellini salad
directions: While tortellini is still warm, stir in cheese, celery, onion, grapes, tomatoes and meat.

title: polish drumstick cake
directions: First Layer:
Mix vanilla wafers, melted butter and 1 package crushed nuts.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill.

title: delta sour cream peach pie
directions: Combine sour cream, sugar, flour and salt.
Fill unbaked pie shell with sliced peaches to just about the top.
Pour sour cream mixture over peaches.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar mixture to taste.
Bake at 375° until it bubbles, approximately 1 hour.

title: kim's a crab pasta salad
directions: Boil pasta until tender; cool pasta.
Chop onion and carrots; throw in with pasta in bowl.
Shake Wishbone dressing bottle (good).
Pour over pasta mixture; then add mayo.
Stir real well. Season with lemon pepper, garlic (fresh or powder) and a little salt.

title: old fashion molasses cookies
directions: Mix in order the sugar, molasses, lard and water.
Add flour with baking powder, salt, nutmeg and ginger.
Roll dough 1/8-inch thick on lightly floured surface.
Cut into cookie shape.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes. Check after 15 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: In a large bowl, combine milk and water. Add pudding mix; beat well. Chill 5 minutes. Fold in whipped cream.

title: fried apple pies
directions: Peel and cook apples until done; add sugar and cool.
Roll biscuits on floured paper real thin.
Fill with apples.
Fry in Crisco oil until brown.

title: poor man's filet mignon
directions: Combine beef, bread, eggs, milk, salt, onion, celery flakes, chili powder and 2 tablespoons barbecue sauce.

title: zucchini appetizer
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease oblong pan (13 x 9-inch).
Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Pour into pan.
Spread evenly.
Bake until golden brown, about 25 minutes.
Cut into 2 x 1-inch pieces. Serve warm.
This makes a good vegetable dish served with meat, also good cold.

title: company potato casserole
directions: In bowl combine potatoes, sour cream, 1 cup of cheese, carrot, onions and seasonings (except Paprika).
Top with remaining cheese and Paprika.
Bake uncovered 350 for 25-35 minutes or until bubbly. Makes 8 servings.

title: peach and ham stir-fry
directions: Blend orange juice into cornstarch; stir in soy, sugar and lemon juice.
Set aside.
Drain peaches; reserve syrup for another use.
Heat wok over high heat; add oil.
Stir-fry peanuts 2 to 3 minutes or until toasted; remove from wok.
Stir-fry ginger root 30 seconds.
Add onion; stir-fry for 2 minutes.
Add zucchini; stir-fry 1 minute.
Remove vegetables from wok; add more oil if needed.
Stir-fry ham in hot oil for 2 minutes.
Stir orange juice mixture; add to wok.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly; cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Stir in peaches, peanuts and vegetables.
Cover and cook 1 to 2 minutes.
Serve over rice. Serves 6.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake (pound cake)
directions: Cream shortening and sugar and add eggs.
Beat until pale and fluffy.
Sift flour and baking powder and add alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Put cream cheese and powdered sugar in a bowl.
Beat until smooth.
Add peanut butter and milk.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in the Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Put in freezer until ready to serve.
Serve frozen with hot fudge.

title: bread pudding with bourbon sauce(recipe is from my late mother-in-law, sonya byrom)
directions: Break up bread.
Soak in milk.
Using your hand, crush and mix bread.
Add beaten eggs, sugar, vanilla and raisins.
Pour melted butter into bottom of 12 x 7-inch baking dish.
Pour in egg mix. Bake at 300° for 1 hour or until very firm.
Let cool slightly. Pour Bourbon Sauce over top.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Pare apples.
Slice and arrange in a 9-inch pastry lined pie pan. Mix 1/2 cup sugar with the cinnamon. Sprinkle over the apples. Sift 1/2 cup sugar with flour.
Cut in butter until crumbly. Sprinkle over apples.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, eggs, rum flavoring, flour, baking soda and unsweetened pineapple juice together.
Mix the mixed fruit, candied cherries, pineapple, dates, raisins and flour together.
Combine the two mixtures together and add the coconut and walnuts.
Mix all together.
Pour into greased bread loaf pans.
Bake at 275° for 2 1/2 hours.
Makes approximately 3 to 4 loaves.

title: pizza cups
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 10 muffin cups.
Brown hamburger, drain.
Stir in pizza sauce and 4 ounces of the cheese.
Separate dough into 10 biscuits.
Place 1 biscuit in each muffin cup. Firmly press in bottom and up sides.
Spoon about 1/4 hamburger mixture into each biscuit lined cup.
Sprinkle each with cheese. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes. or until edges of biscuits are brown.

title: potato refrigerator rolls
directions: Stir yeast into water until dissolved. Add sugar, salt, shortening, eggs and mashed potatoes.
Add flour and mix until dough is easy to handle.
Cover and place in refrigerator for a few hours or overnight. Shape into rolls and let rise 2 to 3 hours.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan well-greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crock-pot macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni; grease crock-pot.
Place 1/2 of macaroni in crock-pot.
Add 1 cup of cheese, rest of macaroni and rest of cheese on top.
Mix eggs and evaporated milk.
Salt and pepper. Cut butter and place into cheese and macaroni.
Pour eggs and milk over mixture, then pour milk to the top.
Cook 1 hour on high, then on low for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: peanut cereal cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Fold in corn flakes, oatmeal, nuts and other ingredients.
Drop by spoonful onto greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: do ahead mashed potatoes
directions: Peel and cook potatoes.
Add sour cream, cream cheese, onion salt and pepper.
Beat until light.
Place in greased 2-quart casserole.
Cover and store in refrigerator until ready to use. To bake, dot with butter and bake at 350° for 40 minutes, uncovered.

title: ham biscuits
directions: Bake biscuits.
Put cheese and ham in biscuits.
Mix butter, poppy seed and mustard in saucepan until melted, then add onion. Spoon mixture over biscuits.
Store in refrigerator.
Warm in microwave for 1 minute.

title: chicken cheese vegetable soup
directions: Simmer diced veggies in chicken stock until tender, but crisp. Melt butter in large pot.
Blend in flour.
Heat milk to boiling, but do not boil.
Slowly blend into flour mixture until smooth.
Add cheese.
Stir until melted.
Strain veggies from stock and add stock to cheese-milk.
Stir until smooth with wire whip.
Add veggies and cooked chicken.
Season to taste. Garnish with fresh parsley sprigs.

title: creamy potato soup
directions: Peel and dice potatoes. Boil until tender.
Melt butter in 5-quart pan over medium heat. Add onion, salt and pepper.
Cook until onion is tender.
Adjust heat as needed. Add flour and stir until smooth and bubbly. Remove from heat.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly. Return to heat and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and add potatoes.
Simmer 10 minutes.

title: chocolate coconut soda
directions: In tall glass, mix together cream of coconut and syrup.
Add ice cream and club soda.
Stir.
Garnish as desired.
Serve immediately.

title: rice and mushroom casserole
directions: Butter casserole dish.
Sprinkle rice.
Mix soups together and pour evenly over rice.
Sprinkle mushrooms and cut up butter patties.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: orange-pineapple punch
directions: Place sherbet in a large punch bowl, then add remaining ingredients; stir well.
Chunks of orange sherbet will remain in punch.
Makes about 5 quarts.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Put rice in bottom of a pan or casserole dish. Brown chops and place on top of the rice. Pour soup diluted with 1/2 can of water over it. Add 1/2 can of water to pan that you browned chops in and put over chops. Bake in 350° oven 1 hour. Be sure to cover dish.

title: snow cream
directions: Wait til the second big snow because the first big snow has all the dirty stuff from the airplanes in it.
Put snow in a big pot. If you want chocolate, put coco* in your sugar.
About 1 tablespoon to a cup of sugar.
Put this on the snow and add enough cream to make it icy.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Beat at least 5 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Add all ingredients.
Spoon into a 1-quart baking dish coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: easy fruit cake
directions: Roll crackers and wafers into crumbs.
Mix with other ingredients.
Pack in graham cracker box.
Chill for several hours or may be made and frozen.

title: chicken breasts supreme
directions: Wrap chicken breasts with bacon strips.
Lay each chicken breast on top of 2 slices of dried beef in greased casserole dish. Mix soup, sour cream and cream cheese; pour over chicken.
Bake at 325° for approximately 2 hours.
(Sauce is good poured over rice or mashed potatoes.)

title: homemade play dough
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add coloring to water. Cook slowly in saucepan, stir constantly.
It will ball up when done.
Remove and knead.
Store in Ziploc bag.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients and put in refrigerator overnight.
Remove and roll into little balls; dip into egg white, then into ground nuts.
Put on greased cookie sheet.
Press thumb in cookie dough and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cream cheese filling for prunes and dates
directions: Put the cream cheese in a bowl and let it soften at room temperature for 1/2 hour.
Stir in the milk a little at a time. Gradually add just enough powdered sugar to make a firm dough. Add the vanilla.

title: canadian flapjacks
directions: Combine all ingredients except apple with mixer.
Add apple and mix by hand.
Spoon into oiled frying pan at medium heat. Turn when bubbles appear and harden.
Brown other side.
Serve immediately with your choice of topping.
Serves 4.

title: mississippi hush puppies
directions: Heat 2 or 3 inches Crisco oil to 365° in deep fryer or deep saucepan.
Combine cornmeal, flour, baking powder and salt in bowl.
Add buttermilk, egg and onion.
Mix until well blended. Drop batter by tablespoonfuls into heated oil.
Fry a few at a time for 3 or 4 minutes or until golden brown.
Turn as needed for browning. Drain on paper towels.
Serve immediately.
Yields one dozen.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach, drain well.
Set aside.
Mix together all ingredients, stir in spinach and cool in refrigerator.
Roll into small balls and bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350 for 15 minutes.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Cook chicken in boiling water until tender.
Debone chicken. Strain broth, reserving 2 2/3 cups.
Combine chicken soup with half the broth.
Mix well and set aside.
Combine mushroom soup with remaining broth.
Mix well and set aside.
Combine stuffing mix with butter, reserving 1/4 cup for garnish.
Spoon half of remaining stuffing mixture in a slightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with half of the chicken.
Cover with chicken soup mixture; repeat layers.
Pour mushroom soup over layers. Sprinkle with reserved stuffing mix.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Remove casserole from refrigerator 15 minutes before baking.
Uncover and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread pie filling on bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Arrange drained pineapple chunks on top of pie filling.
Sprinkle cake mix on top of pineapple.
Pour melted margarine on top of cake mix.
Sprinkle on coconut and nuts. Bake 1 hour at 350°. Serves 12.

title: pickle roll-ups
directions: Leave all ingredients out for 2 hours to soften.
Lay the pickles out on a paper towel; pat to dry.
Lay dried beef out flat and spread softened cream cheese on meat.
Place pickle on edge of meat and roll the meat around pickle (jelly roll style).
Repeat steps and re-roll the pickle with a 2nd piece of meat. Refrigerate the rolls for approximately 1 hour before slicing.

title: gingerbread cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large saucepan, combine sugar, shortening and molasses.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally. Remove from heat; cool to room temperature.
Stir in remaining ingredients in order listed; blend well.

title: ginny's crescent rolls
directions: Combine shortening, sugar, salt.
Add eggs.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add water mixture and flour, knead until smooth. Let rise 1 - 2 hours.
Cut dough in half, roll each half in circle.
Spread melted butter on dough before cutting.
Cut into 1/16ths.
Roll from large end to small end making crescents. Bake at 350°F until light brown, approximately 15 to 20 minutes. Makes 32 rolls.

title: kid pleasers cranberry scoop
directions: In a blender container, process cranberry juice cocktail, strawberries, banana and frozen yogurt on high until smooth. Makes 4 servings.

title: herbed meat balls burgundy(casserole dish)
directions: Combine bread and milk; let stand 10 minutes.
Mix well with fork to a fine mixture.
Add meat, onions, salt and herbs; mix well and form into balls; wetting hands frequently will prevent sticking.
Roll balls in seasoned flour (salt and pepper).
Brown in 2 tablespoons of butter or drippings in skillet.
Place balls in 2-quart casserole dish.

title: cheese dip
directions: Melt cheese. Add rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Serve with chips.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour 1/2 batter into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Layer sliced apples over batter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon. Pour remaining batter over apples.
Sprinkle the top with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together. Cut in shortening until mixed thoroughly.
Add milk and dissolved yeast.
Work together with a large spoon until all flour is moist.
Cover bowl and refrigerate until ready to use.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Dough will keep for weeks in refrigerator.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Cream together oleo and sugar.
Add eggs.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add almond extract.
Stir in flour and baking powder.
Mix until smooth.
Butter a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Turn mixture into pan.
Spoon pie filling into the cake in 16 spots.

title: hot spiced cranberry punch
directions: Heat cranberry juice, cloves, cinnamon stick and water. Boil 3 minutes. Let stand 1 minute. Remove spices. Stir in sugar until dissolved. Blend in lemonade; heat to boiling. Boil 1 minute. Serve hot.

title: sour cream chicken casserole
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Cut water chestnuts into small pieces.
Mix crumbled crackers and margarine.
Spread half of crackers in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix all of the other ingredients and spread over the crackers on the bottom of dish. Sprinkle remaining crackers on top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: country monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into quarters.
Shake in a bag with granulated sugar and cinnamon.
Place one layer of biscuits in greased tube or Bundt pan and sprinkle with nuts. Add two more layers of biscuits and nuts on top of first.
Melt brown sugar and margarine and boil for 1 minute.
Pour over top of the 3 layers. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes to cool, then remove one cube at a time (like finger cakes) and serve!

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Partially defrost hash browns.
Mix them with melted margarine, Cheddar cheese, onions, sour cream, chicken soup and salt.
Put mixture in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle corn flakes on top.
Pour 1/4 cup melted margarine over corn flakes.
Bake uncovered in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes. May be made the night ahead, refrigerated and baked the next day.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Take hamburger; brown in skillet with onion, salt, pepper and garlic.
Pour hamburger and drippings into a big stock pan.
Add the water, then rest of the ingredients.
Cook until potatoes are tender, about 1/2 hour or so.
Very good.

title: classic baked beans
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook bacon to crisp; drain.
Crumble bacon.
In 2-quart casserole, combine bacon, Van Camp's pork and beans, onion, ketchup, molasses, brown sugar, mustard and Worcestershire.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 to 50 minutes or until thickened and bubbly, stirring every 15 minutes.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain and add chili powder.
Mix in next 6 items.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Serve with Doritos chips.

title: cheese straws
directions: Cream margarine and cheese with electric mixer.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Press dough through cookie press onto cookie sheet.
Bake about 12 minutes at 375°.
Makes about 75 straws.

title: cherry or apple crisp(quick!)
directions: Place pie filling in 8-inch square pan.
Combine dry ingredients.
Sprinkle on top.
Dot with margarine or butter. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes until golden brown.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.
Makes 6 servings.

title: electric skillet pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in a 300° electric skillet.
Place pineapple on butter in bottom of skillet.
Add brown sugar to taste.
Mix cake mix, eggs and pineapple juice.
This may have lumps.
Not to worry.
Pour on pineapple rings and bake for 8 minutes with cover on. Cool 2 minutes. Flip onto plate.
Garnish with maraschino cherries.

title: applesauce oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add applesauce.
Sift together the flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt and stir in.
Add oats and raisins.
Drop by spoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Add cucumbers and onions. Bring to a boil for 8 minutes. Pour into hot jars and seal. This makes 8 pints.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour pie filling into a 13X9 pan. Spoon pineapple on top of pie filling. Sprinkle cake mix over pineapple. Melt butter and pour over cake mix. Sprinkle nuts and coconut over margarine. Bake at 350 degrees for 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chicken rice 'n easy
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a 7 x 11 x 2-inch greased glass baking pan, combine wine, stock or water, salt and rice.
Place chicken breasts over rice mixture.
Combine mushrooms with soup. Spread over chicken.
Sprinkle with thyme, bread crumbs and butter.
Cover tightly with foil and bake about 1 hour or until chicken is done.

title: cheesy zucchini lasagne
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Keep aside 1/2 cup of Mozzarella.
Mix remaining Mozzarella with zucchini, Ricotta and Parmesan.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Stir in cranberry sauce and crushed pineapple (do not drain).
Add port wine and nuts.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart greased mold and chill.

title: tomato, leek and onion soup
directions: If leeks are not available, use more onions.
Saute onions, leeks and garlic in olive oil until transparent, but not brown. Combine sauteed vegetables, parsley, thyme, bay leaf, tomatoes and stock in 2-quart saucepan.
Simmer over medium heat until tomatoes (if fresh) are cooked and flavors are well combined.
Remove bay leaf.
Season with salt, tamari, soy sauce and honey to taste. Garnish with chopped parsley and green onion tops.
Yield:
6 cups.

title: easy baked chicken
directions: Remove skin from breasts.
Dip into buttermilk.
Roll in Bisquick.
Line baking dish with aluminum foil. Place chicken on foil and cover with more foil.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Remove top foil.
Bake for 15 to 30 more minutes.

title: grannie's pork chop casserole
directions: Flour, salt and pepper pork chops, then fry them until brown. Saute the onion and pepper.
In a large casserole dish, well sprayed with Pam, sprinkle the rice, then add the onion and pepper. Pour the soup and water over last.
Stack pork chops atop this. Bake at 400° for 45 minutes, uncovered.
Wonderful!

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash and drain vegetables.
Slice cucumbers and onions.
Soak in salt solution (2 quarts ice water and 1/2 cup salt) for 3 hours. Mix vinegar, sugar and spices.
Bring to a boil.
Add cucumbers and onions just to heat through.
Pack hot cucumbers into jars, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Cover with boiling hot liquid.
Adjust lids. Process in boiling water bath for 15 minutes.

title: country ham casserole
directions: Cook ham on top of stove in Teflon lined Dutch oven.
Cook until ham is brown.
Add a cup of water and simmer for 15 minutes. Peel and slice potatoes.
Add flour, onion, cheese and salt. Pour milk over mixture and mix well.
Pour into ham.
Cook for about 30 minutes or until done.
Stir often.
Pour into casserole and serve.

title: chili con carne(large batch)
directions: Crumble and brown beef in skillet or stew pot. Drain and add onion and a bit of oil in necessary. Add tomatoes and seasonings. Simmer about 2 hours. Add beans with liquid. You can add water if necessary. Heat through and remove bay leaf.

title: scalloped potatoes and pork chops
directions: In a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, layer half of the potatoes and onion.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper; repeat layers. Combine the soup and sour cream; pour over potato mixture.
Cover and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: artichoke parmesan dip
directions: Preheat the oven to 325°. Drain and chop the artichoke hearts. Mix the artichoke hearts with the mayonnaise, cheese and garlic, combining well. Put the mixture in a small, ovenproof casserole; sprinkle a little paprika on top and bake for 45 minutes. Yield: 4 servings.

title: peanut butter filled fudge cupcakes
directions: In medium mixing bowl, stir together flour, cocoa, soda and salt.
In large mixing bowl, beat shortening about 30 seconds.
Add brown sugar and vanilla; beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add dry ingredients alternately with the 1/2 cup milk, beating after each addition.

title: clam casserole
directions: Beat all together in casserole and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: apricot nut bars
directions: Mix margarine, nuts, apricots, salt and vanilla.
Add eggs, sugar, baking powder and flour.
Bake in greased 8 x 8-inch pan at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: raisin cookies
directions: Boil raisins in water until water is evaporated.
Mix remaining ingredients in mixer.
Stir in raisins.
Form cookies. Dip each cookie in cinnamon/sugar before baking.
Bake at 350° about 12 minutes.
These are soft cookies.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Beat together well all ingredients except shrimp.
Fold in shrimp by hand.
Best made one day ahead.
Do not use light cream cheese; will not set.
Serve with fresh vegetables or crackers.

title: pickled beets
directions: In quart jar, alternate sliced beets and onions slices.
Fill to top.
Pour pickle juice in to fill all spaces.
Cover tightly and refrigerate 1 week.
A family favorite.

title: sour cream pancakes(a mix between an omelet or a pancake)
directions: Mix eggs, sour cream and self-rising corn meal mix.
Batter may be thick.
Fry in oil until brown.
These pancakes take longer to fry, brown slowly.
Serve with butter and warm syrup.
Makes 8 to 10 pancakes.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and milk.
Add crabmeat, chopped onion, horseradish, salt and pepper; blend well.
Sprinkle with toasted almonds; bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cheese and dried beef together.
Add the whites of onion (chopped fine); form into ball.
Chop the green onion tops and roll cheese ball in them.

title: cookies while you sleep
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Gradually add sugar and vanilla.
Stir in nuts and chocolate chips.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix salmon, egg and crackers.
Add 1/2 can of mushroom soup. Mix well.
Put into well-greased baking dish and put rest of soup on top.
