Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Mix all vegetables, cheese and bacon in large bowl.
Mix sauce and pour over vegetable mix.
Enjoy!

title: fig preserve cake
directions: Combine all dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Add oil; beat well.
Add eggs, beating well.
Add buttermilk and vanilla; mix thoroughly.
Stir in preserves and pecans.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix egg, vinegar and water together.
Sift flour and salt. Add shortening.
Combine with liquid ingredients.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Drain pineapple, reserving syrup.
Add water to syrup to make 1 cup; add to gelatin with vinegar and salt.
Chill until partially set.
Fold carrot, pineapple and nuts into gelatin.
Turn into individual molds or 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch dish.
Chill until firm.

title: tutti frutti jam
directions: Peel, core and grind orange.
Place pears, orange, cherries, pineapple and lemon in kettle.
Cook to desired thickness.

title: chewie pralines
directions: Melt butter in a heavy pan, adding sugar and salt, stirring thoroughly.
Add syrup. While stirring well, add milk slowly. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly to 240 degrees for about 12 to 15 minutes.
Add pecans and stir.
Remove from heat, stir in vanilla.
Drop onto buttered muffin tins so they will be uniform in size.

title: portobello and basil lentil stew
directions: First, heat the olive oil in a large soup pot and saute the onion, garlic, mushrooms, green pepper, salt and white pepper together until the mushrooms are tender.
(This should take about 5 minutes.)
Add the chicken or vegetable stock and tomato paste to the soup pot and mix well until the tomato paste is completely blended into the stock.
Stir in the red lentils and bring to a boil.
Then lower the heat, cover and cook over medium-low heat for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add the basil and simmer with the pot covered 15 minutes longer.
Add extra salt and pepper to taste.
Serve the stew in individual bowls and float 1 tablespoon of dry sherry on top of each bowl.
Garnish the bowls with the remaining basil leaves and serve hot.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cook noodles and drain; keeping warm.
Stack beef strips. cut into 1 inch strips.
In large skillet, heat 2 tsp. oil over medium heat until hot.
Add beef and garlic; stir fry 1 minute or until outside of meat is no longer pink.
Remove from skillet; season with salt and pepper.
In same skillet, cook mushrooms in remaining oil until tender.
Remove from heat.
Add brown gravy mix and water; blend well.
Over medium heat bring to boil.
Reduce heat, simmer until gravy has thickened, stirring frequently.
Add beef back into gravy mixture; heat through.
Serve over noodles; top with sour cream.
Serves 4.

title: ham loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F.
You may have meats ground at meat market.
To meat mixture add the bread or cracker crumbs, milk, and eggs.
Mix all ingredients together, and form into loaf. Please in baking dish.
To make sauce to pour over ham loaf, mix flour, sugar, and mustard. Slowly blend in tomato juice and vinegar, and heat in saucepan until mixture thickens.
Pour over ham loaf, and bake at 350° for 1-1/2 hours.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Add sugar and yeast to warm water.
Make dough and bake at 450°
until brown.

title: white pizza dip
directions: Mix first three ingredients & half of the Mozzarella cheese into shallow pan (pie pan).
Sprinkle the other half of the mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake at 350 for 30 minutes uncovered. Use chunks of bread to dip into mixture.

title: meatza pie
directions: Mix and pat first 2 ingredients in a greased pie pan.
Cover with pizza cheese.
Cover with large can of drained mushrooms. Cover with the 1 cup spaghetti sauce.
Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese and oregano.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: deviled ham whip
directions: Combine all ingredients until well blended.
Chill.
Use as sandwich spread or for stuffed celery.

title: chocolate crinkle cookies
directions: In large bowl, stir together sugar and oil.
Add cocoa, blending well.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, baking powder and salt, blending well.
Cover; refrigerate overnight. Heat oven to 350°.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet. Bake 12 to 14 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet to wire rack. Cool completely.

title: confetti salad
directions: Mix remaining ingredients.
Toss all ingredients together and chill.

title: herbs de provence("gifts from the heart to the table")
directions: Combine and mix well.
Seal in airtight container.
Season meats with herb mixture before cooking, or infuse herb mixture in some olive oil to be used in marinades and salads or to saute meats.

title: tapioca jello salad
directions: Cut each orange slice in half. Save 6 whole slices for top. Add boiling water to dry ingredients; mix well. Place in the refrigerator to cool and thicken to a very thick syrup. Then add Cool Whip and fruit. Place in a container and decorate top with 6 whole orange slices in pinwheel fashion. Can also put a maraschino cherry in middle if desired.

title: "fantasy" dessert
directions: Take 1 stick of margarine, flour and sugar and combine in mixing bowl.
Mix like pie crust.
Press into cake pan (13 x 9-inch).
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Let cool.
Take cream cheese and cream together with 1 cup of powdered sugar.
Beat in 1 cup of Cool Whip.
Spread this mixture on top of crust.
Take chocolate and French vanilla puddings.
Mix together with 3 cups of milk.
Spread over cream cheese mixture.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: pecan fudge pie
directions: In medium saucepan over low heat, melt chocolate and margarine.
Stir in sweetened condensed milk, hot water and eggs. Mix well.
Remove from heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until center is set. Cool.
Chill 3 hours.
Bake at 350°.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: hilton's venison stew
directions: In a 14-inch Dutch oven, brown cubed venison, onion and mushrooms.
Add
beer
and simmer until meat is tender, adding liquid as
needed
(beer or water).
Add tomato paste, Italian tomatoes,
barbecue
sauce,
bite
size
potatoes, carrots and celery.
Simmer
until
vegetables
are done.
Season to taste with salt,
pepper,
etc.
Make a thickening, using cornstarch and water.
Add
to stew, slowly, until desired consistency is obtained.
Remove
Dutch
oven
from
heat.
Open biscuits and place on top of stew.
Oil underside of lid and place on Dutch oven.
Add sufficient
hot coals to top of lid and check often until biscuits are golden brown, about 20 minutes.
Enjoy!!!

title: mother's tea cakes
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, milk, vanilla, salt and flour.
Makes a very soft dough.
Roll out with cookie cutter. Bake at 350°.

title: chicken teriyaki
directions: In small cooking bag, mix soy sauce, honey and sherry.
Add chicken to bag and tie open end securely with plastic strip cut from open end of bag.
Turn chicken on its side and place in 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Marinate in refrigerator 1 to 2 hours, turning chicken over after 1/2 of time.
To microwave, place bird, breast side up, in dish.
Slash bag near closure.
Insert temperature probe through the bag into meatiest part of inner thigh, from below the end of and parallel to the leg.
Microwave at Medium-high (7). Set temperature, 190°.
When oven signals, remove chicken.
Prepare Teriyaki Sauce and finish chicken as described.

title: forfar bridies(scottish meat pies)
directions: Place butter in a skillet to melt.
Add ground beef and onion. Brown until done.
Add seasoning and water to make gravy by adding a little flour or a white sauce with cornstarch.
Make pastry shells and cut into oval shape.
Cover with the meat mixture.
Wet edges of pastry and fold over to make an envelope and crimp edges of pastry with fingers.
Make a slit in top of each bridie.
Bake at 400° for about 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: beans and franks
directions: Cut up the hot dogs and the onion into small pieces.
Saute the margarine in a large skillet.
Add beans and simmer for 30 minutes.
Stir as needed.

title: low-fat whipped topping
directions: Scald the evaporated milk.
Cool slightly.
Soften gelatin in cold water.
Stir gelatin into warm milk and stir until dissolved. Pour milk into small, deep bowl.
Freeze until ice crystals form around edges and mixture is completely jellied.
Whip at high speed of mixer until peaks form.
Gradually add sugar and vanilla. Beat until stiff peaks form.

title: tomato cheese salad
directions: Heat soup and melt cheese in it.
Add gelatin, moistened in 1/4 cup cold water.
Set aside to cool.
Add mayonnaise, celery, onion, pepper and pecans; mix well.
Refrigerate to mold.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pink lady salad
directions: Cream the cream cheese with maraschino cherry juice.
Drain fruit cocktail well.
Whip whipping cream.
Mix all together, put into a serving dish and cover with coconut and maraschino cherries.
Chill.
May add bananas.

title: nan's taco dip
directions: Have the cream cheese and sour cream at room temperature. Place in mixing bowl with the taco dip and blend well until smooth. Spread in a 9 x 12 glass dish. Cover with a thin layer of taco sauce. Sprinkle onion, peppers and tomatoes over the sauce. Top with shredded cheese. Place in refrigerator overnight. Serve with tortilla chips to dip into it.

title: spicy cheese dip
directions: Heat all ingredients together until cheese is melted and soups are well blended.
Serve with corn chips.

title: sugar house cookies
directions: Place the fat, maple syrup and egg in a bowl and beat until light and creamy.
Sift together the flour, salt and baking powder.
Fold in the raisins, oatmeal and nutmeg.
Add the milk and nuts and blend thoroughly into the creamed mixture.
Drop by spoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mix together and chill.
Serve with chips.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed on package.
Saute onion and pepper in butter until tender.
Add chicken, soup and milk to onion and pepper.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add cooked spaghetti and cheese.
Cook until cheese is melted.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Let cool.
Take a 9 1/2 x 13 1/2 x 2-inch baking pan; grease bottom and sides with 1 tablespoon butter.
Add frozen broccoli.
Separate chicken in pieces; mix with broccoli.
Add milk.
Place cheese slices over top to cover chicken, broccoli and milk.
Make stuffing according to package directions.
Spread on top of cheese.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: In a large bowl, mix eggs, oil and milk together.
Stir in sugar, then pumpkin and vanilla.
Mix in dry ingredients.
Stir thoroughly.
Stir in chips.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet and bake in preheated 350° oven for 15 minutes. Makes 5 dozen.

title: tapioca cream
directions: Mix egg yolks, milk, 2 tablespoons sugar, tapioca and salt in saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils.
Remove from heat; cool.
Stir in vanilla.
Beat egg whites until frothy.
Gradually beat in the 1/4 cup of sugar.
Continue beating until stiff and glossy.
Fold into mixture in saucepan. Spoon into dessert dishes.
Serve with cream or fruit juice.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles as directed on package. Return drained noodles to kettle; stir in tuna, sour cream, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole dish.

title: cheddar meat loaves
directions: In a bowl, beat egg and milk.
Stir in cheese, oats, onion and salt.
Add beef and mix well.

title: cauliflower broccoli salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Pour over vegetables. Let stand overnight and toss occasionally.

title: spinach bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Roll out dough on floured surface to form a rectangle.
Spread cheese, then spinach.
Sprinkle on fresh garlic. Fold over dough and tuck in ends to form a loaf. Slit top and wash with egg white.
Place on a greased and floured cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until brown. Serve as an appetizer or side dish with salad.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix 1/2 cup warm water with peanut butter to soften.
Beat eggs and add to dry ingredients.
Add softened peanut butter and remaining water. Stir in cocoa until well-mixed.
Add vanilla.
Pour into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 325° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: spanish chicken
directions: Boil chicken.
Cool and bone.
In large skillet combine Cheez Whiz, soups and chicken.
Heat until blended.
Add chili powder to taste.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add all others.
Beat on medium speed until smooth.
Grease pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 2 large loaf pans.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease cookie sheets.
Break and beat the egg.
Measure and put shortening in another bowl.
Pack sugar; add to the shortening.
Add egg, vanilla and water; beat until smooth.
Measure flour, soda and salt; sift into another bowl. Add flour mixture to egg mixture slowly; mix.
Stir in chips. Bake for approximately 12 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Beat shortening and sugar and add eggs and bananas.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in greased and floured loaf pan in a 300° oven for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: grandma cole's icebox cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and then flour and vanilla. Mix well and then add nuts or chips.
Roll in long rolls and freeze.
Slice and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Layer meat mixture, soup mixture and Tater Tots.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and sprinkle grated cheese.
Bake until cheese melts.

title: grandmother's butterscotch sauce
directions: Cook on low-medium heat until thickens.

title: chickeny collard greens
directions: Chop off stalk end of the collards and pull leaves apart. Fill sink with cold water; add 2 drops of mild dish detergent. Clean and thoroughly rinse collards.
Chop collards in bite size pieces.
In a large Dutch oven, pour chicken broth and water. Bring to a boil.
Add collards, garlic, salt and pepper to taste. Cook, covered, on low heat until tender and the color is dark green.

title: grilled shrimp
directions: You will need skewers.

title: divinity candy
directions: Cook sugar, water, syrup, vanilla and salt to soft ball stage. Pour 1/2 of syrup in a fine stream over stiffly beaten egg whites while beating constantly.
Cook remainder of syrup to crackle stage.
Pour over first mixture in a fine stream and continue beating until it begins to harden.
Add nuts.
Spread evenly in well buttered pan.
When hard enough, cut in 1-inch squares.
Nut halves may be placed so there will be 1 on top of each piece, if desired.

title: mandarin orange sweet potatoes(by dear friend becky jones)
directions: Whip together potatoes, 2 tablespoons margarine, 4 tablespoons brown sugar, rum and salt.
Fold in 1 small can drained oranges. Turn into buttered casserole.
Arrange rest of oranges spiral fashion on top.
Combine rest of margarine, sugar and nuts and spread on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Combine gelatin and water.
Add strawberries, pineapple, juice and bananas.
Pour half of mixture into mold.
When firm spread with sour cream.
Carefully spoon remaining mixture and chill.

title: no fail pie crust
directions: Cut flour and Crisco together until crumbly.
Mix well the water, egg and vinegar.
Combine liquid and flour mixture.
Keeps in refrigerator up to a week.
Freezes well.

title: deviled nut ball
directions: In a medium bowl, mix together deviled ham and cream cheese. Stir in pineapple, green pepper, onion and pepper sauce.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.
On waxed paper, form mixture into a ball or log and roll in mixture of crushed nuts and parsley to coat completely. Serve with crackers.
Makes 2 cups spread.

title: bully pudding
directions: Grease 9 x 9 baking pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Put butter into a 2 quart mixing bowl and stand over hot water to melt.
Remove from heat.
Add sugar and beat until well mixed.
Add eggs and beat until creamy, then add flour and baking powder and beat until smooth.
Fold in dates and nuts.
Turn into prepared pan, bake 40 minutes.
Cool; cut into squares or spoon into serving dishes. Serve with cream or ice cream.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pineapple melon cooler(6 servings)
directions: Peel and seed cantaloupe; cut into chunks.
Place in blender with pineapple and 12 ice cubes.
Whirl at high speed until smooth.
Fill tall glasses 2/3 full.
Add sparkling water and stir.
Garnish with mint and fresh pineapple spear.

title: spaghetti and chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and take off bone.
Cook the spaghetti in the chicken broth.
Brown bell peppers and small onions in margarine. Mix together chicken, pepper, onion, cheese and Ro-Tel.
Add to the spaghetti and then add salt and pepper.
Stir all this together real well.

title: strawberry fluff
directions: Put cottage cheese in bowl.
Pour in dry jello and stir.
Add pineapple.
Fold in cool whip.
Stir and chill.

title: cranberry raspberry relish
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
May be refrigerated and kept for several weeks.

title: chicken different
directions: Wash chicken good.
Mix sour cream, yogurt, salt, pepper, paprika, 3 to 4 drops (1/4 teaspoon) Worcestershire and 3 to 4 drops hot sauce together; place over chicken and cover.
Let stand overnight in fridge.
Heat oven to 350° to 375° (depending on oven).
Roll the chicken in your favorite bread/cracker mixture. Bake 1 hour.

title: herbed feta spread
directions: Combine Feta cheese, cream cheese, mayonnaise and sour cream in mixing bowl. Beat with an electric mixer on medium speed until mixture is blended. Add sun-dried tomatoes, garlic, herbs and hot sauce. Mix until spreading consistency. Gently add chopped green onions. Cover and chill until ready to serve. Serve with raw vegetables or crackers.

title: garden patch macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling water until just tender.
Cook cabbage in boiling, salted water until barely tender, 6 to 7 minutes.
Drain and combine with macaroni, carrots, peas, seasoned salt and chives.
Combine soup and sour cream; fold through macaroni mixture.
Add salt and transfer to greased 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until mixture is thoroughly heated and cheese is melted (do not overcook).
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly with spoon. (Note: Consistency of cake is better if cherries are cut up.) Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for about 30 minutes. Cover with Chocolate Glaze.

title: corn bread muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Beat in separate bowl the milk, shortening and egg; add to dry ingredients.
Beat lightly until thoroughly mixed.
Partly fill hot muffin tins.
Bake in quick oven (450°) for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yields 2 1/2 dozen small muffins.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in pan.
Put chicken parts on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 2 hours.

title: sauerkraut casserole
directions: In skillet, cook sausage and onion until sausage is brown and onion is tender.
Drain.
Stir in apples, kraut, water, brown sugar and caraway seed.
Place in 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: salami roll-ups
directions: Dampen towels (enough to completely cover dry hard rounds). Let stand for 1 1/2 hours or until soft and pliable.
Meanwhile, soften, with mixer, the cream cheese.
Add mayonnaise, pepper and chives; mix well.

title: banana nut loaf
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Beat well.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture alternately with well mashed bananas.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into well-greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for approximately 50 minutes.
Cool on rack and wrap. Better if baked day before served.

title: flavored rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in casserole dish. Add other ingredients. Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: tomato aspic salad
directions: *All vegetables are chopped and optional.

title: homemade ice cream(makes about 1 gallon.)
directions: Blend together all ingredients.
Pour into 1 gallon freezer. Cover, freeze with ice-salt mixture in proportions recommended for freezer.
When ice cream is frozen, pour off brine.
Remove dasher and pack with ice and salt.
Allow to stand 1 1/2 to 2 hours to ripen.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Stir together shortening and margarine.
Beat in sugars and flour and all other ingredients.
Chill dough 2 hours.
Spoon out on cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: world's best cake
directions: Combine cake mix, oil and mandarin oranges with liquid.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Mix well for 2 minutes.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake in preheated oven at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake 10	minutes
at
400°, then 45 minutes at 300°.
Test for doneness with a toothpick.

title: apple slice
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cream shortening.
Beat in sugar.
Beat in egg.
Beat in vanilla.
Add dry mixture and stir until just blended.
Pour half of batter into buttered 8-inch square baking dish or pan.
Smooth batter.
Slice apples very thinly, using vegetable peeler or grater.
Spread slices on batter.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and nutmeg.
Pour on remaining batter.

title: hamburger steak soup
directions: Make white sauce with first three ingredients.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Set aside.
Brown hamburger meat.
Drain off excess fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Add the onion and green pepper to the hamburg; fry, drain and then add the remaining ingredients.
Simmer for about 10 to 15 minutes.
Put on buns and enjoy!

title: ham casserole
directions: Following package directions, cook and drain rigatoni.
Cook onion in oil until tender.
Add flour; cook 1 minute.
Add milk; stir with a whisk.
Add 1/2 of the cheese and the noodles, then put in peas and ham.
Mix good and put in casserole dish.
Top with rest of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: blueberry upside-down cake
directions: Pour washed blueberries into a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole and sprinkle with the 1/4 cup sugar.
In mixing bowl, cream shortening, the 1/2 cup sugar and 1 egg together.
Sift the flour, baking powder and salt.
Add this to creamed mixture alternately with the milk.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Test.
Spoon out while hot and serve with cream, whipped cream, ice cream or milk.

title: breakfast bread
directions: Combine first 2 ingredients and set aside.
Sift together next 5 ingredients.
Cream shortening, eggs and brown sugar.
Add nuts and dates to creamed mixture.
Combine all ingredients and mix well by hand.

title: meat loaf supreme
directions: Mix ground beef with soup.
Add other ingredients.
Shape mixture into loaf.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: clam chowder(crock-pot)
directions: In small skillet, saute bacon and onion until golden; drain and put into crock-pot with clams.
Add all remaining ingredients, except evaporated milk.
Cover; cook on low 6 to 9 hours, or until potatoes are tender.
Add evaporated milk during last hour.

title: lemon meringue pie(microwave)
directions: Mix cornstarch, flour, milk, sugar and salt with a wire whip in a large Pyrex bowl.
Microwave on High for 7 to 9 minutes.
Add beaten egg yolks, beat mixture well with a wire whip.
Microwave 1 minute more.
Add butter and mix well.
Then add lemon juice and rind; mix well.
Pour into baked pie shell and top with meringue.

title: grasshopper candy
directions: In double boiler over low heat, melt morsels.
Remove from heat.
Add nuts and noodles to morsels.
Toss all together until noodles and nuts are covered.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper. Cool.

title: baker's aid
directions: Whip together in blender.
Coat cake pans with a thin coat for baking.

title: popeye biscuits
directions: Mix all together.
Roll and cut out.
Place on a cookie sheet and brush with butter.
Bake at 450°.
Makes about 30 biscuits.

title: marinated baked fish
directions: In a 12 x 7-inch baking dish, combine all ingredients, except fish.
Add fish; marinate 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: fruit cake
directions: Put bread through blender to crumb.
Pour bread crumbs in bowl.
Stir in all the other ingredients.
Mix well.
Spoon into a 6 cup nonstick muffin tin.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.
This equals 2 breads, 2 milks and 2 fruits.

title: holiday wassail
directions: In a large kettle, combine the tea and sugar.
Add juices, cinnamon sticks and 12 cloves.
Bring to a boil and boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Serve warm or cool.
Garnish punch bowl with orange slices, studded with remaining cloves.
Yields 12 to 16 servings (1 gallon).

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Combine flour, sugar, juice, vinegar and egg in saucepan. Heat on medium-high flame until thick.
Simmer for 5 minutes until like pudding consistency.
Cool well.
Fold Cool Whip, apples and 1/2 cup nuts in pudding mixture.
Place in serving bowl and top with remaining nuts.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes; peel and slice.
Add vinegar and seasonings. Fry bacon until crisp, then dice.
Combine potatoes, bacon, 3 tablespoons bacon grease, 4 chopped eggs and onion.
Mix well. Decorate top of salad with the rest of sliced eggs.
If too dry, add a little water and 1/4 cup salad dressing.

title: mom's apple cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Cut Crisco into flour until it resembles fine crumbs; add milk and mix well.
Turn out onto floured board and knead until smooth.
Roll out to a rectangle shape, 1/4-inch thick.
Spread apples over dough and sprinkle cinnamon over apples.
Roll up like cinnamon rolls and cut into 1-inch slices.
Place slices in pan that has the melted oleo.
Heat sugar and water in saucepan until sugar melts.
Pour this syrup around sliced dough.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Make sure you use the 2 cups water as dough will absorb the water.

title: green beans
directions: Mix green beans and potatoes together; cook in saucepan until almost done.
Broil bacon pieces until crispy.
Put together and add mushroom soup.
Finish cooking and serve.

title: rolle pulse
directions: Using 1 flank steak, veal or breast of lamb, trim the edges to make it even.
Spread the ingredients over the meat and roll it up jelly roll fashion.
Tie firmly with a strong cord so it will hold the roll.
Place the meat in kettle of boiling salted water or broth.
Allow to simmer until the meat is tender.
Remove from water and cool in refrigerator.
Slice thin and serve on open-faced sandwiches.

title: cabbage bread
directions: Remove bread from freezer and allow to thaw and rise.
When risen, knead and roll out.

title: ma mapes clove cake
directions: Work butter until creamy.
Add sugar.
Beat eggs; mix with butter and sugar.
Sift flour, cinnamon, cloves and salt.
Beat 1/3 of flour and 1/2 cup of milk with creamy mixture.
Mix soda with rest of milk and add with flour to mixture; mix well.
Pour into greased Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Cool 10 minutes in pan.
Keeps well.

title: crunchy jumbles(cookies)
directions: Mix in usual manner and bake in 350° oven for 12 minutes. Makes 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: miniature cheesecakes
directions: Blend softened cream cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Place each vanilla wafer in bottom of foil cupcake paper and put in cupcake pan.
Divide batter evenly between cupcake papers.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Top with pie filling.

title: macaroon kisses
directions: Beat egg whites until frothy.
Add gradually the sugar.
Beat until stiff and glossy.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls 2 inches apart onto ungreased brown paper.
Bake at 325° about 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Place paper of macaroon kisses on damp towel.
Steam will loosen cookies.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: cheese grits
directions: Cook grits as directed on package:
1 cup grits to 4 cups water.
Add other ingredients and put into casserole dish.
Bake for 40 minutes at 325°.
Sprinkle, after cooked, with sharp cheese and paprika.

title: chicken italiano
directions: Combine melted margarine and oil in a shallow baking dish. In separate flat dish, mix together oregano, garlic powder, paprika and bread crumbs.
Dip chicken pieces in margarine-oil mixture.
Then roll each piece in seasoned crumbs, coating evenly. Place in shallow baking dish.
Bake uncovered in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: little cheddar meat loaves
directions: Shape into 8 small loaves.
Bake at 350 for 45 minutes or until done.

title: raspberry pie
directions: Cook the water, sugar, cornstarch and salt until clear. Remove from heat.
Add the jello.
Fill a 10-inch baked pie crust with fresh berries; pour filling over berries.
Refrigerate.
Top with whipped cream.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream butter and 1 cup sugar together until light and fluffy. Add eggs, separately.
Add vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking soda and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Put French fried onion rings on last ten minutes or so of baking time.

title: quick fondant
directions: Combine milk and vanilla in a medium mixing bowl.
Gradually stir in sugar, stirring until smooth.
Shape fondant into balls. Roll in colored sprinkles.
Yields 1 1/4 pounds candy.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add
melted
oleo, sugar and vinegar.
Beat well. Add pecans, coconut and raisins.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Good!

title: ham dip(food processor)
directions: Put all ingredients in food processor and blend for a few seconds.
Serve with crackers or sliced vegetables.

title: coffee
directions: Mix the coffee in equal portions to milk and serve hot.
If weaker Cafe Au Lait is desired, mix 1 part coffee to 3 parts milk. Top with whipped cream.
Serve with sugar.

title: vegetable lasagna roll-ups
directions: Cook lasagna 12 to 15 minutes or until tender.
Drain and dry on paper towel.

title: meat casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion and pepper in tablespoon of fat.
Add tomatoes, soup, beef stock, salt, pepper and sugar to meat mixture.
Mix well, then place noodles or macaroni in bottom of casserole dish.

title: elaine's zucchini bars
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in greased, floured jelly roll pan.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes in 350° oven.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: In a large bowl, combine cake mix, instant pudding mix, eggs, oil and milk.
Beat until well blended.
Fold in grated German chocolate (except 1/2 cup) and mix.
Fold in chocolate chips. Pour into well-greased tube pan and bake a 350 degrees for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes and remove from pan.
Sprinkle powdered sugar over the cake, then sprinkle the 1/4 cup grated chocolate.

title: pop-up bread
directions: Mix 1 1/2 cups flour and package of dry yeast together and set aside.
Heat at low until warm the oil, milk, water, sugar and salt.
Add this to yeast and flour; beat 2 minutes on medium speed. Add eggs and 1 1/2 cups flour (a little more may be needed).
Beat 1 minute on medium speed or until dough is elastic.
Divide into well-greased 1 pound coffee cans.
Cover with lids.
Let rise 1 hour until dough is 1/2-inch below top of can.
Remove lids and bake 35 minutes at 375°.
Cool 15 minutes in cans before serving.

title: puppy chow
directions: In a microwave or in a double boiler on the stove top, melt peanut butter, chocolate chips and margarine together.
Stir until smooth.
Pour over cereal and stir until all is coated.
Put powdered sugar in a clean bag and pour in cereal.
Close bag and shake until all cereal is coated.

title: chicken mushroom casserole
directions: Saute mushrooms and onion in butter.
Add chicken.
Saute 4 to 5 minutes.
Set aside.
In a glass casserole, mix soup and milk. Add chicken mixture and half of the fried onions.
Mix well.
Top with remaining fried onions.
Cook at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: crispy oven fried chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a large baking pan with cooking spray.
In a pie plate, mix buttermilk and pepper sauce.
On wax paper, mix dry ingredients.
In custard cup, mix butter and garlic.
Dip into buttermilk, then flour mixture.
Bake for 45 minutes or until crispy.
Makes 6 servings.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream oil and sugar.
Add egg yolks, mashed bananas, flour, soda and salt.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Add nuts.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool completely and wrap.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch well.
Add vinegar and cloves.
Bring to a boil.
Drain beets and pour into boiling sauce.
Simmer for 20 minutes.

title: fish cake patties
directions: Mix all ingredients well and form into patties; fry.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown meat in pan with onion; drain cooked spaghetti.
Add ingredients as given.
After it has cooked in the pan a short time, put in baking pan and cover with grated cheese and sprinkle with a little paprika.
Bake 1 hour in a slow oven.

title: aunt peggy's bar cookies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients until crumbly.
Reserve 3/4 cup crumbs. Add to remainder, water, butter (margarine) and eggs.
Beat 2 minutes.
Stir in chocolate chips (semi-sweet).
Spread in large 1/2-inch deep cookie pan (greased and floured).
Sprinkle with reserved crumbs.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Combine dry ingredients; cut in shortening.
Stir in yeast and buttermilk.
Roll and cut as desired.
Bake at 425° until done.

title: coconut creme pie
directions: Mix together and bake at 450° until lightly browned.
Makes 3 crusts.

title: zucchini a la grill
directions: Slice zucchini lengthwise into slices 1/4-inch thick.
Mix remaining ingredients and brush on zucchini slices.
Grill over hot coals until they begin to brown and soften.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: Select medium sized baking potatoes.
Scrub skins and bake in medium oven until tender.
Cool to touch.
Remove a slice from the top side; scoop out the inside, season and mash as for mashed potatoes.
Refill the shells, leaving the top of filling rough. Place in shallow pan in hot oven to reheat and brown the top. Serve very hot.
A bit of Cheddar cheese and/or bacon bits sprinkled on top is good.

title: peppermint cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream shortening and sugars.
Add the eggs, one at a time.
Beat in vanilla and stir in dry ingredients.
Stir in crushed candies.
Shape into a 15 inch roll; wrap in plastic wrap and put in refrigerator for 4 hours.
Unwrap and cut into 1/8 slices.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheets and bake at 375° for 6-8 minutes.
Remove and cool.

title: fresh apple cake 1
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add beaten eggs and beat well.
Sift together dry ingredients. Add to creamed mixture.
Blend well. Stir in apples, nuts, raisins, coconut and vanilla.
Bake in floured and greased tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken in Dutch oven half full of water with the salt until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken and set aside.
To chicken broth in pan, add the 1 can broth and the soups.
Stir until smooth.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Keep simmering while you make the dumplings.

title: hearty chicken casserole
directions: Blend soup and milk.
Mix remaining ingredients, except crumbs.
Top with crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: frozen christmas salad
directions: Soften cream cheese; blend with mayonnaise.
Add fruits with nuts.
Fold whipped cream into mixture.
Spoon into loaf pan. Cover tightly; freeze.
Serves 12.

title: wild duck jambalaya
directions: Brown duck and sausages in melted butter and olive oil.
Add onions, bell peppers and garlic.
Saute for 2 minutes, stirring continuously.
Add all ingredients, except rice and simmer for 45 minutes, stirring often.
Check duck for tenderness.
Add rice and more chicken stock, if necessary.
Cover and place in lowest heat level and cook for 15 minutes or until rice is nice and fluffy.

title: cauliflower soup
directions: In a large kettle, add cauliflower, water and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer until very tender.
Add bouillon cubes, margarine and sausage; bring to a boil.
Stir in Cream of Wheat. Cook 5 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients together except cheese.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch glass dish with Pam and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Top with grated cheese and bake 30 minutes.
tags: cream of potato and celery soup

title: wacky cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Into large mixing bowl, sift flour, sugar, cocoa, soda and salt.
Mix thoroughly.
Make three holes in flour mixture.
Into one hole, put vinegar, into the second the vanilla and into the third the oil.
Pour water over all and mix just until smooth. Put into pan and bake for 35 minutes.

title: patrick's irish soda bread
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together, then mix the sour cream, eggs, raisins and caraway seed into flour mixture.
Shape into round cake pan.
Cut an "X" into the top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes, or when tested, comes out clean.

title: baked beans
directions: Drain off liquid from beans.
Fry strips of bacon.
Crumble the bacon in the beans.
Pour the grease in the beans.
Put all ingredients in a bowl and mix well.
Put in pan and bake 1 hour at 350°.
May slice a can of treat meat and put on top of beans.

title: party puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease 2 small baking sheets.
Place water, butter and salt in a 2-quart saucepan.
Heat over high heat until butter melts and mixture boils.
Reduce heat to low; vigorously stir in flour until mixture forms a ball and leaves sides of pan.
Remove from heat; cool a minute or two.
Beat eggs into flour mixture one at a time.
Drop mixture by scant tablespoonfuls 2 inches apart onto baking sheets.
Bake 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cut slit in each shell and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
Pour 1/4 to 1/2 batter into a 9 x 12-inch or a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli onion soup
directions: In large saucepan, heat oil.
Add onion and saute over medium heat for 3 minutes.
Add water and bouillon cubes.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally, until cubes are dissolved. Gradually add noodles and salt so that bouillon mixture continues to boil.
Cook, uncovered, for 3 minutes, stirring occasionally. Stir in broccoli and garlic powder.
Cook 4 minutes more.
Add milk, cheese and pepper and continue cooking until cheese melts, stirring constantly.
Yield:
Makes about 4 quarts or 12 servings.

title: cream nut fudge(recipe over 100 years old)
directions: Mix cream, sugar and syrup.
Cook slow, stirring occasionally. Cook between soft and hard ball stage or 240° on candy thermometer.
It takes 50 to 60 minutes at low boil.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Cream margarine, sugar, vanilla and almond flavoring.
Beat in egg.
Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Divide into thirds, roll and cut in shapes.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet on upper oven rack at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes or until very lightly browned on bottom of cookies.
Let set on cookie sheet a few minutes before removing.
Do not overbake.
Frost when cool.

title: berry punch
directions: Place strawberries and syrup in blender. Process until smooth. Pour over punch bowl. Add remaining ingredients.

title: popovers
directions: Sift together flour and salt; gradually add milk to flour in a bowl.
Add melted butter.
Beat batter for 2 minutes with mixer. Fill muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake in 450° oven for 14 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake 20 minutes more.
Serve hot.
Can be filled with creamed vegetables or meat or served alone.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Let mixture stand for 15 minutes.
Pour pecans into mixture, coating well.
Dip out and place on cookie sheet.
Bake for 1 hour at 250°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 5 minutes; drain.
Mix soup, eggs, mayonnaise and cheese with broccoli and pour into greased casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and cover with crushed potato chips.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons of melted butter over chips and return to oven for 15 minutes to finish baking and to brown.

title: creamy peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook margarine, sugar and evaporated milk in a heavy large saucepan to the soft ball stage.
Be careful, this scorches easily.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter and 1 cup of marshmallow cream.
Stir until creamy.
Pour into well greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
While warm, score candy.
Let cool.
Cut and put in between layers of foil or waxed paper.

title: peaches and cream dessert
directions: In a bowl, stir together flour, pudding mix and baking powder. Combine egg, milk and oleo (or butter); add to dry ingredients. Mix well and spread in a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.

title: easy brownies(club member: luke robinson)
directions: Place all ingredients, except pecans, in large bowl; beat at medium speed for 3 minutes. Stir in pecans. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cut into 24 squares while warm, but leave in pan until cool.

title: egg nog pie
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Warm the egg nog over direct low heat and stir in the softened gelatin.
Gently heat until gelatin is completely dissolved.
Chill until partially set, and then beat until smooth.
Beat sugar, salt and flavorings into whipped cream.
Gently fold whipped cream into egg nog and pour into prepared pie shell.
Chill 2 or more hours before serving. Garnish with grated nutmeg, toasted slivered almonds and more whipped cream, if desired.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring butter, shortening, cocoa and water to boil.
Add sugar, flour and remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: texas hash
directions: Cook ground beef, onion and pepper until beef is browned; drain.
Add remaining ingredients except rice and cheese.
Stir well.
Pour into casserole, cover and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: poor boy fillet
directions: Chop vegetables; set aside.
Panfry bacon and drain on paper towels; set aside.
Spread meat on paper approximately 7 1/4 x 11-inches about 1/4 to 3/8 inch thick.
Sprinkle with lemon pepper. Mix onion, bell pepper, mushrooms and olives together.
Spread over meat and sprinkle cheese on top.
Roll up meat from long side and cut into 5 equal pieces.
Wrap each with 1 piece of bacon.
Secure with a toothpick.
Place on grill and cook to desired doneness. Serves 5.

title: 1939 german spaghetti
directions: Brown bacon, onion and garlic.
Pour in tomato sauce.
Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
Drain.
Add cooked spaghetti to bacon mixture.
Mix and serve.
Serves 6.

title: southern baked beans
directions: Place beans in a greased, shallow ovenproof dish.
Cover the top with bacon or skinned, sliced franks.
Bake, covered, 30 minutes.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes more.

title: kay isbell's chocolate mousse
directions: Make crust by combining flour, pecans and oleo.
Mix well and press in bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°. Cool completely.
Blend cream cheese and powdered sugar until fluffy.
Fold in 1 cup whipped topping.
Blend well and spread on cooled crust.
Chill.

title: chocolate dessert
directions: Mix 1 cup flour and 1/2 cup margarine until crumbly and press in bottom of a dripper pan (9 x 13-inch).
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes and let cool.
Cream together powdered sugar and cream cheese, then add 2/3 of a large carton of Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled crust.
Combine the milk and large package of instant chocolate pudding as directed on package.
Spread over cream cheese mixture.
Spread remaining Cool Whip over top of dessert and top with nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: naomi's coconut delight
directions: 1st Mixture:
Mix flour, butter and chopped pecans and press down in long pan.
Bake about 20 minutes or until light brown; let cool.

title: tamale pie
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Pour off grease, then add celery soup, refried beans and picante sauce.
On top of tortillas, add a layer of mixture.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Keep adding layers of tortilla shells, ground beef mixture and cheese until all are gone.
Be sure cheese is the last thing on top.
Cook in microwave on High for 15 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Chop all ingredients; mix with cream cheese. Form into a ball. Serve with a variety of crackers.

title: sunday dinner chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except boned chicken to desired consistency.
(I leave my mixture rather loose to keep moist when baked.)
Pour into greased baking dish. Add boned chicken and press into mixture.
Bake at 400° to desired thickness and brownness.
Enjoy.

title: sloppy joes potato topper
directions: In a 10-inch skillet over medium heat, cook beef with pepper until beef is browned.
Drain off any fat.
Stir in soup mix, water and ketchup; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover; simmer for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Spoon over potatoes. Garnish with cheese.
Serves 4.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Add egg, bread and milk.
Mix in next 5 ingredients.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in flour and brown in oil in large skillet.
Prepare gravy according to directions on package, blend in mayonnaise.
Add to meatballs, heat and serve.
Makes about 40 meatballs.

title: philly 3-step cherry cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese with sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Pour into one prepared graham cracker crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until the center is almost set.
Cool.
Refrigerate for at least 3 hours.
Spread with pie filling.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cream puffs
directions: Combine Crisco, salt and water.
Heat to boiling.
Sift flour; measure and add to boiling water.
Beat vigorously until mixture leaves sides of saucepan and does not cling to spoon.
Remove from fire.
Add the unbeaten eggs, one at a time, beating until mixture is smooth each time.
Drop by tablespoons into well-oiled muffin tins.
Bake 40 minutes in hot oven (400°).
Makes 12 servings. When cooled, fill with favorite filling and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: chicken verdicchio(chicken with artichoke hearts)
directions: Place flour in a plastic bag.
Put chicken in bag and shake. Melt 1/2 stick of butter in frypan.
Brown chicken,
about 1 minute on each side for 6 to 8 minutes.
Remove chicken.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Line bottom and side of 2-quart baking dish with tortillas.
Combine soup, green pepper, onion, chili powder and garlic in medium bowl.
Mix well.
Layer half the soup mixture, chicken and cheese in prepared dish. Add layers of remaining tortillas, soup mixture, chicken and cheese. Top with tomatoes. Bake for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: cranberry-sweet potatoes
directions: Arrange the sweet potatoes flat side down in greased 9 x 13 baking dish.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt butter; add corn, sour cream and corn bread mix.
Mix well.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake 45 minutes until top is golden brown at 350°.

title: unbelievable peanut butter cookies
directions: Roll into balls; press down and bake 10 minutes.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Put oranges, apples (washed and cut into sections and seeds taken out) through food grinder.
Grind up cranberries; add to apples and oranges.
Add the sugar.
Stir and chill 6 to 8 hours, in refrigerator.

title: nutty crunch bars
directions: Combine brownie mix, egg yolks and water.
Stir until smooth. Spread in pan (8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch).
Sprinkle coconut and nuts over batter.
Combine brown sugar and egg whites; pour over coconut and nuts. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes (8 x 8-inch) or 25 to 35 minutes (9 x 9-inch).
Cool and cut in squares.

title: gazpacho
directions: In blender or processor, combine 1 cup V-8 juice and next 7 ingredients at medium speed for a few seconds.
Add tomato, cucumber, pepper and onion.
Process until tomato is evenly chopped, but do not puree.
Add remaining V-8.
Pour into 1-quart container and chill for 4 hours.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: onions au gratin
directions: Mix onions, 4 cups cheese, flour and 6 tablespoons butter. Pour into a 2-quart casserole. Melt 1 tablespoon butter and mix with bread crumbs. Sprinkle remaining cheese on top of onions, followed by bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 8 to 10.

title: southern coffee punch
directions: Combine cold coffee, milk, kahlua and sugar in a large bowl. Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Chill thoroughly.

title: crazy filled cake
directions: Put flour, sugar, cocoa, salt, soda, vinegar, salad oil, vanilla and water in bowl and mix until smooth. Grease and flour 9 x 13 inch cake pan and put 1/2 batter in pan. Then beat cream cheese, eggs and sugar together and add coconut, chips and nuts. Now pour this on top of batter in pan and top with remaining cake batter. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: waffles
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together. Add the beaten yolk. Last of all, add stiffly beaten egg white.
Pour on hot grill.

title: orange fruit cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients; set aside.
Combine remainder of ingredients.
Combine both mixtures and bake at 250° for 1 hour and then at 300° for 2 hours.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Take sour
cream,
mushroom
soup, eggs and cheese; mix together. Take
spinach and lobster; add to mixture.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: autumn apple salad
directions: In a saucepan, combine pineapple and sugar.
Bring to a boil and boil for 3 minutes.
Add gelatin; stir until dissolved.
Add cream cheese; stir until mixture is thoroughly combined.
Cool. Fold in apples, nuts, celery and Cool Whip.
Pour into a 9-inch square pan.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares and serve on lettuce leaves.

title: girl scout cookies
directions: Melt chocolate; add peppermint and stir.
Dip cracker in mixture and place on wax paper on cookie sheet.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: golden cauliflower(microwave)
directions: Place whole head of washed cauliflower in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Add water.
Cover and microwave on High 8 to 9 minutes.
Melt butter in a 2 cup glass measure.
Stir in flour, mustard and pepper.
Gradually add broth.
Microwave on High 2 to 3 minutes, stirring every minute or so.
Add cheese and hot sauce. Stir until cheese is melted.
Pour over cauliflower.

title: colonial gingerbread
directions: Grease and flour
a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
In large bowl, measure all
ingredients
and
mix at low speed until blended. Pour batter
into
pan
and bake 1 hour.
Cool.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: breakfast puffs
directions: Beat first three ingredients together thoroughly.
Sift together next four ingredients.
Stir in alternately with milk. Pour into well-greased and floured tiny muffin tins (half full). Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: 4 layer dessert
directions: Melt butter and mix with other ingredients.
Put in baking dish (large) and bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: russian tea
directions: Use heaping tablespoonful in a cup of boiling water.

title: cheese pies
directions: Mix cheeses, eggs, salt and pepper.
Cut filo into 5-inch strips.
Butter strip.
Add same amount of cheese; fold sides a little.
Butter again, then fold like a flag or any shape desired. Bake at 450° until golden brown, 10 minutes.

title: layered 24 hour salad
directions: Layer the first 5 ingredients in a square or rectangle dish. Cover with a good layer of mayonnaise or salad dressing, cheese and bacon (sprinkled over top).
Seal with Saran Wrap or tight lid.
To serve, do not mix but cut in squares.
Make sure all vegetables are drained well before assembly.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Mix corn meal, flour, shortening, milk and eggs.
Bake at 350° for 3/4 hour.
Crumble bread when cold.
Add onion, toast and seasoning and moisten with stock to desired consistency.
Makes large aluminum pan.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Pour flour and sugar together; cut in shortening.
Add yeast and milk.
Knead on a floured board.
Roll out dough.
Cut biscuits and brush with melted butter.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: english toffee cookie bars
directions: Cream the first three ingredients together.
Add the flour, toffee bits and nuts.
Spread on ungreased jellyroll pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25-30 minutes.
Cut while warm and remove when cool. These are a quick alternative to cookies and a sure hit at the bake sale!

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: In a large bowl, cream together cream cheese, butter, milk, salt and vanilla.
Gradually beat in powdered sugar.
If mixture seems too stiff, add a few drops of milk to make it the right consistency for spreading in pretty swirls.
Make enough to frost two 8 or 9-inch layers.

title: quick and easy green bean casserole
directions: Mix the green beans, mushroom soup and half of the fried onions in a 2-quart glass casserole.
Top with remaining onions. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until heated through.

title: fiesta taco dip
directions: Mix sour cream, bean dip and taco seasoning. Spread onto cookie sheet and refrigerate overnight. Sprinkle remaining ingredients the next day before serving.

title: pineapple pretzel salad
directions: Mix together the pretzels, margarine and 1/2 cup sugar.
Press mixture into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake for 5 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Cook together the pineapple, juice and cornstarch until mixture is clear.
Blend together the cream cheese, whipped topping and sugar.
Add cream cheese layer on top of the crumb crust.
Spread pineapple on top of cheese.
Sprinkle with coconut, if desired.
Dot with maraschino cherries.
Chill.

title: peach cream cobbler
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in 1 1/2-quart round baking dish.
Cut butter in and pat firmly on bottom and halfway up sides of dish. Arrange peaches on top, cut side down.
Mix and sprinkle sugar and cinnamon on top.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.
Mix milk and egg yolks and pour on and bake 30 minutes longer.
Cool 30 minutes.
May be served warm or cold and with scoop of ice cream, if desired. Serves 8.

title: apple cake
directions: Place apples on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix eggs, sugar and oil.
Add dry ingredients, walnuts and 1 teaspoon vanilla; spread over apples.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Frost while warm.

title: spanish rice
directions: Saute rice mixture as package directs.
Stir in 2 cups water, ham, onion, tomatoes, garlic powder, hot pepper and seasoning packet.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.

title: shrimp or crawfish casserole
directions: Melt butter; saute onion, green onion, bell pepper, tomato and shrimp or crawfish until cooked.
Add cooked rice and mix; put in a casserole dish.
Bake at 450° until bubbly and turn off heat.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine soup, sour cream, salt and onion.
Add to potatoes and mix well.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Mix together.
Simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: caramel dip(great for apples)
directions: Mix well until smooth.
Serve at room temperature.
Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: chex party mix
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
In open roasting pan, melt margarine in oven.
Stir in seasoned salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Gradually add cereals, nuts and pretzels, stirring until all pieces are evenly coated.
Bake 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Spread on absorbent paper to cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: pinta calata cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on box and bake in 13 x 9-inch pan or baking dish.
When done, punch holes in cake and pour over hot cake the Eagle Brand milk and large can of cream of coconut.
Cool cake, then add carton of Cool Whip and sprinkle coconut over this. Keep refrigerated.

title: tortillas
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Blend in shortening and water; knead.
Let sit covered for 15 minutes.
Roll into balls and roll out.

title: oven porcupines
directions: Heat oven at 350°.
Brown ground beef with chopped onion, then drain.
Mix meat with the rest of the ingredients.
Shape the mixture into balls and place in an ungreased baking dish.

title: potatoes supreme for 50 people
directions: Cook and dice potatoes.
Make a gravy with rest of ingredients; pour over potatoes and place in oven at 325° for 1 hour or until thickened.
If raw potatoes are used, cook 6 hours in 300° oven.

title: chocolate eclair dessert
directions: Line 13 x 9-inch pan with graham crackers.
Mix pudding and milk until thick.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread over graham crackers.
Top with layer of graham crackers, then frost. Refrigerate.

title: veal marsala
directions: Take veal and pound it round and out.
Roll veal in flour and dip into eggs.
Add oil to skillet and fry veal until brown. Remove veal and keep warm.
In another skillet, melt butter.
Then add wine and parsley.
Gently mix sauce until it starts to thicken, then add veal for 2 minutes.
Serve with pasta.
Serves 2.

title: oatmeal apple raisin muffins
directions: Beat together the egg, oil, sugar, milk and oats.
Let stand while you chop the apple.
Add the raisins, apple, flour, baking powder, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Mix just to moisten.
Pour into 12 greased and floured muffin tins 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes. Test at 15 minutes. They bake fast. Delicious.

title: salmon ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except nuts and parsley.
Shape in ball. Refrigerate approximately 2 to 4 hours.
Remove from refrigerator and roll in the mixture of
nuts and parsley.
Place on platter with lemon curls.
Makes 1 large ball or 2 small balls.

title: chocolate chocolate chip cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients, except chocolate chips; add wet ingredients and mix.
Pour into 9 x 13 pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over top.
Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean, about 35 minutes.

title: strawberry pudding freeze
directions: Pour milk into bowl and add pudding mix. Beat slowly with rotary beater or at lowest speed of electric mixer until blended. Blend in whipped topping and strawberries.
Pour into 9-inch square pan and freeze until firm. Serve in ice cream cones or dessert dishes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix and bake for
hour at 325°.
Serves 8 to 10.
If you are not a big sweet potato fan, you will love the taste of this!

title: chicken piccata
directions: Dredge cutlets in flour.
In skillet over medium-high heat, heat oil and butter (or margarine).
Saute chicken until golden brown on both sides.
Add garlic, wine and lemon juice.
Cover; simmer until tender (10 minutes or so).
Remove chicken to plate; keep warm.
Boil sauce in skillet until slightly thick.
Add parsley; stir and spoon over chicken.

title: cranberry chicken loaf salad
directions: Soften gelatine in cold water.
Mush sauce; add juice and heat until melted.
Add gelatine; chill until thick.
Add celery and nuts.
Pour into a 9 1/2 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Chill until set.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger.
Drain grease and add spaghetti sauce mix, onion and tomato sauce.
Let simmer.

title: oven-fried chicken parmesan
directions: Combine stuffing, cheese, parsley and garlic.
Dip chicken pieces in butter.
Roll in crumb mixture.
Place chicken, skin side up and not touching, in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch glass baking dish. Sprinkle with remaining butter and crumb mixture.
Bake until tender.
Do not turn.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Blend confectioners sugar, cocoa, salt, milk and vanilla together in a 1 1/2-quart dish.
Top with butter.
Microwave at High 2 minutes.
Stir smooth and then blend in chopped nuts.
Pour in buttered 8-inch square dish.
Cool.

title: raffa corn pudding
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Add all ingredients.
Beat whites until stiff.
Fold into corn mixture.
Pour into greased casserole. Place in pan of water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Arrange in glass dish.
Place chicken on top of broccoli.
Combine soups, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Salt to taste.
Pour over the chicken and sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Combine bread crumbs and butter and sprinkle over all.
Dust lightly with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: low-fat cupcakes
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients in a large bowl.
In a 2 cup measure, mix milk, applesauce and egg.
Combine liquid and dry ingredients, mixing just to combine.
Batter will be lumpy.
Fill muffin cups that have been sprayed with cooking spray, 3/4 full.
Bake for 20 minutes at 425°.
Muffins should be golden brown.
For children under 4, omit raisins.

title: eggless sweet potato pie
directions: Cream the butter and sugar in mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Add milk and sweet potatoes alternately, beating well after each addition.
Beat in orange rind and ginger.
Pour into pie shell. Bake at 300° for 45 minutes or until filling is set and pie is golden brown.
Serve warm with whipped cream.
Yields 8 servings.

title: party sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together; roll in small balls.
Bake on cookie sheet at 375° for 30 minutes or until done.
Makes about 50 or 60 balls.

title: chocolate candy cheesecake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Press mixture evenly onto bottom and 1 1/2-inches up sides of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Sprinkle chopped candy bars (chops easier if frozen first) evenly over bottom and set aside.

title: warm spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in a medium bowl.
Cover tightly and microwave on medium for 9 to 12 minutes.
Stir every few minutes until cheese is melted and mixture is warm throughout.
Serve warm with crackers, bagel chips or breadsticks.
Can be served in hollowed rye, Italian or French loaves.

title: grandma's moist dark cake
directions: In a deep saucepan, boil together sugar, water, lard, salt, raisins and spices for 5 minutes.
Set aside to cool.

title: grandma henkelman's 1-2-3-4 rhubarb pie
directions: Mix together well and pour over 3 cups of cut up rhubarb in a 9 inch pie crust.
Cover with lattice top crust and pinch the edges.
Brush with milk and sprinkle sugar over the top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 50 minutes to 1 hour.

title: glazed chicken
directions: Mix first five ingredients.
Spoon over chicken and onions in roasting pan.
Bake about 45 minutes, basting occasionally.

title: quick chicken supper
directions: Mix all together in electric skillet except potato chips. Simmer for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle potato chips on top.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: yvonne's salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour dressing over salad mix.
Fresh vegetables can be added.
Makes 10 - 15 servings.

title: frosty strawberry squares
directions: Make crumb mixture:
Combine flour, brown sugar, nuts and margarine.
Spread in a jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally to make crumbs.
When cooled, sprinkle 2/3 of them in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Reserve remainder for topping.

title: banana sweet potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 1-quart casserole.
In a mixing bowl, blend potatoes, 1/3 cup butter, nuts, coconut and 3/4 cup sugar.
Spread half the potato mixture in casserole.
Top with bananas. Spread remaining potato mixture on bananas.
Sprinkle with cornflakes, remaining butter and remaining sugar. Bake for 20 minutes.

title: french silk chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler.
Cool.
Cream butter. Gradually add powdered sugar, beating until mixture is smooth, light and fluffy.
Add chocolate and vanilla to this mixture; blend well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Chill 1 to 2 hours.

title: gum drop bread
directions: In a bowl combine biscuit mix and sugar.
In another bowl beat egg and milk.
Add to dry ingredients and stir well.
Add nuts and gumdrops and stir until just mixed.
Pour into 3 greased 5 3/4 in. x 2 in. x 3 in. loaf pans.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near center comes out clean. Cool for 10 minutes and remove from pans to wire racks to
cool completely. Yield 3 mini loaves.

title: stuffed green pepper
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Cut thin slice from stem of each green pepper.
Wash and clean out seeds.
Cook in boiling water for 5 minutes and drain.
Stuff peppers lightly with meat mixture. Stand upright in small baking dish.
Bake, covered, for 45 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes more.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Break cake into chunks.
Place into pan.
Mix Jell-O as directed.
Pour over cake.
Chill until firm.
Mix Cool Whip and cream cheese together.
Drain pineapple and mix with Cool Whip mixture.
Pour over cake and chill again.

title: orange rice mold
directions: Put the first 3 ingredients together and let stand until slightly thickened.
Add pineapple.
Let cool again until slightly thickened.
Whip the whipping cream and add.
Fold in powdered sugar.
Dream Whip can be used instead of whipping cream.

title: orange pineapple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together for about 2 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured pans.
Bake about 20 minutes at 350°.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients, except tomato paste.
Make small meatballs; cook for 8 to 10 minutes.
Pour off fat.
Add the tomato paste; simmer for 10 minutes.

title: easy mexican casseroles
directions: Using two 2 to 3-quart deep casserole dishes, layer tortillas, refried beans, cheese and olives, then layer a tortilla, chili, cheese and olives a couple of times before repeating, using refried bean layer followed by chili layers, topping off each of two casseroles with cheese and olives.
Bake in 350° oven until heated through and cheese is melted, approximately 30 minutes.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt butter over low heat.
Stir in flour, salt, pepper and mustard until smooth.
Gradually stir in milk.
Stirring constantly, cook over medium heat until thickened (about 10 minutes).
Remove from heat.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups cheese.
Pour over macaroni; mix well.
Put remaining cheese over top.
Bake in a 375° oven for 25 minutes.

title: banana berry french toast
directions: Mix the first four ingredients together and set aside.
Take a large mouth glass and press out rounds of bread (1 per slice). Dip 1 round in batter.
Place strawberries and banana on top.
Dip 1 round in batter and place on top of fruit (sandwich style). Place in nonstick skillet and cook until golden brown on each side.
Garnish plate with fruit and enjoy.
Makes 4.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Mix margarine, flour and pecans with your hands.
Press into bottom of baking dish.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour; cool.
Combine cream cheese, sugar and lemon juice.
Fold in Cool Whip and lightly spread on baked pecan mixture.
Add 2 drops of food coloring to cherry pie filling and spread this on top of Cool Whip.
Place in refrigerator 1 hour before serving.

title: tandy cake
directions: Beat the first 3 ingredients together.
Add flour and baking powder and mix.
Add milk and butter (butter melted in milk). Beat.
Mixture will be thin.
Bake in sheet pan sprayed with Pam at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
When done, spread warm cake with peanut butter and refrigerate until set and cool.

title: 2-step chicken pecan salad
directions: In large bowl, combine first 7 ingredients.
Stir together until well mixed.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours or overnight.
One hour before serving, add pecans and mayonnaise. Stir well and again refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: cranberry apple warm-up(wonderful on a cold day for guests or the entire family.)
directions: In 1-quart casserole, mix juice and spices.
Microwave on High for 8 minutes, stirring once.
Pour into mugs and garnish each with an apple wedge.
Serves 4.

title: raspberry ribbon pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin and sugar in boiling water in a bowl.
Add raspberries and stir until thawed.
Stir in lemon juice.
Chill in refrigerator until mixture is very thick or almost set.

title: beef enchiladas with green sauce
directions: Cook ground round until browned.
Add seasoning.
Mix together beef, Cheddar cheese, eggs, onion, rice and chilies.
Set aside. Pour 1 can sauce into shallow pan; dip tortillas into sauce and fill with beef mixture and roll up and put into a greased baking dish.
Cover enchiladas with other can of sauce and more grated cheese.
Bake in oven for approximately 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Crush crackers, add melted butter and mix.
Make crust in 9 x 13 inch glass pan.
Pat down.
Mix Eagle brand milk and thawed orange juice together in large bowl.
Add drained oranges and Cool Whip.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour in pan over crust and chill.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Cover sweet potatoes in salt water and hard boil for 5 minutes.
Pour all the water off.
Add butter, sugar and nutmeg. Cover with tight lid and reduce heat as low as possible.
Cook about 1 hour or until syrup thickens.

title: ramen pride noodle salad
directions: Mix sugar, oil, vinegar and beef seasoning packet. Set aside.

title: lee's carrot honey salad
directions: Cut carrots 1/8-inch thick.
Boil 4 to 7 minutes until tender-crisp.
Heat remaining ingredients until combined.
Pour over drained carrots; toss to coat.
May be served warm or cold.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: In a large bowl, mix ingredients with a wire whisk.
Spoon mixture into pie crust.
Freeze 4 hours.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of 9-inch loaf pan. Mix all ingredients; beat by hand for 30 seconds.
Pour into pan. Bake 55 to 65 minutes.
Toothpick test for doneness.
Cool slightly before removing from pan.
Keeps one week in refrigerator when wrapped or covered.
Recipe can also be used to make 2 smaller loaves by using 8 1/2-inch loaf pans.
Bake these 50 to 60 minutes. Aluminum "shiny" pans work best as the darker "Ekco" pans make the loaf too dark.

title: chicken milano
directions: Prepare orzo.
Cut breast meat into chunks.
In 10-inch skillet, cook over medium heat in hot butter the onion and garlic until tender.
Add chicken and cook until lightly brown on all sides.
Stir in tomato soup (undiluted) and remaining ingredients. Over high heat, cook until boiling, then reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer about 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve over orzo.
Easy!!

title: italian bean bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine drained beans, tomato sauce, mustard,
dried
onion,
garlic
salt and pepper.
Turn mixture into
a
1-quart
casserole. Cover and bake in oven for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle
cheese
atop.
Bake, uncovered, 1 to 2 minutes more or until cheese is melted.
Makes 6 servings.

title: limeade float
directions: Prepare ahead:
Lime sherbet (round container is prettier for serving).
Thinly slice sherbet (1/2-inch or less thick).
Put slice between foil or plastic sheets and freeze solidly.
When ready to serve, put a few ice cubes in bowl.
Add limeade and soda.
Float sherbet slices on top.
Add more, as needed.
Sherbet will melt while serving.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites
(room	temperature)
until very stiff. Beat in sugar (1 tablespoon
at a time).
Fold in chopped nuts and Nestle morsels.
Drop
on
greased	cookie sheet.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Put cookies	in
oven,
turn off heat and leave overnight. May substitute white
raisins or coconut for nuts. Also, may tint with 2
drops
red or green food coloring.	May double recipe.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries; add sugar and marshmallows and refrigerate overnight.
Next morning, whip the cream.
Add it, nuts and apples to cranberry mixture.
Stir all ingredients together.

title: ice cream cone cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake mix as directed on package. Pour 1/4 cup batter into ice cream cones, filling each about 1/2 full.
Place cones in rectangular or square pan.
Bake as directed on cake mix for cupcakes.
Cool; frost with frosting.
Makes about 30 cones.

title: shrimp creole
directions: In a medium skillet, melt butter and cook green pepper and celery until tender.
Add golden onion soup mix blended with reserved liquid and water, tomatoes and parsley.
Bring to a boil, then simmer covered, stirring occasionally, 20 minutes.
Add shrimp and cook 5 minutes or until shrimp are done.
Serve, if desired, with hot cooked rice.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream margarine and powdered sugar.
Add the vanilla and flour.
Cream well.
Drop by spoon onto an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes until lightly brown.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: In saucepan, over medium heat, in hot oil, cook celery and onion until tender-crisp, stirring occasionally.

title: alfie salad
directions: Toss salad and add your favorite dressing.

title: liver paste
directions: Melt butter and brown livers and onion for about 10 to 15 minutes; cool.
Put 1/2-inch water in blender and add liver mixture and rest of ingredients; blend until smooth. Season with salt and pepper.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Beat butter and shortening together.
Add sugar and mix until fluffy.
Beat in eggs, add dry ingredients with milk and vanilla. Stir in nuts.
Pour into 10 inch tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: very good snack canape
directions: Use equal parts of all ingredients.
Toast small slices of French bread on one side.
Place cheese mixture on other side and toast until lightly brown.

title: quick and easy pumpkin pie
directions: Pour milk into a bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat with wire whisk until well blended (1 to 2 minutes).
Mixture will be thick.
Stir in pumpkin with wire whisk; mix well.
Spread on crust. Refrigerate at least 3 hours.

title: tea cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients. Turn out on floured board. Roll in rolls as refrigerator cookies. Wrap and refrigerate overnight or until ready to cut.
Cut with electric knife.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: egg mcmuffinmicrowave
directions: Toast muffin. Cook bacon between paper towels (1 min per slice). Put beaten egg in custard cup, cook 30 sec. per egg. Assemble McMuffin. Melt cheese in microwave, if desired.

title: zesty broccoli - cauliflower gratin
directions: Combine bread crumbs and Cheddar cheese.
Stir bread crumb mixture well and set aside.
Steam the broccoli and cauliflower, covered, 4 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Drain vegetables and place in a 1 1/2-quart casserole coated with vegetable cooking spray.
Combine margarine, mustard and pepper in a small bowl.
Drizzle over broccoli and cauliflower and toss well. Sprinkle vegetables with the bread crumb mixture and bake at 425° for 8 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Yields 4 servings. Serving size:
1 cup.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: squash dressing
directions: Cook squash in small amount water.
Drain.
Mash and add 1 stick margarine.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Put in a buttered casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cel's rum cake
directions: Grease and flour tube pan.
Coarsely chop walnuts and sprinkle nuts in bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix, pudding mix, eggs, water, oil and rum.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Remove cake and let cool before placing on serving plate.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Wash and place chicken with 6 cups water into a large cooking pot.
Bring to a boil and lower heat to simmer.
Stew chicken until tender, about 30 to 40 minutes.
Remove chicken from broth and allow to cool.
Remove skin and pull chicken meat from the bone.
Cut meat into bite-size pieces.

title: rice and sausage casserole
directions: Cook sausage in skillet, stirring to crumble.
Drain well. Combine sausage, rice, apple, onion, celery, raisens, sugar, salt, allspice, cinnamon and pepper; spoon into buttered 2 quart baking dish.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes, or until thoroughly heated.
Makes 8 servings.

title: corn and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions on pkg.
Add other ingredients to rice, pour into buttered casserole.	Bake at 325° for about 45 minutes.
This can be made ahead of time and freeze.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Cover bottom of jelly roll pan with crescent rolls.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown, about 7 to 8 minutes.
Let cool 10 to 12 minutes.

title: grandmother's carolina meat pie
directions: Cube
meat and	brown
along
with
onion.
Add
water, ketchup, salt and pepper.
Add carrots. Cook about 30 minutes. Add potatoes
and a bit of cornstarch; cook until all vegetables
are tender and a thick consistency has been established. Cut a thin crust for top and bake until crust is done.

title: amish sugar cream pie
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine granulated sugar, salt and half and half.
Bring to boiling, stirring occasionally.

title: cheddar dip
directions: Mix all.
Serve with crackers or raw veggies.

title: santa's 7-up surprise
directions: Chill pineapple juice and 7-Up. Pour additional 7-Up into 2 ice cube trays, placing a maraschino cherry into each cube. Freeze.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Combine milk, sugar, salt and shortening; cool.
Put Sourdough Starter in large bowl.
Add cooled milk mixture; stir in flour to make pliable dough.
Turn out onto lightly floured board; knead for 1 or 2 minutes.
Place in greased bowl; brush with melted shortening.
Cover; let rise until double in bulk.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix pineapple, sugar, flour and cheese.
Spread a thin layer of Ritz crackers in a 8 x 11-inch or similar size pan.
Pour in pineapple mixture. Top with remaining crackers.
Drizzle margarine on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until crackers brown.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook ground beef and chopped onion in small amount of fat in a heavy skillet slowly until meat has turned its color.
Drain off fat.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: play dough
directions: Mix all ingredients except food coloring and cook until it pulls away from pan and forms ball.
Remove from heat.
Knead. Divide into smaller balls and add food coloring to make different color dough.
Stores good in tightly covered containers.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown hamburger meat, onion, salt, and pepper.
Add green beans and tomato soup.
Place in baking dish.

title: favorite lasagne
directions: Brown sausage.
Drain.
Add garlic, basil, tomatoes and tomato paste.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Cook noodles.
Beat eggs. Add cottage cheese, parsley flakes, salt and pepper.
