title: lloyds easy dip
directions: Saute onion in butter, add tomatoes, cubed cheese and sausage (drained).
Simmer 10 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: quick spinach medley
directions: Drain spinach well, pressing out excess liquid.
Cook bacon in skillet. Remove bacon. Set aside.
Saute onion and potatoes in drippings. Stir in marjoram, thyme and spinach.
Heat through. Crumble bacon and sprinkle over top.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: plainville turkey breasts in marsala wine
directions: Cut fillets into 1/2-inch slices.
Gently pound with tenderizer.
Combine eggs and milk in a shallow dish.
On a flat plate, combine bread crumbs, Parmesan and poultry seasoning.
Dip turkey in egg mixture, then in bread crumb mixture, coating thickly.
In frying pan, melt 1 tablespoon butter and 1 tablespoon oil.
Saute a few turkey slices at a time over low heat for 5 minutes.
Add remaining oil and butter as needed.
Return all cooked turkey to frying pan.
Add wine; cover and simmer for 2 minutes.
Top with fried mushrooms.

title: brownies(low-fat)
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Spray square 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Mix brown sugar, margarine, vanilla, egg and egg white.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except powdered sugar.
Spread in pan.
Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, about 20 minutes.
Cool and cut into 2-inch squares.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Makes 16 brownies.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Measure and mix all dry ingredients except nuts in a large bowl.
In a second bowl, mix all liquid ingredients and thoroughly blend with mixer.
Add dry ingredients in small portions at a time.
Add nuts.
Pour in 2 (1 pound) coffee cans, greased, or 2 (1 pound) loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool and serve.

title: peter paul mounds
directions: Mix all ingredients real well.
Form into balls (size of walnuts).
Chill and dip in dipping chocolate.
Place on wax paper until chocolate is firm.

title: vegetable creole
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add cheese, stirring until melted. Add the corn and pepper to the melted butter; stir.
Add the remaining ingredients except toast to cheese mixture.
Heat over low flame until egg is cooked.
Pour all over toast.
Serve at once.
Makes 5 servings.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix together.
Use 3 teaspoons of mix for 1 cup of hot tea. Good over ice, too!

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix jello and water together.
Let cool, but not until jelled. Mix Dream Whip according to directions on package.
Mix cottage cheese into this mixture.
Pour in jello and mix well.
Put into refrigerator until firm, about 2 hours.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Blend condensed milk and Cool Whip together, beating well with a fork.
Add frozen lemonade and lemon juice.
Blend until all frozen crystals are dissolved.
Pour into crust.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.
Yields 6 servings.

title: ranch hand breakfast muffins
directions: On a griddle or skillet, heat butter.
Saute ham until heated and starting to get crisp.
Sprinkle with cheese, cover and heat on low flame.
Toast and butter muffins with spatula; remove equal amounts of ham and cheese.
Place on open-faced muffins.
Dollop with taco sauce and sour cream.
Serves 4.

title: friendship tea
directions: Mix together.
For each cup of tea, add 3 heaping teaspoonfuls to boiling water.

title: wilted spinach salad
directions: Wash spinach, discarding stems.
Pat dry on paper towels; tear into bite-size pieces and place in a bowl.
Add onion and sprinkle with pepper.
Chill.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together.
Mix 1/4 cup in 5 quart ice cream pail of boiling water and serve.

title: baked potato casserole
directions: Layer each step in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: favorite frosting
directions: Beat altogether until smooth.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and mix by hand, the more the better!
Form into balls the size of a walnut.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Place on cookie sheets and flatten slightly.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Mix cream cheese, Cheddar cheese and mayonnaise.
Spread mixture over ham slices and roll up.
Refrigerate for about 1 hour and then cut and serve with crackers.

title: nana's pretzel salad
directions: Mix crushed pretzels and 3 tablespoons of sugar with melted butter.
Pat into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake in a 400° oven for 8 minutes.
Let cool.

title: excellent brownies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in bowl, then add margarine and eggs. Combine all ingredients, except nuts.
Mix in mixing bowl at medium speed, then add nuts.
Pour into greased and floured cookie sheet. Bake 30 minutes at 350° or until done.
Cool.

title: lemon sauce
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and a pinch of salt in a saucepan. Slowly add water and heat over medium heat until thick and clear. Remove from heat; add butter, lemon juice and lemon rind.
Serve with any variety of cakes (i.e.
unfrosted orange, vanilla or pound cake).
Also good with puddings and ice cream.
A variation includes adding 1/4 cup crushed pineapple instead of water.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix cake as directed on box.
Butter the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan and place nuts and coconut in bottom of pan.
Pour cake mix over.
Mix powdered sugar, butter and cream cheese together.
(Butter and cream cheese do better if softened at room temperature.)
Drop in drops on top of cake mix and bake. Cake will crack like an earthquake has occurred.
Bake for about 45 minutes or until done.

title: r.m.'s irish cream
directions: Whip all ingredients in blender.
(Will keep in refrigerator for 1 month.)

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: In a sauce pan, combine the broth, onion, broccoli, thyme, bay leaf and garlic.
Bring to boil. Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.
Place into food processor.
Cover and blend for 30-60 seconds until smooth.
In same pan, melt butter, blend in flour,
salt and pepper.
Add milk all at once.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in broccoli puree from processor.

title: fresh apple walnut cake
directions: Combine flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg; set aside.
In large bowl, beat on medium speed the sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla until smooth.
Gradually beat in flour mixture until smooth.
Fold in apples and walnuts.
Pour into greased pound cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes in pan.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients.
Add eggs, buttermilk and salad oil.
Mix well.
Cover and refrigerate.
Will keep in the refrigerator for up to 6 weeks.
When ready for fresh muffins, fill muffin tins 2/3 full and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix and pour in baking dish.

title: cuke pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers in lime water for 24 hours, then soak in clear water for 3 hours.
Mix vinegar and sugar; tie spices and salt in cheesecloth and put in vinegar and sugar mixture.
Bring to a boil.
Put cucumbers in mixture and let soak overnight.
Boil 30 minutes.
Add raisins and boil 5 more minutes.
Pack in jars and seal.
Chill before serving.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven and baking sheet to 375°.
Beat sweet potatoes until smooth.
Mix in butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Mix in nutmeg, salt and evaporated milk.
Pour filling into pie crust and put on baking sheet.
Bake for 60 to 65 minutes. Cool before serving.
May be served with Cool Whip.

title: chick 'n' dressing
directions: Cut cooked chicken in bite size pieces.
Mix melted butter with dressing.
Dilute soup with broth.
In a 2-quart casserole, layer 1/3 dressing, 1/2 chicken and 1/2 soup; repeat, ending with dressing.
Bake, uncovered, for 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift the sugar, flour and salt in a bowl; set aside.
In a saucepan, bring butter, shortening, water and cocoa to a boil. Remove from heat and pour the dry ingredients into melted mixture. Mix well.
Beat in eggs and other ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into greased and floured 10 to 15-inch pan.
Bake for 50 minutes at 325°.

title: pumpkin pecan bread
directions: In a small bowl combine first 6 ingredients and set aside. In
a large mixer bowl, cream margarine and sugar until light. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Blend in pumpkin.
Add dry ingredients and mix just until moistened. Turn into two greased 8 x 4-inch loaf pans.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool on wire racks.

title: hot water corn bread
directions: You will also need a skillet (cast-iron or stainless steel).

title: lemon sesame scallops
directions: Combine yellow pepper and carrot in 10-inch microwaveproof pie plate; sprinkle with water and a pinch each of salt and pepper. Cover and microwave on High 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir in snow peas. Microwave, covered, 30 seconds more.
Let stand, covered, 2 minutes.

title: spicy chicken
directions: Mix sauce ingredients and pour over chicken in baking dish. Cover with foil and bake at 350° until done.
Turn chicken after first 1/2 hour.

title: hospitality pie
directions: In skillet, melt butter.
Put in coconut and nuts and toast; set aside to cool.
Mix the cream cheese, Eagle Brand
milk and Cool Whip.
Put half of the toasted mixture in with the Cool Whip mixture.
Stir well; put this mixture into the two pie crusts. Sprinkle the remaining 1/2 of the toasted mixture on top of the pies.
Then drizzle ice cream topping on top of each pie.
These freeze well or keep in refrigerator if you do not freeze.

title: pot roast patke style
directions: Put roast, potatoes and carrots into a large roasting pan.
Add mushroom soup and dry onion soup mix.
Mix well, using hands if you wish.
Cover and bake in 300° oven for three hours.
Oh!
so good.

title: pennsylvania cole slaw
directions: Beat cream, sugar, vinegar and salt together thoroughly until the dressing is like whipped cream.
Discard outer leaves of cabbage. Shred the rest finely and combine with dressing just before it is ready to serve.
Serves 6.
Enjoy!

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Wash the cranberries, then put them on the fire with the water, but in a covered saucepan. Let them simmer until each cranberry bursts open. Then remove cover of the saucepan. Add the sugar and let them all boil twenty minutes without the cover. The cranberries must never be stirred from the time they are placed on the fire.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook and drain mixed vegetables.
Add next four ingredients to cooked vegetables.
Place in casserole dish.
Use crumbs on top and put pats of butter on the crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bubble cake
directions: Place rolls in bottom of Bundt pan.
Pour ingredients in order over rolls.
Melt stick of oleo and pour over all.
Let sit overnight on counter (not refrigerated).
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: turkey or chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine.
Add broth and mix with dressing mix.
Put 1/2 of this mixture in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Combine chicken, celery, onion and mayo.
Put this over dressing for the second layer.
Put remaining dressing over for third layer.
Beat egg and milk together and pour over the third layer.
Cover pan and set in refrigerator overnight.

title: pear butter
directions: Note:
If recipe is halved, half each ingredient along with pear pulp.

title: prosno
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in buttered casserole dish.

title: mom's white cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together, adding flour gradually, enough to make a soft dough. Roll and cut with cookie cutters.
Sprinkle with sugar and place a raisin in the center. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes. These cookies remain soft.
Makes 36.

title: chocolate chip pudding cookies
directions: Mix flour with baking soda.
Combine butter, sugars, pudding mix, and vanilla in a large mixing bowl.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture, then stir in chips and nuts.
(Batter will be stiff)

title: diabetic breakfast fruit loaf
directions: Combine and whisk together all liquid items.
Sift together all dry ingredients; combine. Fold apricots, dates,
raisins and nuts into mixture.
Bake in Bundt pan or loaf pan, greased with Pam and floured.
Bake at 350° for about 40 to 50 minutes or until cleanly tested.

title: coffee punch
directions: Pour all ingredients together in large punch bowl; mix and serve.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix first three ingredients and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan, lightly greased.
Cook at 300° for 15 minutes, until set.
Cool completely.
Mix cream cheese and sugar; fold in 1/2 of Cool Whip. Spread on cool crust.
Mix chocolate pudding mix with milk.
Beat until it begins to set.
Spread on other mixture.
Cool in refrigerator for 30 minutes
until set.
Add rest of Cool Whip. Sprinkle on chopped nuts or shaved chocolate or lemon rind.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Garnish with crushed potato chips.

title: meatballs hawaiian
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Form meatballs around a chunk of pineapple, making sure all the pineapple is covered.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: coconut cream cheese filling
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter in skillet.
Add coconut, stirring constantly, over low heat, until golden brown.
Spread coconut on paper towel to cool.
Cream 2 tablespoons butter with cream cheese.
Add milk; beat in sugar gradually.
Blend in vanilla. Stir in 1 3/4 cups coconut.
Spread and sprinkle with rest of coconut.

title: glazed fruited chicken
directions: Drain fruit; set aside.
Reserve 1/2 cup liquid.
Stir liquid into salad dressing.
Stir over medium heat until it boils.
Add stuffing.
Spread in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Add chicken. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Brush with additional salad dressing.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Melt marmalade; arrange fruit around chicken.
Brush with marmalade.
Bake 15 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: bacon cheese dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together and bake for 20 minutes.
Serve with Ritz-type crackers for dipping.

title: bread and butter pickles(diet center)
directions: Cut cucumbers and onions; toss with salt.
Place in large magnelite or heavy pot.
Cover for 1 hour.
While cucumbers are standing for 1 hour, mix remaining ingredients together.
Heat until just boiling.
Drain cucumbers.
Add mixture.
Heat until boiling.
Process into hot jars and lids.
Yields approximately 9 pints.
If jars are sealed, it does not require refrigeration.

title: chocolate pumpkin muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400° and grease 12 muffin cups. Combine dry ingredients in large bowl, making a well in the center. Combine wet ingredients and pour into well. Add morsels and stir just until moistened. Fill cups 3/4 full. Sprinkle with 1 teaspoon nuts. Bake 18 to 20 minutes. Cool 5 minutes before removing from pan.

title: new orleans squash
directions: Cook sliced squash until fork-tender; drain. Saut onions and pepper in butter. Add all ingredients except crumbs. Pour into 1 1/2-quart greased casserole. Top with crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 6. Can freeze. Can do ahead.

title: easy crock-pot chicken(number of servings: 6 to 8)
directions: Wash and separate chicken breasts.
Place in crock-pot.
Mix soup, sour cream or yogurt and flour and pour over chicken.
Cook on low heat for 8 to 10 hours.
If necessary to cook more quickly, cook chicken and soup only at high heat for 3 to 5 hours, adding sour cream or yogurt and flour during last half hour of cooking. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: quick chocolate pie
directions: Prepare filling as per instructions on box.
Use 2 boxes for thicker pie. Fill crust and finish cooling in refrigerator.
Add vanilla to cream and beat until frothy. Add sugar slowly and continue beating until stiff peaks form.
Spread over pie and serve or store in refrigerator.
Almost sugar free.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Put all ingredients, except bacon, in a covered pot and simmer just until tender.
Saute diced bacon until a light brown.
Put cooked zucchini (include any liquid in pot) and sauteed bacon into blender at medium speed about 1 minute, doing 1/3 at a time.
You can freeze zucchini soup.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions.
Cook broccoli until tender.
In a large pan, melt together Cheez Whiz and cream of mushroom soup.
Stir until well blended.
Add rice and broccoli; mix together.
Put in an 8 x 8-inch casserole dish.
Heat in 350° oven until sides bubble (approximately 15 minutes).
Sprinkle with French fried onion rings.
Brown for 5 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cut tops off peppers; remove seeds and membranes.
Parboil in boiling water for about 5 minutes.
Saute beef and onions in butter until cooked through.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Whip cream until thick.
Mix chocolate with cream.
Place a layer of graham cracker on the bottom of a medium size pan.
Place layer of cream mixture on top of bottom layer of gram.
Build your cake from there, ending in cream mixture.
Refrigerate over night. Keep Refrigerated.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix brown sugar, flour and spices in a large mixing bowl.
Cut margarine into sugar mixture and blend until mixture is crumbly. Peel and slice apples into 1 1/2-quart baking dish, which has been greased.
Add water or juice.
Sprinkle sugar mixture on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: white bean chili
directions: Combine and bring to boil above ingredients; cook until chicken is done.
Remove chicken and shred or chop.
Return chicken to stock and add 2 cans white Northern beans.
Top with Monterey Jack cheese, chips and salsa as desired (garnish).

title: sour cream cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, alternating flour and sour cream.
Grease and flour 8 x 8-inch square pan.
Pour in half the dough. Sprinkle with a mixture of 1/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon. Pour in remaining dough and top with 1/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: quick stroganoff
directions: Cut meat diagonally across grain into strips 1/4-inch thick. Heat cooking oil in skillet and brown meat quickly.
Drain off oil.

title: corn muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Heat oven to 350°.
Pour in one tablespoon of oil or shortening in each muffin tin.
Heat oil. Pour in cornbread mix and bake until brown.

title: cole slaw
directions: Toast seeds and almonds in 375° oven for 5 minutes.
Mix all ingredients together.
Blend canola oil, vinegar, sugar, and seasoning packet from noodles.
Pour over slaw 15 minutes before serving.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Cook sausage until brown and crumbly; drain.
Separate dough into 8 triangles.
Place on ungreased 12-inch pizza pan with points toward center.
Press over bottom and up sides, sealing to make crust.
Spoon sausage on crust; sprinkle on potatoes.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Beat eggs with milk, salt and pepper; pour into crust.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: new england boiled dinner
directions: Simmer corned beef in water to cover for 2 hours.
Add turnips. Cook 30 minutes.
Add carrots and potatoes; cook 30 minutes longer or until meat/veggies are tender.
About 1 hour before meat is tender, cook beets; skin and keep warm.
Begin cooking cabbage in a large kettle about 30 minutes before meat is tender.
Slice meat. Arrange on a large, warm platter.
Spoon hot veggies around meat. Pour melted butter over veggies.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serve with horseradish sauce and mustard.

title: easy fish loaf
directions: Remove bones from fish and skin.
Flake with fork.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Place in loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: vodka slush
directions: Boil 7 cups water and 2 cups sugar; cool.
Bring to a boil 2 cups water and steep tea bags for 5 minutes.
Mix orange juice and lemonade with vodka and freeze, stirring occasionally.

title: meat empanadas
directions: Fry ground meat with its own juice.
Add the onions, tomatoes, bell peppers and salt and pepper when it is brown; taste it before.
In a large bowl, pour the corn flour, 1 tablespoon salt and the water; handle it until it is soft.
Make little balls and start to make little tortillas with a tortilla machine.

title: sausage pasta supper
directions: Stir-fry all ingredients in the 3 tablespoons butter, 1/4 teaspoon garlic powder and 1 teaspoon oregano.
Heat through. Stir in 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese.
Serve over buttered pasta with additional cheese.

title: frozen lime mint salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine both cans of undrained pineapple, lime gelatin, marshmallows and mints.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon mixture into paper baking cups in muffin tins.
Cover and freeze 6 hours or more. Peel off paper and serve on lettuce.
Garnish with a red cherry. Can be kept frozen in covered container for a length of time.

title: american chop suey
directions: Saute peppers, onions and mushrooms in cooking oil in large frying pan until soft and tender.
Brown chopped meat and drain fat.
Add vegetables to meat mixture.
Add tomato sauce and remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil, then simmer 20 to 25 minutes.
Cook macaroni according to package directions and add to meat mixture.

title: potato soup
directions: Dice and cover carrots, onion and celery with just enough water to cover them and simmer while peeling potatoes.
Peel and dice potatoes. Add to carrots, onion and celery.
Add enough water just to cover vegetables.
Cook until done.
Turn off the heat and add margarine, evaporated milk and sprinkle in parsley.
Make sure soup is off the heat because evaporated milk will curdle.

title: no cook rice krispies squares
directions: Mix oats and cereal together in large bowl.
Bring sugar and syrup to a boil over medium heat.
Add peanut butter and vanilla. Mix well.
Pour over cereal mix and mix well.
Add chocolate chips.
Mix.
Pour in 9 x 12 inch greased pan.
Press firmly to set.
Cut into squares.

title: yummy blackberry dumplings
directions: Heat berries and sugar to a gentle boil.
Mix Bisquick and milk with fork.
Spoon dough onto berries.
Cook, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Cover and cook 10 minutes longer.
Cool slightly and serve with whipped cream.

title: gail's italian beef
directions: Place roast in covered baking dish.
Add beef broth, seasoning mix, water, oregano and pepperoncini.
Cover and bake at 275° for 5 hours until tender.
Remove meat from pan and shred.
Place meat back in pan, add pepperoncini and mushrooms.
Cook 30 minutes more.

title: mom's marinated vegetable salad
directions: Mix together.
Cover and let set for 21 hours in refrigerator. Very good with baked ham.

title: fruit dip
directions: Melt both in microwave.
Beat well with a spoon.
Serve with fruit.

title: poor man's steak
directions: Mix all ingredients except gravy.
Spread in a loaf pan. Chill in refrigerator overnight.
Cut into 8 serving pieces.
Coat the "steaks" with flour and fry in a little margarine.
Place fried "steaks" in a crock-pot; cover with gravy and cook on high for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Stir yeast into 1/4 cup warm water and let stand 5 minutes to dissolve.
Pour milk into large bowl; add flour (3 cups) and dissolved yeast.
Blend well.
Cover and let rise in warm place until double in bulk (approximately one hour). Add sugar, salt, cinnamon, eggs, butter and 3/4 cup flour.
Blend well.
Turn out on lightly floured board and knead gently, working in remaining 3/4 cup of flour until dough can be easily handled. Knead in raisins.
Pull pieces of dough about the size of medium lemons; roll into 8-inch long rope and form into coil.
Arrange into buttered 9-inch cake pans.
Cover and let rise until double in size (approximately 1 to 1 1/2 hours).
Brush tops with milk.
Bake for 25 minutes.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, Karo, peanuts and salt 4 minutes at full power. Stir.
Cook 3 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla.
Cook 2 minutes. Stir in soda until golden brown.
Pour on buttered cookie sheet. Break into pieces when cool.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken.
Remove cooled chicken from bone.
Reserve the water from the chicken to boil spaghetti in.
Saute mushrooms, celery and onion.
Add chicken and soup to cooked veggies and mix. Add cooked spaghetti.
Put in casserole.
Mix in 1/2 of cheese. Top with remaining cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: ham and artichoke casserole
directions: Melt butter in saucepan over medium heat.
Blend in flour. Remove from heat and gradually stir in warm milk.
Return to heat and stir until thickened.
Add seasonings, then cheese.
Cook until melted.
Remove from heat and stir in sherry.

title: simply sensational salsa
directions: In a medium sized bowl, combine all ingredients and mix well. Cover and let stand in refrigerator at least 2 hours. Salsa will get hotter the longer it stands. Makes 2 quarts.

title: potato soup
directions: Drain juice from potatoes, saving 1/2 cup.
Add cream chicken soup, milk and potato juice.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir good and simmer 15 minutes.

title: sour cherry pie
directions: Mix
sugar, butter, salt and cherries.
Bring to a boil and cook a few minutes.
Taste for desired sweetness.
Combine cornstarch
to
thicken cherries.
Bake at 425° until crust is golden brown.

title: margarita shrimp
directions: Heat oil in skillet over medium-high heat. Add shrimp, onions and garlic and saut until shrimp just begin to turn pink (about 1 minute). Remove from heat and add tequila. Return to heat and bring to a boil, scraping up any brown bits. Transfer to a medium bowl to cool. (Can be prepared 6 hours ahead.) Cover and refrigerate.

title: cajun chicken
directions: In electric skillet, bring liquid to boil. Rub chicken parts with salt and garlic salt.
Add chicken parts to cola mixture and cover.
Simmer 1 hour, turning occasionally.
Serve with rice.
If juice is watery, add cornstarch or flour to thicken and pour over chicken and rice.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine shortening and peanut butter.
Add the sugars, then the beaten egg.
Combine dry ingredients and add to mixture.
This makes a stiff dough.
Roll into balls, flatten with a fork and place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: soft old-fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and oleo.
Add eggs and mix.
Add buttermilk and mix.
Add vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients and mix into batter. Drop by heaping tablespoons onto greased cookie sheet (about 6 to 8 per sheet).
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Sprinkle with granulated sugar while hot or ice.

title: sauerkraut cake(don't laugh; it's good!)
directions: Blend together the butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add dry ingredients and water alternately to egg mixture.
Rinse, drain and chop sauerkraut and stir into cake batter mixture.
Turn into two 8-inch or one 9 x 13-inch pan and bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until center springs back when lightly pressed.
Ice and fill with Mocha Whipped Cream or Powder-Sugar Icing.

title: autumn vegetable beef soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in large saucepan.
Drain off fat. Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil and simmer, covered, 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: chocolate milk
directions: Add chocolate to desired consistency.
Stir until dissolved. Drink.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Alternate layers as follows:
beans, water chestnuts, and cheese.
Mix all other ingredients, except onions, thoroughly and pour over layers.
Bake at 350° for 45 minute to 1 hour.
Put onions on top for last 15 minutes of baking time.

title: kathy's corn bread
directions: Mix well.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 425° for about 20 minutes.

title: ice cream cookies(kid's recipe)
directions: Beat together
butter and sugar.
Add egg and beat well.
Add flour and beat well.
Add vanilla and beat.
Stir in chocolate chips, nuts or M&M's.
Spoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until cookies are golden brown.
Makes about 2 dozen.
Recipe may be doubled.

title: blueberry bread
directions: Beat egg and sugar, add orange juice and oil.
Mix flour and dry ingredients together.
Sift, add to egg mixture.
Add nuts and blueberries, mix well.
Turn into greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for 50-55 minutes.

title: sweet potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes 30 minutes; cool.
Dice.
Cook peas 3 to 5 minutes; cool.
Mix remaining ingredients; add to potatoes and peas.
Gently stir together.
Makes 8 servings.
Calories: 255 per serving.

title: tomato bake
directions: Fry bacon; remove and drain.
Leave 1 tablespoon of grease in pan.
Saute onion and green pepper in grease.
Mix all ingredients.
Spoon into lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Sprinkle bacon crumbs and cheese over top.
Cook at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: wild rice soup
directions: Saute onion, carrot and celery in the butter.
Add flour to thicken, then add chicken broth.
Next, add rice; mix.
Lastly add cream; do not boil.
Cook slowly for up to 2 hours.
A crock-pot works well on low heat for the 2 hour cooking.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream eggs, shortening and sugar.
Stir flour, vanilla and coconut into mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in tube or Bundt pan.

title: cream wafer cookies
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Chill 1 hour.
Heat oven to 375°. Roll 1/8-inch thick.
Cut into 1/2-inch rounds.
Transfer to waxed paper heavily sprinkled with sugar, turning to coat both sides. Place on ungreased baking sheet. Prick in 4 places with a fork. Bake 7 to 9 minutes or until slightly puffy.
Put 2 cooled cookies together with Creamy Butter Filling.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Blend together sugar and flour.
Stir into eggs with remaining ingredients.
Mix by hand or with mixer.
Pour into 2 greased 9-inch pie pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, until coconut is browned and pie is firm.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix ingredients.
Put 2 cups of crushed potato chips in bottom of casserole (save some for the top).
Put rest of ingredients in casserole.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: ground beef and potatoes
directions: Cook meat and onion.
Drain.
Layer 1/2 of the potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch dish, then layer 1/2 of the meat mixture, followed by 1/2 cup of cheese.
Top with remaining potatoes, then rest of meat mixture.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti in salt water; drain.
Mix together the dressings.
Add mixed dressings and vegetables, except tomato, to drained spaghetti and let marinate overnight in refrigerator. Before serving, add diced tomato.

title: ben's fried okra
directions: Wash and drain well small pods of okra.
Slice into rounds, about 1/4-inch thick and discard stem ends and tips. Sprinkle with salt and roll in cornmeal to coat well.
Drop into hot fat and cook until golden brown, stirring often.

title: harvey wallbanger cake
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine cake and pudding mixes.
Add eggs, oil, orange juice, Galliano and vodka.
Beat at low speed with electric mixer 1/2 minute; beat at medium speed 5 minutes (do not underbeat.)
Scrape bowl often.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch fluted tube pan; bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes; remove cake to rack.
Pour glaze over warm cake.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Rinse rice; drain well.
Drain tomatoes, mushrooms and olives and save juices to use for 1 1/2 cups boiling liquid needed.
Add all ingredients; mix well. Place in 2-quart casserole with a lid (spray with oil first).
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.
Keep covered or it will be too dry.

title: lainey's arroz con pollo(rice with chicken)
directions: Use a large, heavy Dutch oven type pot for cooking.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix all in 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Set dish in shallow pan holding 1 inch hot water.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until pudding is firm at edges.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Add lettuce, onion and celery into large container.
Cook peas as directed; drain and add to lettuce.
Mix well.
Spread mayo on top of lettuce, onion, celery and peas.
Then top with sugar, cheese and bacon bits.
Refrigerate for 12 hours.
Mix well and serve.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Preheat oven to 400° and lightly grease baking sheets. Combine flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt; set aside.
Cream 1 1/2 cups sugar, butter or margarine and shortening.
Beat in eggs and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Stir in flour mixture just until blended.

title: hot tamales
directions: Chop the first five ingredients and fry.
Mash frequently to keep meat in small pieces.
Season with cumin and chili powder. Cook more, then season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: turtle cake
directions: Melt caramels with milk in top of double boiler or in microwave at 30% (do this before mixing cake as it takes a while to unwrap and melt the candy).
Combine cake mix with water, butter and eggs in large mixer bowl and blend on low speed 30 seconds.
Then beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour 1/2 the batter in greased 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until cake puffs up and is gooey.
Pour caramel mixture over partially baked layer to within 1/2-inch from the edge.
Sprinkle nuts and chocolate chips evenly over caramel.
Pour remaining batter and bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool in pan and cut into squares.
Top with ice cream.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Soften cream cheese and thaw Cool Whip.
Beat all ingredients together.
Pour into pie shell and freeze until firm.

title: italian vegetable fondue
directions: Pour oil into fondue pot; add garlic and pepper.
Chop anchovies; add to fondue pot with anchovy oil.
Heat until bubbly. Serve as dip for fresh vegetables such as radishes, carrot sticks, small green onions and celery sticks.
Yields 6 servings.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except coconut and nutmeg.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) unbaked pie shells.
Sprinkle with coconut and nutmeg.
Cover well.
Bake for 60 minutes at 350°.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: salsa
directions: Blanch tomatoes and remove cores and skins.
Quarter. Coarsely chop peppers and onions.
Combine all ingredients.
Cook 1 1/2 hours.
Process in hot water bath.
Pint jars, 10 to 12 minutes.

title: easy cutout cookies
directions: In large bowl, combine cake mix, shortening, water and egg. Blend together with a fork until crumbly.
Knead dough.
Form a ball.

title: banana muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease 2 tins (holding 6 muffins each) with soft butter.
(I use vegetable shortening.)
In a bowl, beat together butter, brown sugar and egg, mixing thoroughly.
In a large bowl, combine flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt. Make a hole in the center of the flour mixture.
Pour the butter mixture into the hole; then mix it.
Pour into muffin tins, filling about 3/4 full.
Bake for about 20 to 25 minutes.
Insert a toothpick in the center.
The toothpick should be clean.

title: ham sandwich filling
directions: Mix together using enough mayonnaise to hold mixture together. Good on rolls.

title: skillet baked beans
directions: Brown bacon in skillet (325° in electric skillet); remove and saute onion in drippings.
Combine other ingredients with bacon drippings.
When beans start to bubble, reduce heat.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Fold in bacon.
Can be baked on top of 30 minutes.

title: chocolate chip pudding cake
directions: In saucepan add 2 cups milk to pudding mix.
Cook until pudding is thickened, stirring constantly.
Add pudding to dry cake mix, stirring to mix completely.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with chocolate chips and chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese stand at room temperature.
Combine it and shredded Cheddar.
Add pepper, pimento, onion, sauces, lemon juice and salt and pepper.
Mix together well (can do with hands) and shape into a ball.
Press chopped pecans all over ball.

title: quick cake
directions: Mix with electric mixer in order given.
Bake in tube pan for 1 hour at 325°.

title: kentucky spoon bread
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: rolling ice cream
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
together.
Pour mixture into one pound cans and
put
lids on.
Place each can in a three pound can and add
layers
of ice and rock salt until 3/4 full.
Put lid on and roll the can back and forth for 30 minutes.
